title: chicken casserole
directions: In 2-quart casserole dish layer chicken on bottom, then rice. On stove top in saucepan combine soup and water, heat.
Then pour soup over chicken and rice.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix altogether; put in loaf pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 55 minutes or until golden brown and toothpick comes out clean.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put chicken in stock with onion and green pepper.
Let simmer until onion and pepper are soft.
Add soy sauce and slices of tomato.
Let simmer until tomato is soft.
Mix cornstarch with a little cold water and stir into chicken mixture to thicken.
Pour over rice and serve.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, cream, sugar, salt and vanilla in a bowl; mix well. Add condensed milk and pudding mix. Stir until blended. Pour into freezer can and add milk almost to fill line. Churn in freezer per instructions. Makes 4 quarts.
The pudding mix adds to the flavor and body of the ice cream.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Chop all vegetables and mix together with sunflower seeds and bacon.

title: orange pie
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Drain oranges and cut in small pieces. Combine fruit in a bowl and sprinkle with the powdered jello. Add Eagle Brand and nuts.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Better if refrigerated overnight.
Serves 12.

title: mystery pecan cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Using mixer, blend cream cheese with sugar, 1 egg, salt and vanilla until smooth.
Spread in pie crust. Sprinkle with pecans.

title: corn bread stuffing
directions: Simmer onions in boiling water until tender. Drain, reserving 1 cup of the liquor. Mix crumbs and seasoning. Add celery soup and onions, chicken soup and 1 cup of liquor in which they were cooked. Add butter, onions and eggs and mix thoroughly. This amount of dressing will stuff a 10 to 12 pound bird. If baked separately, allow 45 minutes for baking.

title: taco salad
directions: Toss all these ingredients together.
Eat immediately.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Take 1 cup fruit juice and add to pudding mix and Tang. Mix with mixer until thick.
Pour over fruit and chill.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook cheese until it melts.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Place beans in casserole dish, pour mixture over them.
Top with crackers or bread crumbs.
Spread small amount of butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until liquid thickens.

title: green stuff
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding together.
Add and stir Cool Whip and marshmallows.

title: chicken rice soup
directions: Boil chicken in water in a large pot.
Save chicken broth. Drain fat.
Add cut up pieces of cooked chicken to large pot with cans of chicken broth.
Add tomatoes, cilantro, celery, carrots and onion.
Add garlic salt; stir.
Add green chiles and green chile jalapeno salsa.
Cover; let it simmer until vegetables are cooked.
Add 1/2 cup rice.
When rice is cooked, add shredded Monterey Jack cheese.

title: conch stew
directions: Crack conch shell with hammer.
Remove conch; clean down to white meat, making sure all black has been removed.
Beat conch meat with hammer until about 1/4-inch thick; cut into bite-size pieces.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms.
Remove stems and chop up.
Add stems, onion, cheese, celery, butter and sauce mixed, to the mushroom cap.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: bette's date balls
directions: Cook dates, eggs, sugar and margarine or butter in double boiler until done; cool.
Pour over Rice Krispies.
Form into balls with hands well coated with butter.
Roll in nuts or coconut.

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a Bundt pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: dutch butter cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar together.
Add egg half, salt and vanilla. Mix this, then add flour.
Make big ball and push this in pie dish (plus or minus 8-inch).
Decorate with almonds.
Coat with egg half (leftover).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, then turn the oven off and let the cookie cool in the oven.

title: cinnamon breakfast rolls
directions: Mix yeast, sugar and water; stir until yeast dissolves.
Add cake mix; stir well with 2 cups warm water.
Add 2 1/2 cups flour and beat until smooth.
Add 2 1/2 cups flour and stir well.
Place on floured board and knead in enough flour to make a sticky mixture.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out, only working with about a third of the batter at a time.
After cutting with cookie cutter, dip one side in sugar.
Put on baking sheet.
Bake 8 or 10 minutes in moderate oven.
I prefer 325° oven for 4 minutes in lower half and 4 minutes in upper half.
Don't overbake.

title: polish sauerkraut
directions: Cook mushrooms, onions and peppers in butter.
In crock-pot, cook sausage until heated.
Add vegetables, kraut, tomatoes and salt and pepper.
Cook in crock-pot on high for 3 to 4 hours or on low for 5 to 6 hours.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Bone chicken and put in baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream. Pour over chicken.
Mix crumbled Ritz crackers, poppy seed and butter.
Put on top of chicken and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: creole chops
directions: In hot frying pan, season and brown pork chops slowly and thoroughly on both sides.
Mix together all other ingredients and pour over browned chops.
Cover and cook slowly for one hour or until tender.
Serve with rice.

title: winning tea punch(makes 25 five ounce servings)
directions: In a punch bowl, combine instant tea, water, concentrates and cranberry juice.
Just before serving, add ice.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables, celery and onions and cook on stove until done. Drain. Mix mayonnaise and cheese. Pour into baking dish. Put on top 1 stick Ritz crackers, crumbled with 1 stick of butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, corn syrup, butter, vanilla flavoring and flour to the beaten eggs.
Add pecans and pour mixture into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Cook in preheated 275° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until set.
Use bottom rack.

title: company squash
directions: Combine sour cream, soup and sauteed onion (or dry onion). Line casserole dish with butter.
Put 1/2 of stuffing mix on bottom of casserole dish.
Put layer of squash on top.
Pour 1/2 soup/sour cream mixture on top.
Put layer of squash on.
Pour rest of soup mixture on.
Pour rest of stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until brown on top and bubbly.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Put brown sugar, flour and two cups milk on in a double boiler and
bring	to
scalding point.
Beat egg yolks and add other 1/2 cup milk;
stir
into
hot	mixture.
When done, add butter and vanilla.
Pour
into crust.
Top with meringue made from egg whites and brown.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and marshmallow; squeeze juice of 1 orange in until mixture is of dip consistency.
Shave rind and add to dip. Serve with pieces of cut fruit such as pineapple, apples, strawberries and melon pieces.
Great for kids and summer parties.

title: toa vakalolo(chicken in coconut cream)
directions: Broil, grill lightly or saute chicken until almost cooked.
Cut onions into rings and grill/saute until transparent.
Put chicken and onion into a saucepan or large frying pan with chopped and skinned tomatoes.
Pour coconut cream over chicken mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 15 minutes until chicken is tender.

title: apple impromptu
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare apples.
Place in greased pie pan.
Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples. Cover tightly with foil.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes. Meanwhile, cream butter.
Gradually add sugar; cream well.
Add vanilla and egg; beat well.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Spread evenly over apples in pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes longer at 400°, until golden brown.
Serve warm or cold topped with whipped cream.

title: queen elizabeth's cake
directions: Soak dates in boiling water with soda.

title: cherry cheesecake pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla. Fold in Cool Whip; blend well. Spoon into crusts. Chill at least 4 hours before serving. Spoon cherries on top.

title: 1000 island salad dressing
directions: Add all ingredients in a small bowl and whisk until proper thickness.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes; mash.
Add rest of ingredients.
Horseradish can be added, if desired, approximately 2 tablespoons.

title: green jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 3 cups of boiling water.
Mix mayonnaise, milk, lemon juice, cottage cheese and pineapple together and add to jello.
Stir to mix well.
Add to jello mixture the celery and pecans.
Refrigerate until solid.

title: lasagna
directions: Crumble beef and sausage in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and microwave at time cook High 7 to 9 minutes or until meat is lightly brown.
Stir 3 times.
Drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, mushrooms, oregano, garlic, salt and pepper.
In 10 x 6 x 2-inch oblong baking dish, layer 1/3 of noodles and top with 1/3 of sauce and 1/2 cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with last 1/3 of noodles and last 1/3 of sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover and microwave Medium-low for 30 minutes or until lasagna is hot at center, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 14 minutes.
Let stand, covered 5 minutes before serving.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss together first 5 ingredients and add a dressing made of sugar, mayonnaise and vinegar.
Blend together.

title: mary's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Cool and peel.
Mix with other ingredients.
Garnish with hard-cooked eggs, parsley and paprika. Use 2 extra eggs for garnish.

title: overnight cherry salad
directions: Drain cherries and cut up, drain pineapple.
Combine all ingredients, adding whipped cream and pecans.
(Can be kept a week while stored in refrigerator.)

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Wash and peel sweet potatoes and cut in strips.
Soak in cold salted water for a short time.
Drain; dry between towels.
Fry in deep fat at 365° for 3 to 5 minutes, or until brown.
Drain on absorbent paper; sprinkle lightly with salt.

title: speedy fajitas
directions: Cut peppers into 1 inch strips. Heat 1 tsp. oil and chicken or beef. Stir fry 3-4 minutes or until meat is done. Remove from heat. Heat 1 tsp. oil and add pepper and garlic. Stir fry 1-2 minutes. Add chicken or beef, onion soup mix, water and salsa to pepper mixture. Heat through. Warm tortillas and place mixture in center of tortillas. Serve with your choice of toppings.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix everything together except cheese. Place in greased 9 x 13 baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 - 45 minutes.
Place Velveeta slices on top and return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: fresh coconut pie(poppy's favorite)
directions: Mix sugar, flour, beaten egg yolks and milk.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Add butter and flavoring; cool.
Add fresh coconut.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.
Serve cold.

title: jalapeno cornbread casserole
directions: Combine cornmeal, milk, beaten eggs, salt, soda, bacon drippings, and corn.
Mix well, set aside.
Brown meat until crumbly.
Drain well on paper towels.
Pour half of corn batter into well greased cast iron skillet or baking dish that has been dusted with cornmeal.
Sprinkle grated cheese evenly over batter. Sprinkle meat evenly over cheese.
Then sprinkle chopped onions and jalapenos over meat.
Top with remaining cornbread batter. Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Cool and whip when soft set. Add pineapple.
Whip cream and fold in grated cheese.
Combine gelatin mixture to whipped cream mixture.
Divide crumbs.
Place half on bottom and sprinkle other half on top.

title: stabilized whipped cream frosting(a baker's secret instead of butter cream frosting.)
directions: Mix 1 3/4 cups frosting mix to 1 1/2 cups whipping cream.
In a large bowl, with electric mixer on low, mix the frosting mix and whipping cream for 30 seconds, scraping the bowl constantly.
Turn mixer to high and mix for 3 more minutes, scraping the bowl occasionally, until the mixture holds its shape.
It will remain stiff up to 48 hours.
May be used to frost and decorate cakes, cookies, etc.

title: foil wrapped veggies on grill
directions: Cut a large square of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Mix all ingredients and place on square.
Fold up securely so no juices escape.
Place on charcoal grill, turning once during cooking, 45 minutes to 1 hour.
May also be placed in 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: apple wheat crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix apples, 1/4 cup brown sugar, lemon juice, tapioca and cinnamon. Set aside for 10 minutes.

title: shrimp molded salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Soften cream cheese.
Heat soup; when hot, add cream cheese and gelatin.
Stir until melted.
Cool to room temperature, stirring occasionally.
Add celery, scallions and mayonnaise.
Pour half of the mixture in mold.
Drain shrimp; add to rest of cream cheese mixture.
Add to mold.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: oriental pepper steak
directions: Dredge pork chunks flour in and garlic salt.
Brown well in oil.
Drain.
Add 1 1/2 cups water, pepper flakes, instant minced onion, catsup, ground mustard, soy sauce and ginger.
Simmer 25 minutes.
Combine cornstarch, 1 tablespoon water and honey.
Stir into pork mixture.
Bring to a boil; cook 1 minute.
Serve over cooked rice.
Makes four 3/4 cup servings.

title: sugar free lemon cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Mix with electric mixer. Drop batter by rounded teaspoonful on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, then milk.
Put in the rest of ingredients.
(Add chocolate chips, if desired.)
Roll out, adding more flour as needed.
Cut to desired shapes.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Will make 50 to 60 cookies.

title: pecan balls
directions: Mix ingredients together and roll into balls. Roll in powdered sugar. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: fried apples
directions: Core apples and slice across, making rings.
Fry in hot grease until slightly brown.
Drain and dip in granulated sugar.
Serve hot.

title: surprise pie
directions: Blend all ingredients for 60 seconds.
Pour into a greased 10-inch deep pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add pineapple, including juice.
Congeal.

title: pepperoni roll
directions: Roll out dough, add cheese and top with pepperoni.
Roll and pinch to seal edges.
Cook at 375° until brown.
Serve sliced.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients except chips and cheese. Sprinkle them over top of mixture and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: suzie's strawberry delight
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare, bake and cool cake as directed on package.
Trim all crust from cake; cut or tear cake into bite size pieces and place in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: play dough
directions: Blend ingredients together and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture is too stiff to stir (about 3 minutes). Put on wax paper and knead until smooth.
(Not to be eaten!
For children's playing only!)

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or golden brown.
If using small pie shells, this will make 2 pies.

title: cole slaw
directions: Boil sugar, white vinegar and pemeril for 2 minutes.
Pour over cabbage.
Refrigerate.
Keeps 3 weeks.

title: angie's green chile casserole
directions: Layer first four ingredients in order given in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the next four ingredients and pour over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Spread 1 can tomato sauce over top.
Return to oven 15 minutes longer.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix flour, oleo and powdered sugar.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Toss cabbage and carrots.
Add sugar, vinegar and Miracle Whip.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.
Will keep several days.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 425 degrees for 5 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350 degrees and bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: orange delight salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling
water;
add	sherbet and mix well. Let set until
partially
congealed.
Stir	in mandarin oranges and whipped cream.	Pour in mold and let chill.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in butter until soft.
Add seasonings. In large bowl, beat eggs; add cheese and zucchini mixture. Spread 1 to 2 teaspoons mustard on crust, then mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Can use 8 ounces crescent dinner rolls for crust in 10-inch pie plate or 12 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: beefy vegetable-noodle soup
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion in Dutch oven until beef is brown.
Drain well.
Stir in sauce mix, water, bay leaf, salt, pepper and tomatoes with liquid.
Break up tomatoes with a fork. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer, stirring occasionally.
Stir in noodles and mixed vegetables.
Cover and cook 10 minutes longer.

title: perkins pancakes clone
directions: Put all ingredients into blender container. Process by pulsing (on-off) at high speed until smooth, about 2 minutes. Let batter stand for 10 minutes before using. Allow 1/4 cup batter for each 6-inch round pancake prepared on hot, lightly greased griddle. Makes 16 pancakes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Use pastry blender to cut shortening and all other ingredients until mixture resembles very fine bread crumbs.
Store in container in refrigerator.
Use as needed.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Serve on a bed of watercress or Boston Bibb lettuce.

title: peanut pie
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, corn syrup, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in peanuts and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread cubes in milk.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° in a pan of hot water for about 45 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: "forever" wedding cake
directions: Mix all with a pint of sympathy.
Flavor with cheerfulness and understanding.
Bake well forever.

title: pizza with hamburger crust
directions: Mix in large bowl, first 4 ingredients.
Stir in 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Spread meat mixture in 10-inch pizza pan or pie pan.
Pour on 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Arrange cheese strips in crisscross design on beans.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes at 425°.

title: mandarin orange jello
directions: Make jello, using 1 cup hot water and 1 cup juice.
Let it start to jell.
Whip cream and set aside.
Whip jello, then add softened cream cheese.
Add whipped cream.
Stir in fruit and chill.

title: german salad
directions: Press all liquid from sauerkraut (rinse).
Add all other ingredients.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix in blender.
Heat in 350° oven for about 1/2 hour or until lightly browned on top.
Serve with bread sticks.

title: sugared peanuts
directions: In a heavy saucepan, blend first 3 ingredients.
Boil until syrup will spin into a thread.
Pour in two cups of peanuts or pecan halves and stir constantly until syrup begins to harden. Pour out on waxed paper and separate halves and allow to cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli; add salt and pepper.
Mix cheese, mayonnaise, eggs, cream of mushroom soup and onion in saucepan. Stir at all times until boiling on medium, about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Put drained broccoli in casserole dish; top with sauce and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 or 30 minutes depending on oven.

title: quick and easy bars
directions: Cream eggs, brown sugar, vanilla, water and shortening.
Crush 1 2/3 cups graham crackers.
Add to creamed mixture, flour, chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake in 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan in a 350° oven for 16 to 18 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle chocolate chips on hot bars; let stand and spread.
Cool and cut.
Makes 24 bars.

title: tom's cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients. Form into ball and chill. When firm, coat with a mixture of chopped nuts and sesame seed, lightly toasted.

title: pickled squash
directions: Put squash and onions in salt water and cover 1 or 2 hours. Combine pepper, vinegar, sugar and seed; bring to a boil.
Drain water from squash and put into vinegar mixture.
Bring to a boil again, then put in jars and seal.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Pour hot water over broccoli to thaw.
Mix all ingredients together.
(Cheez Whiz mixes better if melted 30 seconds in microwave first.)
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: slushy punch
directions: Mix and freeze in gallon jug.
Set out 3 hours before serving. (Longer when cold weather.)

title: coffee can bread
directions: Combine all ingredients together and beat with electric mixer 2 minutes.
Then add 4 cups flour and knead until easy to handle. Divide in half and put in greased cans with lids on.
Let stand until lids pop off.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let stand in cans for 5 minutes; then remove.
(Add a pan of water to oven while baking.)

title: butterscotch oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add hot water.
Add flour mixed with soda and salt.
Add (stir by hand) nuts, oatmeal, vanilla and butterscotch chips.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, just until lightly browned.
Do not overbake.
Let cool for a few minutes and carefully remove with spatula.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt oleo.
Pour over stuffing mix and stir.
Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish with 1/2 the crumbs.
Save rest for top.
Mix all other ingredients; pour over stuffing mix.
Sprinkle rest of crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
May be made in 2 smaller size casseroles.
Freeze one.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Beat egg.
Add to flour/sugar.
Add vinegar and reserved pineapple juice.
Cook in small pan on low heat.
Stir and cook until thick.
Cool.
Pour cooled dressing over apples, pineapple and peanuts.
Mix in nondairy topping.
May sprinkle additional peanuts over top for garnish.

title: jan hagel cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and egg yolk and cream well.
Sift all the dry ingredients.
Add to the first mixture, then add vanilla.
Spread on a greased cookie sheet and brush with the slightly beaten egg white that has been diluted with 1 teaspoon water.
Sprinkle the top with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 300° for 1/2 hour.
Cut into squares while still warm.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt bars and 1 stick butter in saucepan over low heat.
Beat 1 stick butter and sugar. Add eggs. Add flour, soda and milk. Add candy, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan which has been greased and floured. Bake at 350° for at least 1 hour. Remove when it tests done. Frost with favorite chocolate frosting when cool.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Mix according to package directions, except leave out the water and use 1 can mandarin oranges.
Mix and bake.
Makes 3 layers or one 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: quick light corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375° (350° if using glass pan).
Mix and sift together first 5 ingredients.
Add yeast, buttermilk and shortening for a thin batter.
Mix lightly.
Pour into greased loaf pan; bake 55 minutes.
Cool on rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Freezes well.
If self-rising meal and flour are used; omit salt and soda.

title: hawaiian chicken salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together with enough salad dressing to hold together.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and marinate for 12 to 24 hours. Stir occasionally.
Use as appetizer or at picnics or lunch.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Cook onion in butter in large saucepan until tender.
Blend in flour, mustard, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in milk; cook and stir over medium heat until sauce thickens.
Stir in cheese. Arrange potatoes in greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with ham and pour sauce over all.
Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes longer.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pea salad
directions: Cut up lettuce, then layer with celery, eggs, green pepper, onion, peas and bacon bits.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar together. Stir all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: texas tortilla soup
directions: Heat butter and oil. Saute onion, jalapeno, garlic, carrots, celery and chicken. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Add combined spices, flour and hot pepper sauce. Stir in tomatoes and chicken broth. Simmer 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all the ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2 loaf pans (pans should be greased and floured).
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Let bread set for several minutes before removing from the pan.

title: pickled yellow squash
directions: Soak
squash, onion and bell pepper in salt for 1 hour. Cover with
ice
and
mix
thoroughly.
Drain.
Rinse in cold water and drain again.
Mix sugar, vinegar, mustard and celery seed; bring to boil.
Add drained vegetables and bring to boil again.
Pack loosely in jars and seal.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush crackers fine.
Mix crackers, cherries, raisins and pecans.
Melt marshmallows and milk together.
Pour over cracker mixture.
Mix well.
Put in loaf pan or a Bundt pan lined with wax paper.
Chill overnight.

title: how to churn milk and make butter
directions: You will need a churn and churn dash.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in brown paper bag. Moisten potatoes with water.
Drop in bag and shake until well coated.
Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place potatoes in pan. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Turn several times during baking.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain.
Add onion and carrot to squash; add the sour cream.
Melt margarine and mix with 1/2 of corn bread stuffing.
Reserve 1/2 for top.
Place squash mixture in casserole dish.
Put reserved stuffing on top, then the cup of soup on top of stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all together.
If concerned, mix sugar and flour together first to avoid lumps. Pour into 9-inch pie pan and bake until cooked when knife comes out clean. Bake at 325°.

title: vanilla pudding(for pie filling)
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Gradually add to milk in saucepan (thick pan works best).
Cook over medium heat until starts to thicken.
Take 1 cup of mixture and mix egg yolks into it (slowly to keep eggs from cooking).
Pour back into pan.
Continue cooking until thickens like pudding.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla.

title: chicken continental
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll chicken in flour; brown in butter. Heat soup, onion and celery with water in saucepan.
Put rice in 2-quart casserole.
Stir in 2/3 cup soup mixture.
Top with chicken.
Pour remaining soup mixture over.
Add salt.
Cover and bake 30 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: crispy italian chicken
directions: Brown meat both sides (no salt and pepper).
Cook in pressure cooker 10 minutes.
Remove meat from water it was cooked in.
Make gravy in same drippings with flour, evaporated milk, salt and pepper.

title: holiday pinwheels
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; spread on tortillas.
Drain vegetables and blot dry on paper towels.
Sprinkle equal amounts of remaining ingredients on top of cream cheese.
Roll tortillas tightly to form logs.
Wrap in plastic or foil.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Cut tortilla logs into 1-inch pieces, discarding ends. Serve with spirals facing up.
Makes about 3 dozen.
(I have made with 1/2 of the ingredients; i.e., 1 package cream cheese and 1/2 package Ranch dressing.)

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Cream together sugar, peanut butter and vanilla.
Add milk and mix well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture and beat well.
Place in a greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Allow to cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan.
This is a very moist loaf with a rich peanut taste.

title: mom's chestnut stuffing(enough for a 14 to 16 pound turkey - 11 cups)
directions: In a large pan, melt butter.
Cook celery, onion and seasonings (about 10 minutes).
Mix with bread crumbs and chestnuts.
Stuff in turkey.

title: special salad
directions: Dressing:
In blender, puree onions.
Add whole egg and blend 2 minutes more.
Switching blender on and off, add oil in steady stream until mixture thickens.
On medium speed, blend in vinegar. Add garlic and pepper.
Blend 10 seconds more.
Chill.

title: crab au gratin
directions: Toast one side only of white bread slices, butter the untoasted sides and spread with crabmeat.
Sprinkle crabmeat thickly with grated cheese and broil until cheese is melted.
A moment before removing from broiler; pour on sherry.
Serve at once.

title: chicken italiano
directions: Combine margarine and oil.
Brush chicken pieces with mixture. Combine remaining ingredients.
Roll chicken in crumb mixture. Arrange in a 13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add pineapple. Stir in bread cubes.
Bake in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: creamy pasta primavera
directions: Saute vegetables in 1/4 cup oleo.
Add cream cheese and milk. Stir over low heat until cream cheese is melted.
Stir in ham and Parmesan cheese.
Toss spaghetti with remaining oleo.
Add cream cheese mix; mix lightly.
Serve immediately.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together until completely blended.
Keep chilled until ready to serve; best served with a sweet cracker. Can also be in a baked pie shell and served as a pie.

title: doughnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar in lukewarm water.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour and beat well.
Cover and let rise in warm place, free from draft, about 1 hour until bubbles burst on top.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add to yeast mixture.
Add remaining flour to make moderately soft dough.
Knead lightly, then place in well-greased bowl; cover and let rise 1 1/2 hours.
When light, turn out on floured board and roll 3/4-inch thick.
Cut with doughnut cutter.
Place on floured board; cover with cloth and let rise for 1 hour.
Fry in deep fat hot enough to brown a 1-inch cube of bread in 60 seconds or 375°.
Fry on both sides, turning only once.
Drain, cool and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place thawed broccoli in bottom of casserole.
Break chicken up over broccoli.
Add celery soup.
Moisten bread crumbs and sprinkle over mixture.
Pour chicken soup over mixture.
Top with cheese and bake 1 hour at 300° to 350°.

title: jewish hash
directions: Slice 1 onion in bottom of crock-pot.
Add meat, lemon pepper season and cloves.
Slice other onion on top of meat.
Add vinegar and water; cook on low for 12 hours.
After 12 hours, drain meat (most of liquid off) and add brown sugar and barbecue sauce.
Cook for 6 more hours on low.

title: tropical ambrosia
directions: Combine all ingredients except coconut in a medium bowl; mix well.
Spoon into dessert dishes; sprinkle with coconut.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat all ingredients until creamy (except eggs).
Add eggs last and beat.
Pour into graham cracker crust and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: oatmeal fruit muffins
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 20 minutes.

title: vanilla rice pudding
directions: Gradually stir milk and egg into pudding mix in saucepan. Add rice and raisins and sugar.
Stir and cook over medium heat until mixture comes to boil.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.

title: dilly bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water; stir to dissolve.
Heat cottage
cheese
until
lukewarm.
Combine in mixing bowl with sugar, onion,
butter,
dill
seed, salt, baking soda, egg and yeast.
Add flour
a
little at a time to make a stiff batter, beating well
after
each
addition.
Cover and let rise until doubled (50
to 60 minutes).
Stir down, turn into greased pan or 8-inch casserole
dish.
Cover
and
let rise 30 to 40 minutes. Bake in
oven
40 to 50 minutes.
Cover with foil last 15 minutes to prevent excessive browning.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and roll into small balls.
Mix the granulated sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over the "balls" of dough.
Roll the balls in the sugar/cinnamon mix.
Bake at 275° for 30 minutes.

title: greek salad(salata)
directions: Toss lightly.
Garnish with Feta cheese and olives.

title: fruit special
directions: Mix the pie filling, strawberries and their juice, oranges and pineapple chunks.
Chill.
Add bananas just before serving.

title: jiffy porcupines
directions: Combine
ground
beef,
rice, onion, salt and pepper in bowl; mix
well.
Shape
into
1-inch balls.
Brown meatballs lightly on all
sides
in
hot oil in 10-inch skillet; drain. Add mixture of tomato sauce and water.
Simmer, covered,for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yields 4 servings.

title: french toast with bananas and walnuts
directions: In a large shallow bowl, using a fork, beat the eggs until lightly frothy. Stir in the milk and set aside. Peel the bananas and cut in small pieces. Put in small bowl and mash them with a fork. Stir in the walnuts and the nutmeg. Spread the banana mixture over 4 slices of bread, leaving a 1/4 inch border uncovered on all edges. Top with the remaining bread slices and press down gently to seal.

Place 2 sandwiches in egg mixture and press down gently. Turn over and let soak for a moment until evenly saturated on both sides. Repeat with the other 2 remaining sandwiches. Melt 2 Tbsp. butter in a frying pan or griddle over medium heat. Place the sandwiches on griddle and fry until the undersides are gold brown, about 2 minutes. Add the remaining butter, flip the sandwiches with a spatula and fry until golden brown. To serve, place the toast on plates and dust with confectioners sugar. Serve with maple syrup or jam.

title: cheesy chicken & broccoli macaroni
directions: Spray large skillet with no stick cooking spray.
Add chicken; cook and stir 2 minute or until no longer pink.
Stir in broth.
Bring to boil.
Stir in macaroni.
Reduce heat to medium-low; cover.
Simmer 8-10 minute or until macaroni is tender.
Add Velveeta and broccoli; stir until cheese is melted. Yield:
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Remove chicken.
Add soup and sour cream to broth.
Bring to boil.
Cut tortillas into strips.
Add to broth mixture.
Cook until tender.
Add chicken, salt and pepper.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Combine soy sauce, sherry, cornstarch, garlic and 1/4 cup water; set aside.

title: sausage and cheese rolls
directions: Pat out biscuits until flat.
Roll out balls of sausage. Place sausage on flattened biscuits.
Sprinkle with cheese, then roll them up.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pear cobbler
directions: Pour can of fruit and juice in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Add sugar (if fruit is sweetened, omit sugar).
Mix spices and spread over fruit.
Spread 1/2 box of dry cake mix over fruit.
Dot 1 stick of margarine over cake mix.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: chicken and seashell casserole
directions: Can prepare the evening before or in the morning to be served that night.
Mix all ingredients, put into casserole dish.
Store in refrigerator for a day.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in an uncovered casserole dish.

title: ann's toffee bars
directions: Line sheet cake pan with tinfoil.
Put graham crackers in pan (separate crackers).
Combine sugar, butter and oleo in small pot. Let come to boil for 3 minutes.
Spread over crackers.
Sprinkle chopped or ground nuts over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine soup, turkey and vegetables in 9-inch pie plate.
Stir together remaining ingredients.
Pour over turkey mixture.
Bake about 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: rainbow punch
directions: Make scoops of sherbet and place on a foil-lined baking sheet. Freeze 2 hours or until firm.
When ready to serve, pour ginger ale into a punch bowl and top with scoops of sherbet. Serve with straws and spoons.
Makes about 20 (4 ounce) servings.

title: strawberry frosted soda
directions: Place boiling water and gelatin in blender container; cover and blend until gelatin is dissolved.
Pour 1/2 cup of the gelatin mixture into a measuring cup; set aside.
Add half of the milk to remaining gelatin mixture in blender container; blend on low speed until well mixed.
Add half the ice cream; cover and blend just until smooth.
Pour into tall glasses.
Repeat with reserved gelatin mixture, milk and ice cream.
Garnish each glass with a fresh strawberry, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spice tea
directions: Combine ingredients and heat until sugar dissolves.
(Bring to boiling point.)
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
May store in refrigerator for 2 months.
To make 1 gallon, multiply ingredients by 4.

title: apple yogurt sauce(low-fat topping for pancakes and waffles)
directions: Mix together.
Allow to sit for several hours for flavor to develop.
Great on French toast.
Has less than 1 g fat.

title: grandmother's coconut pie
directions: Mix together and put in pie crust.
Sprinkle on more coconut. Cook at 350° until brown.

title: egg pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Cook about 45 minutes until firm in a 350° oven.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: rhubarb preserves
directions: Cook rhubarb and sugar.
Keep stirring as it tends to burn easily.
Cook about 15 minutes or until it starts to thicken. Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
This may be frozen or refrigerated.
Very good on your morning toast.

title: the best baked chicken
directions: Line baking pan with chipped beef.
Wrap skinless, boneless chicken breasts with strips of bacon.
Place on beef.
Mix one pint sour cream and one can mushroom soup.
Pour over chicken and bake at 275° for 3 hours.
Cover with foil for first two hours of baking, then remove foil to brown.

title: layered salad
directions: In a shallow casserole dish (13 x 9-inch) layer:
zucchini and tomatoes.
Cover these with thinly sliced white onion rings. Sprinkle over vegetables:
brown sugar, basil, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover all with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and bake another 45 minutes.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Makes at least 2 loaves of bread.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix both puddings and jello with water in saucepan.
Heat to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Cool and add the oranges, pineapple and Cool Whip.
You may also add marshmallows if you wish.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Combine sugar, water, spices and food coloring; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add butter.
Sift together dry ingredients; cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk all at once and stir just until flour is moistened.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Saute oleo, onion and bell pepper.
Mix with other ingredients (peas last).
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake until bubbly in 350° oven.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix for 5 minutes with electric mixer.
Pour into greased tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: pizza-forkable
directions: To baking mix, add buttermilk and mix.
Roll out in cookie pan or pizza pan.
Layer sauce, veggies (green peppers, onion, mushrooms and olives).
Add tomato chunks and then cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: spring sass downside-up cake
directions: Grease (8 x 12-inch) baking dish.
Arrange rhubarb, marshmallows and 3/4 cup sugar in bottom of dish.
Cream butter with 1 cup sugar; add eggs.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Pour over the rhubarb mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cool 5 minutes.
Turn onto platter.
May be served with whipped or plain cream.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream lard and sugar together.
Add eggs, 1/4 cup water and flavor.
Add the dry ingredients and stir.
If too soft, add a little more flour.
Bake at 450°.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix jello, cold water and hot water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in refrigerator to jell.

title: squash casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients together with 1 cup of the corn bread stuffing. Put in a casserole dish and bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Cut up 1/2 stick margarine into remaining stuffing.
Sprinkle on top of casserole and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: big cookie
directions: Beat sugar and shortening.
Add egg, water and vanilla.
Beat. Add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix and add peanut butter chips. Spread on greased pizza pan to 1/2-inch from edge.
Bake 7 minutes at 350°.
Arrange marshmallows, nuts and chocolate chips on top. Bake until marshmallows are lightly browned.
When cool, drizzle with mixture of 1/2 cup chocolate chips, melted with a little shortening.

title: trudy's lime pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers, taking out seeds.
Cube and mix with lime in 2 gallons of water.
Soak cucumbers for 24 hours.
Rinse well. Cover with clear water and soak for 3 hours.
Drain and cover with boiling water.
Drain and mix vinegar, sugar, salt, celery seed, pickling spice and food coloring.
Add cucumbers and boil for 35 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: cracker brittle
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan with foil.
Arrange crackers over the bottom of the prepared pan. Combine butter or margarine and sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil 2 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat.
Pour and spread evenly over the crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely before cutting or breaking crackers into pieces.

title: texas chili
directions: In a large Dutch oven (cast-iron is best) on medium-high heat, brown steak in oil quickly on both sides until well browned. Remove steak, turn stove to medium.
Add onions, green pepper and garlic.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add browned steak to onions and peppers. Add all spices.
Stir over medium heat for 1 minute.
Turn heat down to a simmer.
Cover and simmer 4 hours.
After done, top each bowl of chili with shredded Monterey Jack cheese.

title: beef jerky
directions: This recipe is for 1 pound of venison or steak.
Preferably I use steak.
Marinate meat for 4 or 5 hours; drain in colander. Place on trays to dry in dehydrator (do not overlap meat).
Dry at 145° for 8 or 10 hours.
It will bend like a green willow without breaking.
Refrigerate when done.

title: marshmallow cream fudge
directions: Combine milk, butter, sugar and salt in heavy saucepan. Bring to full boil over medium heat.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove
from
heat,
add
chocolate
and vanilla. Stir until smooth. Pour
into lightly greased pan (about 8 x 9 inches).
Cook until firm.	Cut into squares.

title: strawberry-lime punch
directions: Place juices and sugar in pitcher. Mix well until sugar is dissolved. Add strawberries. Mix well until combined. Slowly add lemon-lime soda. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: glazed bananas
directions: Combine orange juice, brown sugar and lemon juice in a large skillet; cook over medium heat 1 minute or until sugar melts, stirring constantly.
Add halved bananas and cook 1 minute. Carefully turn bananas and cook an additional minute.
Transfer to individual serving plates.
Serve warm.

title: hot salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: mango limeade
directions: In large pitcher or 2-quart measuring cup, stir together sugar, lime juice and mango nectar until sugar is dissolved.

title: oven chicken
directions: Coat pan with cooking spray oil.
Mix flour and seasonings. Coat chicken. Drizzle with Butter Buds.
Bake in oven, uncovered, at 425° for 30 minutes. Cover and bake 30 minutes more.

title: lady baltimore cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients 4 times.
Add sugar, eggs, butter and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes or until done when tested.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook ingredients until forms a medium ball or hangs on spoon. Pour over cooked popcorn and shape into balls.
Butter hands to prevent sticking.

title: sour cream blueberry lemon pancakes
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; mix well.
In medium bowl, beat together milk, sour cream, egg substitute and vanilla.
Pour milk mixture over dry ingredients and mix until batter is smooth; stir in margarine.
Gently fold in blueberries and lemon zest.
Butter nonstick skillet and set over medium heat; when hot, ladle 1/2 cup batter into pan to make 6-inch pancake.
Repeat this process until all of batter has been used.

title: chocolate freezer dessert
directions: You will need an 8-inch square pan.

title: fondant
directions: Combine sugar, cream of tartar and water in thick saucepan. Place over heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Wipe crystals from side of pan as necessary.
Boil, without stirring, to 240° or soft ball stage.
Pour onto lightly buttered platter. Cool to 110° or lukewarm, turning edges toward center as necessary to prevent hardening.
Pour extract in center of candy.
With fondant spatula, fold candy toward center; repeat movement until candy becomes opaque.
Work in hands until smooth and shiny. Store in airtight container at least 24 hours.
Divide and work food coloring into fondant as desired.
Form into candies or bonbons; place on waxed paper to set.
Store in semi-airtight container.
Yield:
80 undipped centers or 1 1/4 pounds.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken into pieces.
Place broccoli in bottom of baking dish.
Put chicken over broccoli.
Spread soup over chicken.
Top with Cheddar cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Melt oleo and cream with sugar. Add beaten egg and dissolved yeast.
Add flour and stir until mixed.
Let rise a few minutes.
Place by spoonfuls in greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Batter may be stored in refrigerator in tight covered bowl 2 or 3 days.

title: glorified rice
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Refrigerate until thickened. Combine pineapple, marshmallows and rice.
Cut cherries in small pieces.
Whip cream.
Chill other ingredients while gelatin is chilling.
When gelatin is partially set, add pineapple mixture and part of cherries.
Fold in whipped cream and place in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cherry bits.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
Serves 12.

title: barbecued pecans(great gift!)
directions: Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Heat oven to 300°. Dissolve sugar in vinegar.
Coat all pecans in this mixture until it is all soaked up.
Spread pecans out evenly in one layer on cookie sheet. Bake for 20 minutes. Take out and stir around, then bake 10 minutes more.
Melt butter and mix with seasoned salt. Drizzle over pecans. Bake 5 minutes more or until dry.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Bring sugar and sour cream to a boil over medium heat.
Cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Add nuts; toss until coated.
Dry on waxed paper.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Combine all ingredients in large skillet.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until tender, about 10 to 12 servings.
Can add (German) sausage, cut in about 3 or 4-inch pieces and fried with 4-inch chunks of Italian sausage.

title: fay's good egg custard
directions: In a nonstick boiler, melt butter.
Add milk, sugar and eggs (beaten well), stirring constantly to keep from sticking.
Add pinch of salt.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Sprinkle nutmeg over the top of the pie and cook at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken salad(serves 100)
directions: Prepare in order given; can mix everything but eggs and mayonnaise the day before.
Add eggs and mayonnaise the morning it is to be served.

title: snack stuff
directions: Melt bark and stir other ingredients in.
Spread on wax paper and cool.
Break into chunks and serve.

title: jumbo shells with cheese filling
directions: Cook jumbo shells for 9 minutes; drain.
Rinse with cold water, drain and arrange in single layer to fill.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix together all ingredients and boil for 5 minutes.
Add a pint of home-canned beets or a can of beets to the sauce.
Let stand for 1/2 hour or more.
Reheat before serving.

title: bonbons
directions: Combine all ingredients except chocolate chips and paraffin. Roll into balls and chill.
(Can use whole nuts or drained maraschino cherries instead of chopped nuts.)

title: banana ice cream
directions: Mash bananas, sugar and juice.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Add evaporated milk and homogenized milk; stir well.
Freeze in ice tray.
Stir often while freezing.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Wash and dry mushrooms.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sugar drop cookies
directions: Blend dry ingredients.
Combine sugar and oil; add eggs and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls. Dip the balls in sugar.
Flatten balls with the bottom of a glass. To give a corrugated look, score them with a fork.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes on a lightly greased cookie sheet.

title: shrimp noodle bake
directions: Cut shrimp lengthwise.
Combine noodles, sour cream, soup, onions, olives, dill weed, seasoned salt and half of the cheese; mix well.
Fold in shrimp.

title: brenda's favorite rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in milk, sugar, salt, egg, butter and 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough of the remaining flour so dough is easy to handle.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface; knead 5 minutes, until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl; turn over.
Cover; let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours in a warm place.
Punch down; shape into rolls.
Place in greased pans. Let rise 20 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes, until nicely browned.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Broil broccoli until tender; drain.
Brown beef, onion and celery.
Layer ingredients in a buttered casserole dish.
Cover with cheese.
Cover and bake at 350°
for 40 minutes.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Bring to a boil on medium heat. Boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Set it off the burner and add 2 teaspoons vanilla and 2 teaspoons water and boil for 1 minute.

title: crawfish and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute green onions and bell pepper in skillet, using butter. Combine all ingredients in a 4-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: super sweet pickle sticks
directions: Cut cucumbers in strips lengthwise.
Put boiling water over cucumbers and let set overnight.
Pack in clean glass jars next day.
Combine all other ingredients and boil 5 minutes.
Pour over the cucumbers which were packed in the jars.
Seal at once.
May process in water bath for 5 minutes.
If they seal without water bath, they are better.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Place chicken in a shallow baking dish.
Mix lemon juice, soy sauce and sugar; pour over chicken, coating each piece.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients evenly over chicken.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour; uncover and bake 1/2 hour more,
basting twice. Serves 4 to 5.

title: orange whole wheat pancakes
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Mix together last 3 dry ingredients.
Add liquids to dry ingredients.
Stir just enough to mix.
Cook on griddle.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Saute or steam onion and pepper until tender.
Add onion and pepper to the tomatoes and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add 1 cups of nuts.
Chill and form into ball.
Roll in remaining cup of chopped pecans.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix margarine, shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs.
Blend dry ingredients.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls. Mix 2 tablespoons sugar and the cinnamon.
Roll balls into sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased sheets. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from sheets immediately.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together thoroughly the first 5 ingredients.
Sift together and stir in the remaining ingredients.
Chill dough. Roll into balls size of large walnuts.
Place 3 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in flour, crisscross.
Bake until set, but not hard at 375° (quick moderate oven).
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.
Spread melted peanut butter chips on top for frosting.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in cranberry sauce and undrained pineapple until sauce melts.
Chill until partially set.

title: salmon ball
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; stir well.
Chill thoroughly. Shape into a ball and roll in parsley.
Serve with assorted crackers.
To freeze, place salmon ball in an airtight container in freezer.
To serve, remove from freezer and let thaw completely.
Yields one (6-inch) ball.

title: chicken chop suey
directions: Boil chicken.
Remove from bone.
Return chicken to broth; add bean sprouts and water chestnuts (drained).
Add drained mushrooms; simmer.
Add celery,
onions and soy sauce; simmer until celery and onions are done.
Thicken cornstarch and water by cooking.
Add to mixture and salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Cook and thoroughly drain broccoli.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 425° until done.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Roll into small balls. Dip in melted chocolate to cover. Yum yum good.

title: silly putty for two
directions: Mix.
Lift globby glue out of starch and knead until it thickens (about 5 minutes).
Stretch and pull it.
Store airtight.

title: witch's brew
directions: Boil cloves in water until it turns a tea color.
Strain cloves and add all other ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: beef cream cheese ball
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, 2 jars chopped dried beef, green onion, Accent and Worcestershire sauce. Form mixture into 2 balls. Roll balls in remaining jar of chopped beef. Serve with Triscuits or other crackers.

title: quail or dove in casserole
directions: Clean quail thoroughly.
Rub inside and out with butter or margarine, salt and pepper.
Truss quail and place on spit. Roast under low gas flame 20 to 25 minutes.
Allow 2 quail per serving.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix milk, vanilla, almond extract and lemon juice. Stir until thick. Fold in Cool Whip. Put in pastry shell; chill.
Top with your favorite topping.

title: fluffy cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together using a spoon or wire whip. Chill for 8 to 10 hours before serving.

title: sour cream banana bread
directions: Beat together sugar and oil.
Add eggs, mashed bananas, sour cream and vanilla.
Blend well.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Fry hamburger;	drain.	Add rice and onion.
Cook until rice is tender.	Place
cabbage	in
bottom of casserole dish. Put hamburger on top.
Mix soup with water and pour over meat. Cook 1 hour at
Place
cheese
on
top
and put in oven until melted, just a few seconds.
Serves 6.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix all together and bake in an 8 or 9-inch square pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Rub in soft shortening. Mix beaten egg and milk; stir into dry ingredients.
Drop into hot broth by tablespoon.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes.

title: rhubarb and strawberry tart
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Into medium bowl, measure flour, sugar and salt.
With pastry blender or 2 knives, used scissor fashion, cut shortening into flour mixture until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Add water, 1 tablespoon at a time, until pastry just holds together.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake 10 minutes in preheated 450° oven.
Then reduce heat to 350° and bake another 30 minutes or until custard is set.

title: tuna timbales
directions: Lightly brown tuna
and
onion	in
salad oil.	Add egg yolks, bread, lemon
juice
and seasoning.
Fold in egg whites and turn into greased
custard cups.
Bake in pan of hot water at 350° until firm.
Unmold and serve with white sauce.

title: appetizer meatballs
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients with 1/3 cup Manwich; mix well. Form mixture into 1-inch balls; arrange in baking pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes; drain excess fat.
Pour remaining Manwich mix and water over meatballs.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Makes 30 to 35 meatballs.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple syrup and stir to dissolve.
Chill in oiled pan or individual molds until firm.
Serve on lettuce.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix the ingredients and place in a baking dish. Cook in preheated
oven at 375° for 1 hour. Serves 8 to 10.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; cut in oleo and oil.
Combine eggs, sour milk, vanilla and zucchini; add to flour and oleo mixture.
Mix well.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: stuffed green peppers(method:  foil packet)
directions: Remove seeds from green peppers; set aside.
Finely chop onion; set aside.
Mix together the hamburger, bread crumbs, onion and egg.
Stuff mixture into green peppers.
Place stuffed green peppers on shiny side of individual pieces of foil; top with 1/4 cup of tomato sauce.
Wrap, using drugstore wrap method.
Place on coals; cook for 12 to 15 minutes on each side.

title: cinnamon nut buns(this recipe came from a 1936 ashville times newspaper)
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening with a knife.
Stir in milk and work lightly into a dough.
Roll out on a floured board into a sheet 6 x 8-inches.
Spread with softened butter; sprinkle with brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts. Roll up like a jelly roll and slice crosswise.
Place in a well-greased pan.
Bake in a hot (400°) oven for 12 minutes or until browned.

title: caramel-pecan pie
directions: Place 1 cup pecans in bottom of pastry shell; drizzle with 1/4 cup caramel topping.
Set aside.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Pour mixture over pecans.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool completely, and chill.
Garnish with pecan halves and drizzle with additional caramel topping, if desired.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease well and flour 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: swiss steak with tomato sauce
directions: Season the steaks on both sides with salt and pepper.
Dredge the steaks in flour; shake off excess.
Using 2 tablespoons of butter, brown the steaks on both sides in a skillet.
Remove the steaks and set aside.
Melt remaining butter; add garlic, onion and sweet pepper and cook, stirring frequently, until the onions are translucent, about 5 minutes.
Return the steaks to the pan, overlapping them slightly.
Add the tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce and bouillon.
Bring to a simmer and cook, covered for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until tender.
Skim any excess fat from the surface, then stir in the cornstarch and water mixture.
Bring to a simmer and allow to thicken.

title: graham cracker quickies
directions: Line buttered cookie sheet with whole graham crackers.	Boil sugar and butter 2 minutes or until blended.
Pour over crackers. Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake in 375° oven for 8 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.
(Don't overbake, they are best a bit chewy.)

title: rice with pine nuts
directions: Heat the olive oil in a medium saucepan.
Add the rice and saute gently for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Be sure not to brown the rice.
Add the water, salt and pepper; bring to a rapid boil.
Cook for about 7 minutes on medium-high heat until the water gets below the surface of the rice.
Reduce the heat to the lowest point, cover the saucepan tightly and cook for 25 minutes, until all the water is absorbed into the rice.
Fluff the rice with a fork, sprinkle all the pine nuts on top and serve.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Starting with cookies, layer pudding and Cool Whip in a clear glass bowl. Repeat layers ending with Cool Whip.
Chill for at least 1 hour.

title: pasta e fagioli
directions: You can use any kind of pasta you have at home (i.e., elbow macaroni, spaghetti, broken into little pieces or linguine same instructions, break up).
I use a handful per person.

title: never fail fudge icing
directions: Mix and bring to a boil. Boil 1 minute (rolling). Cool.
Beat until thick.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash avocado with fork, potato masher or in food processor. Add all other ingredients and chill.
Leave the avocado pit in the guacamole to prevent browning.
Check the seasoning before serving.
This recipe is for 1 avocado.
If you use more simply increase all other ingredients to taste.

title: pecan crusted squash
directions: Combine and drizzle over squash.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.

title: braided bread-russia(kolach)
directions: Dissolve 1 tsp. sugar in the water and sprinkle the yeast over it. Add 1 Tbsp. of sugar, stir and let stand for 10 minutes. Combine the yeast with the milk, lightly beaten eggs, salt 2 Tbsp. of sugar, oil, and 2 cups of sifted flour. Beat until smooth. Cover and let rise in a warm place until light and bubbly, about 1 hour. Mix in enough flour to make a light but slightly sticky dough, then knead in bowl until smooth and elastic. Now form dough into a bowl and very lightly oil dough enough to cover the whole dough ball. Cover bowl of dough with a warm damp dish towel, lightly damp only. Let rise in warm place until it doubles in size. Punch down and allow dough to rise again slightly.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Place all ingredients in large pot.
Bring to a boil; lower heat and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: flat enchiladas
directions: Heat oil in a frying pan to a depth of about 1/2-inch.
Have enchilada sauce heated in a large saucepan.
Dip tortillas one at a time into hot oil for about 15 seconds and turn over for another 15 seconds to soften.
Dip tortillas in enchilada sauce and stack on plates (3 to 4 per plate) with onion and cheese sprinkled between each layer and on top.
Fry the eggs and put on top of each stack. (Keep plates of enchiladas hot in oven while cooking eggs.)
Pour any leftover sauce over enchiladas and top with lettuce and tomatoes.
Serves 4.

title: ginger cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cream the butter for 2 minutes.
Add honey and molasses.
Cream mixture for 2 minutes longer.
Beat in eggs, one by one.
Mix together flour, baking powder, baking soda, ginger, cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg until well combined.
Stir mixture units the batter alternately with the boiling water.
Stir until smooth.

title: viennese torte
directions: In saucepan (or microwave) heat chocolate, butter and water; stir until blended.
Cool slightly.
Add egg yolks, sugar and vanilla; stir until smooth.
Chill until mixture is spreading consistency (about 45 minutes).
Slice cake horizontally into 6 layers.
Spread chocolate between layers, then on top and sides. Chill at least 45 minutes before serving.
Cut into thin slices. Very rich!

title: yeast doughnuts
directions: Lukewarm milk.
Put in shortening, salt and sugar.
Let cool. Dissolve yeast in small amount of lukewarm milk.
Add beaten eggs to first ingredients. Stir in flour, slowly, to make thick dough. Let rise in large bowl until doubled in bulk.
Turn out on floured board.
Knead well.

title: scalloped potatoes and linguica
directions: Peel and slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick.
Mix potatoes, soup, onion, pepper and salt in a casserole dish (9 x 12-inch).
Slice linguica and put on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are soft.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces, skin side up, in a microsafe baking dish.
Arrange thicker pieces towards edges of dish.
Pour melted butter over chicken.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and ginger; top with celery.
Cover dish with waxed paper.
Microwave at High power for about 16 minutes, turning dish once if the oven is not a rotating one.
Rearrange chicken pieces.
Mix pineapple juice with brown sugar, water, soy sauce, vinegar and cornstarch in a microsafe measuring cup.
Microwave at High power for 3 minutes, until mixture thickens, stirring once.
Pour mixture over chicken. Add pineapple chunks and red pepper.
Cover with waxed paper; microwave at High power for another 6 to 8 minutes, until chicken is tender and juices run clear when chicken is pierced with a fork.

title: garlic spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and margarine, mixing until well blended. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.
Makes approximately 1 2/3 cups of spread.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium mixing bowl, beat egg yolks. Stir in Eagle Brand, ReaLime and food coloring, if desired.
Pour into pie shell.
In small mixer bowl, beat egg whites with cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff, but not dry.
Spread on top of pie, sealing carefully to edge of shell.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Cool completely.
Chill thoroughly.

title: layered hamburger bake
directions: Cook the noodles in water until tender and drain well.
Brown and drain the meat.
Add the tomato sauce, sugar, salt, garlic salt and pepper. Add the cooked noodles and stir until blended. Set aside.

title: amish oatmeal cookies
directions: Grind raisins
and
peanuts
through food grinder using medium blade,
set mixture aside.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg
and
cinnamon
into
very
large bowl or dishpan. Cut in lard into the mixture using pastry blender or two knives until it forms fine crumbs.
Add ground raisins and peanuts, sugar and
quick
cooking
oats, mix well.
Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk.
Add
molasses
and 3 of the eggs. Beat with rotary beater until blended.
Add the flour mixture and mix well.
Drop by
heaping tablespoonfuls about 3 inches apart.
Flatten each with floured bottom of drinking glass to 2 1/2 inch
round.
Beat with rotary beater one egg until well blended.
Brush tops
of rounds with egg batter.
Bake at 375° for 8 to
minutes
or until golden brown.
Makes about 54 cookies.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground chuck; drain off all liquid, then add water and the rest of the ingredients.
Cook on low for 1 hour.

title: special occasion punch
directions: Mix sugar and water; simmer for 5 minutes.
Chill.
Chill juices and 7-Up.
Mix sugar and juices in bowl.
At serving time, pour in 7-Up.
Add ice cubes; garnish with mint leaves.
Makes 7 quarts or about 60 punch cups.

title: cranberry-orange holiday relish
directions: Mix Jell-O and water as directed on package.
Cool.
Grind and combine oranges, apples, cranberries and pecans.
Add sugar to mixture.
Stir and let stand for 10 minutes.
Add Jell-O; mix well and refrigerate.

title: corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease square pan (8 x 8 x 2 inches or 9 x 9 x 2 inches).
Blend all ingredients for about 20 seconds.
Beat vigorously for 1 minute.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: easy apple dish
directions: Arrange apple slices in 8 x 1 1/2-inch round pan, lightly greased with butter.
Mix oats, sugar, flour and cinnamon. Sprinkle this mixture over the apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm topped with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in egg and cream, using wire whisk.
Set aside.
Boil noodles; drain and return to pot.
Pour cream mixture over noodles; toss lightly, adding cheese and pepper.
Reserve some cheese to serve at the table.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Grease and flour 3 layer cake pans.
Combine Wesson oil, eggs and vanilla and beat.
Add sugar.
Sift and measure flour, soda and salt, mixing well.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: shepard's loaf
directions: Cut out top of loaf for the lid.
Hollow out bread completely and save large pieces for dipping.
Mix all remaining ingredients including the bread pieces and put in loaf.
Replace top and wrap in foil.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix ingredients, then stir in blueberries (blueberries should be washed and drained).
Pour into greased muffin tin.
Cook until golden brown.
Makes 12.

title: country ham balls
directions: Mix together.
Add enough milk to roll into small balls; set aside.

title: terrific tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
With an electric mixer, cream together the butter and the granulated sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating briefly after each addition.
Add extracts and flour.
Beat until smooth.
Grease a jelly roll pan and pour mixture into pan. With the blade of a table knife, mark off 20 squares.
Put one tablespoon of pie filling in the middle of each square.
Bake at 350° for 27 minutes.
Let cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Put a small amount of powdered sugar into a strainer and sprinkle a light dusting of the sugar onto the tarts.
Cut into marked squares.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 3/4 cup Pepperidge Farm dressing mix. Place in a deep casserole dish. Sprinkle top with remaining 3/4 cup dressing mix. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: In a large skillet brown meat and remove from skillet with slotted spoon.
Pour off fat, reserving 1 teaspoon in skillet. Add onion and garlic, saute 3 to 4 minutes, stirring frequently until softened.
Add tomato sauce and paste, along with salt, pepper and oregano.
Mix in the hamburger and simmer mixture for 15 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Place 3 noodles in a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with about a third of each of the following:
sauce, Mozzarella and cottage cheese.
Spread again with sauce, Mozzarella and cottage cheese.
Top this with 3 noodles and complete with remaining third of the sauce and cheeses.
Bake for 30 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.
Serves 8.

title: pina colada pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, milk, rum, 1/2 cup pineapple and coconut in blender for 30 seconds.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust; sprinkle with coconut.
Freeze until firm (4 hours). Garnish with remaining pineapple.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
Store leftover pie in freezer.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Slice and wash onions; set aside.
Crush Ritz crackers.
Set aside.
Melt butter in a skillet and saute onions until they are clear.
Put half the onions in an 11 x 8-inch baking dish. Sprinkle cheese over onions and then half of the Ritz crackers over the cheese.
Repeat these layers.
Pour milk over casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Line pan with whole or half graham crackers.
Mix pudding and milk.
Add Cool Whip; spread half over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers.
Add rest of pudding.
Put a layer of crackers on top.
Cover with chocolate icing.

title: baked corn
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Melt
the
butter and oleo in large skillet
and
saute
onions
and
peppers until tender. Combine corn (including liquid), eggs, sour cream, cheese and muffin
mix with
the
sauteed onions and peppers.
Pour into (vegetable spray coated) baking dish.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° preheated oven.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: In small heavy saucepan, heat butter. Add bacon and cook 5 minutes or until bacon is golden brown. Remove bacon and set aside. Add onions to pan and cook for 5 minutes. Remove onions and set aside.

title: fruit cake
directions: Chop pecans with any fruits that need to be chopped.
Mix with the Eagle Brand milk and bake in a 275° oven for about 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Let cool before removing from pan.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl and stir until blended well.
Spray two 9-inch pie pans with no-stick cooking spray (Pam).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all together in layers.
Cover and cook for
1 hour in 325° oven.
Uncover and cook 15 minutes.

title: homemade spray and wash
directions: Pour ingredients into spray bottle and mix.
Never mix ammonia with bleach containing products which may result in dangerous gas.

title: easiest corn fritters ever
directions: Beat egg yolks slightly.
Stir in pancake mix and corn.
Fold in slightly beaten egg whites.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil. Fry until golden brown.
Drain.
Serve with syrup.
Makes about 40.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook ground beef, onion, garlic and parsley in olive oil until beef is brown.
Add tomato paste, water, salt and pepper.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring often.
Cook lasagne as directed.
Put 1/2-cup or more in large, shallow baking dish, then half of cooked lasagne, meat sauce, Ricotta and eggs (mixed), shredded Mozzarella.
Repeat layers, ending with meat sauce.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: steak with herb-spice rub
directions: Marinate steaks overnight with whatever marinade that you like. Pour off marinade. Mix the 8 ingredients and rub on both sides of steak. Let sit for 20 to 30 minutes, then grill.

title: applesauce loaf
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add other ingredients, mix well.
Fold in nuts.
Turn batter into greased loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 60 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan.
Drizzle with glaze.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in pineapple.
Mix together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir flour mixture into creamed mixture.
Add 1 cup nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Stir in eggs, onions and milk. Mix together until smooth.
Drop from spoon into hot oil.
Fry until lightly golden brown.

title: cake icing
directions: Beat until smooth.
May divide icing into small bowls and add food coloring for desired colors for decorating (best to use Wilton icing coloring).

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the soup with the cheese, milk and sour cream.
Thaw vegetables.
Mix half the onion rings.
Spray dish.
Mix all together in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Top with remaining rings.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Stir.
Bake more.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Cream the cheese and cut dried beef in small slices.
Mix all together except pecans.
Make into ball; roll in pecans.
Chill.

title: cheese and onion pie
directions: Peel and quarter onions.
Boil 45 to 60 minutes.
Drain thoroughly and return to pot.
Pepper lightly.
Add sliced cheese and mix until cheese is melted.
Pour mixture into pie shell. Cover with top.
Flute well and pierce with fork.
Bake until crust is golden brown.
Set stand 5 to 10 minutes before slicing. Excellent main course.
Serve with Caesar salad.

title: barbecue chuck roast
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place meat. Pour 2 tablespoons liquid smoke over roast.
Sprinkle with celery salt and garlic powder. Cover tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: pasta romana
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions (al dente); drain. In large skillet, melt butter; cook ham and mushrooms until tender.
Add light cream (low-fat).
Heat to boiling.
Cook until liquid is reduced to half, about 6 minutes.
Add peas.
Heat thoroughly.
Toss with hot, cooked pasta and Romano cheese.
Makes 4 servings, about 1 1/2 cups each.

title: flaming mangos
directions: Wash and peel mangos. Cut each into 6 slices. Place in skillet or chafing dish. Pour orange juice over the fruit and sprinkle with sugar. Heat to simmering, stirring gently to dissolve sugar and coat fruit. After 3 or 4 minutes, pour in tequila. Keep over medium heat.

title: lizzies
directions: Use
a
little of the
flour to sprinkle over the fruit before mixing
it
into the dough.
Drop the final mixture by teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, and salt; set aside.
Cream together shortening, peanut butter, and both sugars;
add egg and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Stir in sifted ingredients; mix well. Roll into balls and dip in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350 for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from oven, place a Hershey kiss in center of cookie.
Place back in oven for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: pinwheels
directions: Blend cream cheese, onion, horseradish and Worcestershire sauce until smooth and spreadable.
Separate the slices of turkey and ham, laying one slice of turkey on each slice of ham.
Then spread with cheese mixture.
Roll and fasten with toothpicks. Chill.
Just before serving, slice into 1/2-inch slices.
Makes about 50 pinwheels.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in order.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 300°.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix soup, green chiles, salt, onion and chicken.
Spoon in corn tortilla; add cheese.
Roll.
Place on cookie sheet.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Cook meat with Creole seasoning in iron pot until brown; drain.
Brown onions.
Cook celery, bell pepper, parsley, garlic, tomatoes, sauce, paste and Worcestershire for 1 1/2 hours over low heat.
Add meat and onions.
Add chili powder and cayenne pepper. Add water to cover ingredients.
Cook for 30 minutes.
If recipe is not salty enough, add 2 more ounces of Tony's seasoning. Freezes well.

title: applesauce meat balls
directions: In mixing bowl, combine all ingredients, except barbecue sauce; mix thoroughly.
Form into balls.
Put in baking dish and brown in oven.
