Remove from oven; drain off excess grease.
Cover with barbecue sauce.
Bake in a 350° oven until done or put into crock-pot and simmer until ready to eat.

title: chicken and peas
directions: Brown garlic and onion in oil.
Add chicken, tomato, red bell pepper, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Cover chicken and simmer for 10 minutes.
After 10 minutes, add potatoes and pat of butter. Let simmer for another five minutes, adding a little amount of water in case the mixture gets too dry.
Next, add peas.
Let simmer another 10 minutes and it's done.
Serve with white rice.

title: pistachio torte
directions: Mix crackers and margarine together and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes and allow to cool.
Mix the pudding, milk and ice cream thoroughly and pour into the crust.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Top with Cool Whip, chopped nuts and crushed Heath bars.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix 1 package of raspberry Jell-O and 2 cups of hot water; set in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Dissolve Knox gelatine in 1/2 cup of cold water, then add sugar, half and half cream, cream cheese, pecans and vanilla.
Pour this over the raspberry Jell-O.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Spread blueberries evenly in pie crust.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour on top of blueberries.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: daikon salad(servings:  4)
directions: Boil chicken for 20 minutes and cut into long thin strips after cooking.
Pare the radishes and cut into half and then into thin strips.
Sprinkle salt over and drain after a few minutes. Mix seasonings and dress them with radishes and chicken.
Place the lettuce leaves on the plate and in the center of it.
Sprinkle sesame seed over the top.

title: taco casserole
directions: In large skillet, cook ground beef and the onion until beef is browned.
Drain excess fat.
Stir tomato sauce, water and taco seasoning mix into meat mixture; heat through.
Remove from heat.

title: creole pork chops
directions: Season pork chops with salt and pepper.
Brown in oil.
Remove from skillet.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and chops.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until meat is tender.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender. Remove the meat from the bones. To broth,

add milk. Bring to a boil and add the biscuits which have been rolled real thin and cut into bite-sized pieces. Then drop into boiling broth. When finished with dumplings, add chicken, black pepper and salt to taste. Be careful and do not let the dumplings burn while adding the rest of raw dumplings. Put lattice on top of pie and dot with oleo. Bake until brown.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Store in refrigerator 3 days in covered bowl, mixing well each day.
At end of 3 days, shape in 6 rolls, place on broiler rack pan and place in 150° oven.
Bake 4 hours, turn rolls and bake 4 more hours (total 8 hours).
Cool, wrap in foil and store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: mini ham sandwiches
directions: Chop fine the
ham
and
Swiss cheese. Slice rolls down the middle and	open.
Melt margarine. Add minced onion, poppy seed, golden
mustard and Worcestershire sauce. Spread mixture over rolls. Layer
ham
and
cheese.
Put
top
back on rolls. Bake at 350° about 10 minutes. Cut and serve.

title: shelly's chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook chicken with salt, pepper and onion.
Have plenty of water for soup base.
After chicken has cooked, remove meat; add bouillon cubes to liquid.
Add celery and carrots.
Cook vegetables.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except gelatin.
Sprinkle gelatin gradually as you mix ingredients.
Chill for 48 hours.

title: spinach pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken divan
directions: Skin and boil chicken breasts until cooked thoroughly, then debone.
Cut broccoli and boil it until tender-crisp.
Line bottom of shallow baking pan with stalks of broccoli.

title: enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
In a skillet, saute onion in melted butter until tender.
Add ground beef and brown, draining off excess liquid.
Set aside.
In saucepan, heat beans until warm, then combine with beef.
In one tortilla, place 1/4 cup of meat mixture and roll up, placing seam side down in baking dish.
Continue until all tortillas are filled.
Combine next 4 ingredients and heat in saucepan until hot.
Pour over tortillas.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: san antonio wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place wings in baking dish. In a bowl combine picante sauce, catsup, honey and cumin and pour over chicken. Marinate chicken in refrigerator at least 1 hour. Drain chicken; reserve marinade. Place wings in a single layer on cookie sheets and bake for 30 minutes. Brush with reserved marinade. Turn and bake for 15 minutes longer. Heat oven to broil and cook wings for 5 minutes on each side, until golden brown.

title: jambalaya
directions: Add oil to a large Dutch oven. Over medium heat, saut onion, garlic, green pepper and celery until onion is translucent. Add parsley, ham, chicken, bay leaf and cayenne pepper. Cook, stirring often, 5 to 6 minutes. Add tomatoes (with juice), tomato sauce and 1 3/4 cups water. Gently simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes. Add rice and Andouville sausage. Stir well. Bring mixture to a boil. Lower heat and simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes or until rice is cooked and most of the liquid is absorbed. Remove bay leaf. Salt and pepper to taste. Serves 6.

title: garden pizza
directions: Bake crescent rolls flat in jelly roll pan.
Set aside.
Mix cream cheese, mayo, horseradish, dill weed, onion, garlic salt and pepper sauce.
Spread on dough and top with assorted raw chopped vegetables.
Sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese. Cut into squares and serve.

title: spicy raisin rocks
directions: Beat together sugar, shortening, eggs and milk.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and spices.
Stir into creamed mixture. Stir in raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: blue icicle
directions: Chill and serve up in Martini stemmed glass.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oats and hot water and set aside.
Cream sugar and butter until mixed good.
Add eggs, mixing with mixer, then add dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly with mixer, adding oats and water mixture.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: sesame chicken with honey dip
directions: Cut chicken into 1/2 inch strips and poach.
Preheat the oven to 425°, combine 1/2 cup mayonnaise, dry mustard, and onion, mix well.
Add the chicken and toss to coat.
Toss bread crumbs and sesame seeds to mix.
Roll chicken in bread crumb mix to cover. Place on a baking sheet and bake until brown, about 10 minutes. Blend 1 cup of mayonnaise with the honey and dijon mustard dip for sauce.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into small balls and place on baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not over cook!

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix cheese and Bisquick together.
Then add raw sausage.
Make into small balls (about size of quarter).
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Cool and drain on paper towels.

title: hawaiian marshmallow pie
directions: Microwave marshmallows and reserved 1/2 cup pineapple liquid in a large, microwave-safe bowl on High 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until smooth when stirred.
Stir halfway through heating time. Refrigerate 30 minutes or until slightly thickened.

title: quick and easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix rice, soup, mushrooms, sour cream and water in a large casserole dish.
Place chicken strips on top and press into mixture.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: layer salad
directions: Use 13 x 9-inch dish.
Chill 24 hours.
(May add or subtract other things.)

title: bungalow dish
directions: Cook noodles per package instructions.
Brown chopped meat. Add onion, pepper and sugar.
Add tomato sauce.
Simmer; mix with noodles.
Bake in covered casserole 35 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 to 6 servings (recipe can be doubled).

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand overnight to blend flavors.

title: ice cream punch
directions: Let ice cream stand at room temperature for 25 to 30 minutes or until softened.
Combine with 7-Up and ginger ale in punch bowl; mix softly.
Yields 40 servings.

title: date nut cut-ups(cookies)
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, beating well.
Mix together dry ingredients and stir into creamed mixture.
Add dates or raisins and nuts.
Divide into 4 portions. On a greased cookie sheet, spread each portion in 12 x 2 1/2 x 1/2-inch strips (about 3-inches apart).
Bake in 375° oven about 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: marshmallow puffs
directions: In double boiler, melt margarine and add caramels.
Stir regularly while melting.
Add Eagle Brand milk, stir.
Dip marshmallows (using toothpick) in caramel.
Roll in Rice Krispies until coated.
Set on wax paper to cool.
If caramel gets too thick, thin with a little milk.
Keeps well.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut beef across grain into 1/8 inch strips.
Combine soy sauce, garlic, ginger and beef; toss.
Heat oil in large frying pan or wok.
Add beef and toss over high heat until brown.
Taste and if not tender, reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Turn heat up; add veggies.
Toss about 10 minutes, until tender-crisp. Combine cornstarch and water.
Add to pan.
Stir and cook until thickened.
Add tomatoes and toss to heat through.
Serve over rice with chow mein noodles.

title: beth's peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the cheese and add all but Cool Whip.
Fold in half of the Cool Whip.
Place in pie shell. Refrigerate several hours. Top with the other half of the Cool Whip before serving.

title: cucumber salmon spread
directions: Mix salmon, cucumber, green onion, lemon juice and cayenne. Stir in mayonnaise and yogurt, mixing until well blended. Serve sandwich or cocktail-style on rye bread. Cover and refrigerate remaining spread.

title: no-sugar cookies(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl with wooden spoon, stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Drop dough by tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake about 20 minutes until lightly browned.
Stir in tightly covered container. Contains 80 calories per cookie.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen light, cake-like cookies.

title: taco dip
directions: Add taco seasoning mix to cream cheese, add sour cream to aid spreadability.
Use the mixture to cover the bottom of a serving plate.
Cover with tomatoes, lettuce, olives and cheese.
Just before serving, top with a drizzle of salsa and a dollop of sour cream.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together, pour into pan and bake until tests with nothing on test item.

title: holiday cookies
directions: Mix well shortening, sugar and egg.
Add buttermilk.
Sift and stir in dry ingredients.
Add nuts, dates and cherries.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on a slightly greased cookie sheet.
Top with cherry or nut.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: english trifle
directions: Bake cake mix with 1 package pudding or get cake mix with pudding already in it.
Mix pudding mix together.
Cool a large punch bowl.
Add: a layer of pudding, layer of cake (crumbled), layer of strawberries, layer of Cool Whip and a
layer of nuts. Repeat layers.

title: orange delite
directions: Add Jell-O and puddings to boiling water.
Cook for 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
If desired, you can add Cool Whip, mandarin oranges and bananas after cooking.
Pour into mold or pan.
Cool. Set overnight.

title: jezebel
directions: Make paste of dry mustard and horseradish. Mix into remaining ingredients. Adjust taste to your own taste buds; serve over cream cheese with crackers.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs, water, pumpkin, vanilla and fruit.	Mix well with a fork.
After mixed thoroughly, put in stem pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
I always test with a toothpick to see if done.
Pour glaze over cake while it's still hot, after taken from the oven.

title: rowlandin
directions: Take each slice of steak.
Place a strip of bacon.
Add a slice of pickle and carrot; roll up and place toothpicks in to hold together.
Brown.
Add beef gravy (canned).
Simmer about 1/2 hour.

title: chick steaks
directions: Mix meat, potato flour and water.
Make into very thin patties. Salt and pepper meat.
Combine eggs and milk.
Dip patties in egg mixture, then in flour.
Repeat dipping in egg mixture and flour.

title: braised pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in butter.
Transfer to braising pan.
Saute onion and celery in pork chop drippings until tender.
Add wine and bring to a boil.
Pour over chops seasoned with salt and pepper.
Cover.
Braise in 300° oven 1 1/2 hours or until tender. Remove chops from pan.
Strain juices.
Stir mustard and capers into juices.
Pour over chops and simmer a few minutes more. Serves 4.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine Cracker Barrel cheese, softened cream cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Mix well until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Mold into ball.
If desired, sprinkle finely chopped walnuts on top and garnish with cherry.

title: creole burgers
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onions.
Add seasonings.
Pour off grease.
Add soup, catsup, mustard and water.
Simmer until thick, stirring often.
More water may be needed if too thick.
Also, you may add more catsup and mustard.

title: string beans
directions: Cook until beans are tender.

title: frozen chocolate frangos
directions: Using electric mixer, beat butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add melted chocolate and continue beating thoroughly.
Add egg yolks and beat again until fluffy.
Blend in extracts.
Sprinkle 1/2 nuts into 18 cupcake liners.
Spoon mixture into liners.
Top with remaining nuts.
Freeze.
When serving, can be topped with whipped cream.

title: chicken strata casserole
directions: Put 3 slices cubed bread in greased casserole dish (9 x 13 x 2-inches).
Spread on chopped chicken.
Pour on mixture of next 8 ingredients.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Add soup and buttered bread cubes.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Last 1/2 hour, add 1/2 cup grated cheese.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except lettuce and tomatoes with electric mixer.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Top with lettuce and tomatoes. Serve with nacho chips.

title: apricot sticks
directions: Mix the apricots, sugar and water in saucepan.
Let come to a boil and cool.
Mix the remaining ingredients like pie dough. Take out 1 cup or approximately half for top.
Press remainder in shallow pan. Spread apricot mixture over.
Spread cup of dry mixture over and pat down.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add the egg yolk and vanilla; mix until blended.
Add flour and blend.
Chill overnight.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook each batch at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: zucchini coleslaw
directions: Drain zucchini between layer of paper towels.
Place in a large bowl and combine with cabbage, carrot, onions and radishes. In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables and toss well. Cover and chill at least 1 hour. Contains 55 calories.
Diabetic Exchange:
1 vegetable, 1/2 fat.

title: aunt denny's turkey loaf
directions: Combine all the ingredients, mixing well.
Place in a glass 9 x

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Dissolve chocolate in hot water and set aside to cool.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Dissolve soda and salt in 1/4 cup buttermilk.
Meantime, add 3/4 cup buttermilk alternately with flour to cream mixture.
Then add the soda and buttermilk, then dissolved chocolate and the vanilla.
Mix well, then fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Grease and lightly flour 3 (9-inch) cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Let cool in pans for 10 to 15 minutes or cake will crumble.

title: country vanilla ice cream(no cooking involved)
directions: Beat eggs, adding sugar gradually.
Continue to beat until mixture is very stiff.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into a gallon freezer container and freeze ice cream as directed.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in boiling water until tender.
Drain and mash squash.
Mix remaining ingredients and mash squash.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to squash.
Remove 1/4 cup grated cheese and 1/4 cup crackers for top of casserole.
Place squash in lightly buttered 8 x 8-inch casserole.
Add grated cheese and cracker crumbs on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes or until brown on top.

title: stuffed turkey loaf
directions: Brown onion and celery in margarine in frying pan.
Combine with stuffing mix, poultry seasoning, eggs and water to make a stuffing.
Add half of stuffing to ground turkey and mix well. Pat out half of meat mixture in two (1-quart) loaf pans.
Spread with remaining stuffing, then top with remaining meat mixture.
Pour tomato juice over loaves and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Serves 8.

title: sugar-free cream puff dessert
directions: Bring the water and oleo or butter to a boil; remove from heat.
Add the flour and eggs, one at a time; beat after adding each egg until fluffy.
Spread on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: In baking dish, lay chicken (may substitute pork cutlets) on bottom.
Fix dressing according to package instructions; add soup. Pour over meat and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: veal cutlets
directions: Pound veal thin.
Cut into 8 pieces.
Enclose 1 slice of cheese and 1 slice of ham, season with salt, pepper and sage, between 2 veal cutlets.
Moisten with wine.
Flour each veal sandwich.
There should be 4. Brown in butter and oil; turn and brown other side. Keep warm.
Add wine to skillet and scrape up brown pieces.
Pour over cutlets.
Serves 4.

title: cornbread skillet
directions: Brown hamburger and add onion, chili and Worcestershire sauce, soup and water.
Drain beans and spread over hamburger.
Put cheese on top of beans.
While this mixture is coming to a boil, add milk and egg as directed on the Jiffy muffin mix.
Mix just until moist and pour over top of meat mixture.
Turn on low or simmer and cook for 25 minutes, covered (don't peek!).
During the 25 minutes of cooking, toss together a green salad and your meal is complete.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Mix sugar, catsup, soy sauce, vinegar and garlic.
Pour over chicken in casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or more. Serve with wild rice or white rice.
Put a little sauce on it. This is very tasty.

title: baked potatoes
directions: Mix together and bake at 350°
for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook pasta; drain.
Mix ingredients, except 1 cup cheese.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes, covered.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in butter. Add chicken, soup and milk.
Heat for 15 minutes. Serve on toast.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Beat all ingredients together well.
Pour into buttered pan. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In a 3 or 4-quart pan over medium heat, cook salt pork until soft.
Leave in pan.
Put in onions, carrots and celery.
Cook until soft.
Pour in clam juice and add potatoes, salt, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and hot pepper oil.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, or until potatoes and carrots are tender.
Stir in half and half and clams.
Add the liquid they are in.
Add parsley.
Heat until hot, without boiling.
Remove salt pork now, which is floating on top.
Makes 8 cups.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, butter and water.
Bring to a boil. Beat eggs and nuts.
Add hot syrup gradually.
Pour filling into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 30 minutes in a 375° oven until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: caren's country breakfast
directions: Layer bread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add cheese.
Mix together the eggs, milk and mustard; beat.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes; check with toothpick.
It should come out dry.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: kahlua cake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch
baking
pan, layer cake (which has been slit in
half,
lengthwise).
Layer of pudding, layer of Cool Whip, second half of cake, kahlua and pudding ending with Cool Whip on top.

title: watergate pudding
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix with hands and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan: flour, sugar, oleo and pecans.
Bake at 375° until light brown.

title: willie's homemade vegetable beef soup
directions: In large stock pot, brown ground chuck and onion.
Add tomato soup, tomatoes and water.
Add potatoes, peas, carrots, corn and green beans to meat mixture.
Season with basil, salt, seasoned salt, pepper and sugar.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 1/2 hour.
If soup is too thin you can make a cornstarch thickening and add to soup for texture and thickness. (Two tablespoons cornstarch and 1/2 cup water.
Mix and pour gradually into soup.)

title: mae's bread pudding
directions: Combine biscuits, milk and water; let soak until soft. Add remaining ingredients. Grease large baking dish with oil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm on top.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; saute onions and celery.
Add cheese and milk.
In casserole, put soup, rice, broccoli and water.
Mix. Pour cheese mixture over and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: steamed fish(jing yue)
directions: Preparation:
Shred green onions lengthwise and cut into 1-inch lengths.
Sliver ginger.
Clean fish; sprinkle with salt and place in a wide, shallow dish with a rim, about 1-inch high. Dish may be prepared ahead of time to this point.
The author comments, "Never cook seafood ahead of time.
It must be eaten as soon as it is cooked."

title: super easy salmon loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl with fork, shred salmon. Add butter and eggs; mix until blended.
Stir in crackers.
In small glass measure, mix buttermilk with baking soda; stir into salmon mixture until blended.
Spoon mixture into prepared pan. Bake 30 minutes until set.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: pat's bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 to 1/2 cup water. Cream oleo or butter, Crisco, sugar and salt. Add yeast and eggs. Then add 1 cup hot water and 1 cup cold water.
Add flour. Knead. Let rise in refrigerator overnight or in a warm place. Punch down. Rise again. Shape and bake at 350° in oven 30 minutes.

title: mock lobster
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape and lay on a bed of lettuce. Top with seafood sauce.

title: tomorrow's salad
directions: *To make 1 cup juice add water.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together; beat eggs.
Add to dry mixture.
Add applesauce.
Also mix well.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.

title: corned beef cheese ball
directions: Chop corned beef into small pieces.
Mix with first four ingredients.
Shape into ball, roll in pecans.
Chill before serving.

title: mushroom soup
directions: In soup pot, heat chicken broth to boil.
Fry onion.
Add to broth.
Fry mushrooms in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add to broth. Add thyme, bay leaf and peppercorns.
Bring soup to rolling boil.

title: ella davis' molasses cake
directions: Cream well the sugar and shortening.
Add next 4 ingredients. Dissolve the baking soda in 1 cup boiling water.
Add to sugar mixture, then add the flour.
Mix and let stand for 20 minutes. Roll on floured board.
Cut and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Lay cake close in pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Do not take cake from pan while hot.

title: *garu 2(wheat)
directions: Follow same directions as the Garu made for church in 8 pound bulk.

title: butterfinger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Beat in egg.
Sift dry ingredients over cut up pieces of candy bars.
Combine with wet mixture.
Chill.
Drop on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes.
Remove immediately.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar gradually until light and fluffy. Add remaining ingredients in order listed.
Blend well and pour into unbaked shell.
Bake for 40 minutes at 375°.

title: aunt virginia's favorite planter's punch
directions: Pour all ingredients into a cocktail shaker; shake well.
Pour over crushed ice in a Tom Collins glass.
Decorate with fruit in season.
Serve with a straw.

title: pittsburgh potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in boiling salt water for 5 minutes. Add pimentos and cook 7 minutes.
Drain.
Put into baking dish and pour on sauce mixed with cheese and salt.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are soft.

title: broccoli side dish
directions: Cook fresh broccoli.
Do not overcook.
Drain and cut into small pieces.
In skillet, add olive oil and broccoli.
Sprinkle garlic powder over broccoli to taste.
Stir-fry until heated through.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top, if desired.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into balls and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
You can freeze them.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple and add enough water to make 2 cups.
Heat and dissolve Jell-O in it.
Cool and add Coke.
Set aside until slightly thickened then add rest of ingredients.
Add nutmeats if desired.
Freeze cream cheese and dice for easier crumbling.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Melt cheese and one stick of butter over low heat.
Pour over broccoli in a square casserole dish. Stir and mix together with a fork.
Mix crushed Ritz crackers and a 1/2 stick melted butter.
Sprinkle on top of broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pinon gravy
directions: Crush pinons and boil them until oil rises to top; skim off oil.
Boil again and season with salt.

title: delectabites
directions: Thoroughly mix butter or oleo, sugar and vanilla.
Gradually stir in flour and walnuts or pecans.
Chill.
Shape into marble-size balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes, until firm, but not brown.
Roll gently in powdered sugar.
Cool; sugar again.
Makes 50 cookies.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Spray a Bundt pan with Pam and sprinkle pecans in bottom of pan. Mix remaining ingredients in a large bowl with electric mixer about 2 minutes. Spoon batter over pecans. Batter will be very thick. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Test with toothpick for doneness.

title: banana pops
directions: Peel bananas and slice in half crosswise.
Brush bananas with orange juice.
Insert wooden skewers in cut end.
Place on waxed paper-lined cookie sheet.
Freeze until firm.
Combine chocolate chips and shortening in top of double boiler.
Bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook until chocolate melts, then cool slightly.
Spoon chocolate over frozen bananas.
Immediately roll coated bananas in nuts.
Serve at once or wrap in plastic wrap. Freeze.

title: texas trash
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Melt butter and grease.
Add rest of spices and pour over nuts.
Bake at 275° for 30 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.

title: salami
directions: Mix ingredients well and let stand 24 hours in icebox, covered.
Take out and roll into 3 rolls.
Place in aluminum covered pan and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: coconut filling
directions: Combine sugar and water or coconut juice in a saucepan.
Cook until syrupy.
Add coconut and cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Ice a plain cake. Makes enough icing for a 2-layer cake.

title: german purtzels
directions: Mix lukewarm water, sugar and yeast in a bowl.
Add salt and 2 cups of the flour; beat with mixer.
Add eggs and melted shortening; mix.
Add 4 1/2 cups flour, raisins and vanilla. Allow to rest about 20 minutes.
Spoon into real hot grease and brown; drain and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cherry vanilla ribbon pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth. On low speed, beat in water and pudding mix until smooth. Chill 10 minutes. Fold in whipped cream. Spread half the pudding mixture in prepared pastry shell. Top with half the cherry pie filling. Repeat. Chill 2 hours or until set. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: molasses muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease muffin tins.
Mix or sift dry ingredients.
Mix together egg, oil, honey & molasses then gradually add to dry ingredients.
Slowly stir in hot water.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full and bake for 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Remove from tins and cool.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place blueberries in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and margarine together with fork and knife until mixed well.
Sprinkle mixture over blueberries.
Bake for 1 hour.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: vegetable chowder
directions: Mix everything together in a large heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Cook slowly, covered, until potatoes and celery are tender, about 20 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spumoni cake
directions: To one part, add green food coloring and chopped nuts.
To one part add red food coloring and chopped red cherries.
To one part, add melted unsweetened chocolate and chocolate bits, if desired.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix salad oil, eggs and sugar with a wooden spoon, then beat until creamy.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder and add gradually to batter and beat well.
Add vanilla, then chopped apples and pecans.
Mix and pour into well-greased 8 x 8-inch pan and bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: cracker pie
directions: Place in buttered pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil fryer in salted water until very tender.
Remove all bones and skin.
Break into pieces.
Saute onion and celery. Add the mushrooms and chicken soup with cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Simmer until cheese melts.
Add chicken and cook over low heat for 30 minutes. Break flour tortillas in pieces for a thin layer in bottom of dish.
Add half the chicken mixture. Repeat tortillas and rest of chicken. When ready to use, top with shredded Cheddar cheese and bake at 350° until cheese melts and chicken is hot and bubbly.
To increase amount use larger fryer, one mixed cream of mushroom and cream of chicken soup and more Velveeta cheese.

title: apricot whip
directions: Stir first 8 ingredients together and make a well in the center.
Slowly add oil and milk, that have been mixed together in the measuring cup.
Stir and pat and press into a 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine, sugar, oil, flavoring, eggs (one at a time), milk and flour.
Grease and flour tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool 30 minutes.

title: garlic fried chicken
directions: Combine buttermilk, lemon juice, garlic, salt, pepper and celery salt.
Mix well.
Place chicken in a shallow pan and pour buttermilk mixture over top.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight.
Remove chicken from liquid.
Dredge chicken in flour.
Heat 1-inch of oil in a large skillet to 325°.
Add chicken and fry 30 to 35 minutes, turning once.
Drain chicken well on paper towels.
Yields 4 servings.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; add buttermilk, oleo and eggs.
Beat at low speed with an electric mixer until moistened; beat at medium speed 3 minutes.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine 1/2 cup brown sugar, pecans and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle over batter.
Cover and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in a 400° oven for 1 hour.
While still hot, slice each potato in half lengthwise.
Scoop out pulp into a large bowl.
Mash potatoes, adding salt, pepper, margarine and milk to taste.
Stir in onion, Cheddar cheese, Monterey Jack cheese and spinach.
Spoon back into shells.
Bake potato halves at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serve, or freeze potatoes before reheating.

title: scalloped mashed potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Wash and dice or cut in rings.
Put in pot with water; cook until done.
Pour excess water off.
Add butter, onion salt and garlic salt.
Blend with mixture or with fork.
Put pot on low heat; add cheese and sour cream.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Let simmer for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: pizza di pasqua(easter tart)
directions: Lightly grease and flour two 9-inch pans.
Blend butter and flour and shape into a well.
Add egg yolks, powdered sugar, vanilla and milk to center.
Mix ingredients well and knead to form a ball of dough.
Set aside one-quarter of the dough for later use.
Roll out remainder of dough and use it to line the bottom and sides of the prepared pans.

title: pickles
directions: Cook 4 hours, slowly.
Makes 12 pints.
Can or keep in refrigerator.

title: "california clam chowder"
directions: Fry diced bacon and onion.
Add garlic; fry until onion browns.
Put aside.
Boil cubed potatoes until soft.
Do not drain.
Add to bacon mixture.
Stir together.
Add all other ingredients.
Do not allow chowder to boil.
Simmer until you feel the flavors have blended.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add water, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook until meat is tender, about 45 minutes.
You may need to add more water.
Add celery and onions.
Cook 1/2 hour.
Add mushrooms.
Mix soy sauce and cornstarch.
Stir into cooked mixture until thick.
Add drained bean sprouts and water chestnuts.
Serve over rice.

title: watergate salad
directions: Put pineapple and syrup in mixing bowl.
Add pudding mix. After mixing pineapple and pudding mix, fold in Cool Whip.

title: cucumber rounds(sounds boring but very yummy and light.)
directions: Find a cookie cutter or small glass to cut rounds of bread about the same size of the cucumber rounds.
Mix dill weed, mayo and onion together.
Spread mixture onto bread rounds top with cuke round and sprinkle with lemon pepper to garnish.
Assemble rest of rounds and enjoy!

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix other ingredients and add flour mixture.
Roll in ball size.
Place on a cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Flatten with a fork dipped in hot water.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until well done.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Heat water and shortening to a rolling boil in saucepan.
Stir in flour all at once.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture leaves sides of pan and forms a ball, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat, beat in egg thoroughly.
Beat mixture until smooth and velvety.
Mix in cheese and meat.
Drop by teaspoons on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 25 minutes or until puffed and golden brown.
Makes about 30 puffs.

title: one hundred dollar cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until soft and fluffy.
Add chocolate which has been melted over hot water.
Add eggs which have been thoroughly beaten.
Add flour, salt, baking powder, vanilla, nuts and milk.
Pour into two 9-inch pans and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: heavenly onion
directions: Slice onions thin; saute.
Put in buttered 9 x 12-inch flat casserole.
Add layer of Swiss cheese, grated.
Add layer of sliced and buttered French bread.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix 1 can cream of chicken soup, 1/2 cup milk and 2 teaspoons of soy sauce. Pour over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
May be prepared a day early and refrigerated.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together;
put in a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ice cream jello(do day before)
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Mix ice cream in jello water.
Add fruit.
Put in casserole or Tupperware dish.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix together and leave covered in refrigerator overnight.
Use yellow cake mix.
Mix 2 layers and slit each layer, making four. Ice with the mixture between layers and on top, do not ice sides. Seal in cake cover and refrigerate for 4 days.
Icing is slightly liquid and absorbed by cake.

title: "pecan pie ooo-la-la"
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar; mix well.
Add other ingredients and the 1/2 cup chocolate morsels.
Add 1 cup pecan pieces; blend well.

title: bloodshot eyeball cookies(halloween)
directions: Frost cookies with frosting, leaving edges of cookies showing. Press jelly beans into frosting to make pupils of eyes.
Decorate with red gel to make "eyes" look bloodshot.

title: hot crab or sealeg dip
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add cream cheese and blend (butter may separate a little).
Add crab meat and stir.
Pour in baking dish.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 375°
until hot and bubbly (approximately 1/2 hour).
Serve with crispy crackers.

title: cherry berry in the snow
directions: Start the day before serving.
Heat oven to 275°.
Beat egg whites, tartar and salt until frothy.
Gradually add 1 3/4 cups sugar.
Beat until stiff and glossy.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake for 1 hour.
Turn off oven and leave in oven until cool.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown
the chopped bacon, celery and onion in olive oil and butter.
When brown, add the beef, salt and pepper and let meat brown
slowly.
When
meat is brown, baste with wine and cook until the wine has almost completely evaporated.
Sprinkle
the meat
with
flour.
Add
the tomato sauce and enough water to cover meat and cook for about 40 minutes.
When meat is
cooked, add
the chopped garlic, parsley and fennel seed. Cook 10 minutes longer, then serve.
Serves 6.

title: leg of lamb
directions: Make slit in the leg of lamb and put garlic pieces inside. Season outside of lamb with salt, pepper and paprika.
In bottom of pan, put sliced onions and mixture of water and tomato juice. Cook 3 1/2 hours in 325° oven.
After first 1 1/2 hours, mix brown sugar and ketchup together and spread over meat; do not baste, sauce will form gravy.

title: cabbage kielbasa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large Dutch oven.
Cover and cook over medium heat, 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: barley casserole
directions: Brown onion, celery and barley in butter about 3 minutes.
Put soup, parsley and water in casserole dish; stir until slightly mixed.
Add browned onion, celery and barley and stir until uniform.
Bake, covered, 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Stir before serving.
Serves 6.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil and sugar, and mix thoroughly.
Add cake mix and sour cream and mix well.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50 minutes.

title: linguine
directions: Brown
hamburger,
green pepper and onion; drain.
Cook noodles
at
same
time.
Break
into 4 pieces before cooking. Mix hamburger mixture, noodles, pizza sauce, tomato sauce and Parmesan
cheese.
Put
in	9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Have a baked pie shell that is cool.

title: oven baked stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large roasting pan.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours or at 250° for 4 hours (wait 2 hours to peek, then re-cover and finish baking).

title: sausage wild rice casserole
directions: Cook sausage until slightly browned.
Add rice and seasonings and water as directed on package.
Cook and simmer until almost dry.
Mix eggs and soup.
Set aside.
Place a layer of Rice Krispies in slightly greased casserole, then a layer of cheese. Repeat until filled.
Last, pour egg and soup mixture over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: egg souffle
directions: Beat with beater
until
frothy
first	4
ingredients. Stir in cubed cheese.
Pour
into
greased deep 1-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 30
minutes
or until golden brown and fluffy. Serve with bacon,
sausage	or
ham
and hash browns. May be served as a breakfast or brunch.
Serves 4.

title: trisha's snickerdoodles
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Add to first mixture.
Mix well and chill.

title: old fashioned potato salad
directions: Stew potatoes until done. Drain and mash with the mayonnaise. Add the eggs, onion, cucumbers or sweet pickle cubes and salt and pepper to taste.

title: spinach with corn
directions: Saute garlic and shallot in broth in nonstick skillet until soft.
Add corn; cover and steam for 3 minutes.
Add drained spinach, herb blend and vegetable seasoning.
Cover and cook for 2 more minutes.

title: homestyle macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Drain.
Grate cheese.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk and melted butter.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish. Bake at 400° for approximately 30 minutes.
Top with cheese and brown on top.
Serves 6.

title: bath salts
directions: You will need baby food or other small empty jars.

title: good brownies
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt butter and mix graham cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle coconut on top, then pour Eagle Brand milk on top. Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Melt chocolate and peanut butter together.
Pour over crust. Top with almonds.

title: karen's hot taco dip
directions: Mix the beans, taco mix and onions together and put in a 9 x 13 dish sprayed with Pam. Spoon sour cream onto bean mixture and spread evenly. Top with cheese. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Serve with taco chips.

title: three layer caramel cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream together butter, sugar and eggs. Beat until smooth.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix until well blended.
Add milk and flavors.
Mix until smooth and fluffy.

title: orange-cranberry torte
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and baking soda; stir in nuts, dates, whole cranberries and orange rind.
Combine eggs, buttermilk and salad oil.
Add to flour/fruit mix.
Stir until blended.
Pour into well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Let stand in pan until lukewarm. Remove to rack over wide dish.
Combine orange juice and 1 cup sugar; heat until sugar dissolves and pour over cake.
Pour drippings over again and again until gone.
Wrap in foil. Refrigerate; serve with cream.
Will refrigerate 2 weeks or more or freeze.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; drain and add taco seasoning and small amount of water.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Cool.
Place lettuce in large bowl. Add hamburger, beans, tomatoes, cheese and chips.
You may put dressing on salad or serve it on the side.
I mix 3/4 cup dressing to 1/4 cup taco sauce or to taste.

title: pizza hits
directions: In a
cup
combine
butter, garlic salt and onion salt. Split muffins
in
half and spread with seasoned butter. Place in baking pan. Toast under broiler 3 inches from heat. Remove and spread halves
with catsup.
Layer with one slice each of Provolone
and American
cheese.
Top with a slice of Italian sausage.
Sprinkle with oregano. Broil 4 to 7 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: dutch cake
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Pour melted butter (3 to 4 tablespoons) over top.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: potato onion soup with cheddar cheese
directions: Cook garlic, potatoes, onions and celery, stirring occasionally, 10 to 15 minutes.
Add broth, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes or until tender.
Stir in milk and add cheese.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter and saute onions.
Add soups and Cheez Whiz, stirring until melted.
Add broccoli.
Mix well and pour into baking dish.
I cook this in the microwave for 30 minutes or bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ann's tomato aspic
directions: Mix
gelatin
according to package directions.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into small mold or individual molds. Let
set in refrigerator until firm.
Makes 4 servings;
each serving 29 calories, 1.2 grams protein and 0 grams fat.

title: frozen strawberry jam
directions: Mix strawberries and sugar and let stand for 30 minutes. Take water and Sure-Jell and boil for 1 minute. Add to berries and sugar. Put in cups/jars and jell. Freeze.

title: sugar cream cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well and put in greased cake pan (9 x 13-inch).
On top add mixture of powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.
Will look like a bar cookie when cooled.

title: buckeyes
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter together, then add sugar.
Mix well.
Roll into bite size balls. Chill for about 1 hour.
Melt chocolate chips in saucepan along with paraffin. Stick toothpicks in balls, then dip into chocolate mixture.
Put balls, chocolate coated, on wax paper to set.
Remember to let a small section of top of ball not covered with chocolate to look like the buckeye. After chocolate is set, serve as you like.

title: chocolate krinkles
directions: Combine ingredients, dry first and then wet.
Chill dough overnight.

title: uncle albert's roasted chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Remove giblets; trim.
Cover with water (with bay leaf).
Simmer until tender; remove chicken and reserve broth for gravy.
Wash and dry chicken; rub inside with salt.
Oil outside of bird.
Insert meat (poultry) thermometer.
Tuck wings under back (truss legs, if desired).
Place in a 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and continue to roast for 30 minutes, or until thermometer reaches 185°.
Remove from pan to platter; let rest 15 minutes before carving.
Serve with favorite stuffing (baked separately) and gravy made with pan drippings and giblet broth.

title: dog biscuits(makes 8 dozen)
directions: *To brush on tops.

title: tuna florentine
directions: Squeeze spinach to remove excess water.
Spread spinach evenly in bottom of 2 quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with onion, tuna, and eggs.
Mix soup and sour cream together.
Pour over eggs.
Mix melted margarine with bread crumbs and sprinkle evenly over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until brown and bubbly.
Serve with warm fresh bread.

title: apple bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat eggs.
Add sweetened condensed milk, applesauce, water, margarine, cinnamon and vanilla.
Stir in bread and raisins, completely moistening bread.
Turn into buttered 9-inch square pan.
Bake 1 hour or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool.
Serve warm with whipped cream.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: no-cook summer chili
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving or early in day, slice jalapeno pepper lengthwise in half; remove and discard seeds. Finely chop jalapeno pepper. Thinly slice red onion.
In large bowl, combine jalapeno pepper with undrained pork and beans, drained corn, white beans, black beans, tomatoes and chili powder. Sprinkle sliced onions on top.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap and refrigerate 1 hour to blend flavors.
Makes 6 main dish servings.

title: favorite company casserole(serves 6)
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add garlic, tomato sauce, sugar, salt and pepper.
Simmer about 10 minutes and remove garlic.
Cook noodles according to package directions. Chop onions, including tops, and mix with cottage cheese and sour cream.

title: awesome chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery, and carrots in 1 tsp. margarine. In a bowl, combine sour cream, both soups, chicken, and peas; add in sauteed vegetables. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 baking dish. Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 30 min. Combine crackers crumbs with the rest of the margarine; sprinkle over the top and bake for 10 min. longer.

title: potato and ham casserole
directions: Saute ham and onion.
Mix together all of the ingredients in a casserole.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover a little while before it is done.

title: angel fancy
directions: Melt chocolate in water.
Blend in beaten yolks.
Cook and stir a few seconds; add vanilla and salt.
Cool.
Fold sugar into whipped cream and fold this into chocolate mixture.
Fold in beaten egg whites last.
Pour over angel cake pieces in large bowl or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill overnight.
Serve with dollops of whipped cream, if desired.

title: pepper steak
directions: Pound flour into steak along with black pepper; cut into strips.
Brown meat in olive oil, put in onions and cook a little while.
Add water to cover.
Season with salt and pepper to taste. Add tomato sauce; cook until meat is tender.
Put in carrots, green pepper, cook until tender.
Add peas; add water as necessary.
Good over mashed potatoes.

title: chicken stew
directions: Cut up chicken and cook slowly in gallon of water for 2 hours. Do
not
boil rapidly.
Debone chicken and put back in broth. Add
next
ingredients.	Cook
slowly
for 6 hours, adding
hot water
occasionally to have 5 to 6 quarts of this mixture.
Then add
the potatoes and corn.
Cook 1 more hour. Stir
often	to prevent scorching.	Season with salt, pepper, sugar
and
hot sauce
as
desired.
This is great to have in freezer for a quick meal.

title: kansas city cinnamon rolls
directions: Scald 1 cup of milk; add sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm, then dissolve yeast in a cup of warm water.
Add to milk mixture the egg and 2 cups of unsifted flour.
Beat until smooth. Stir in 2 more cups of flour.
Refrigerate in covered bowl at least 2 hours (up to 1 week).
Roll out into a 7 x 14-inch rectangle on a floured surface.
Spread with oleo pretty thick.
Spread with brown sugar.
Sprinkle with cinnamon liberally.
Roll up and seal edges. Cut into 20 rolls.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and let rise to doubled in size, about 30 minutes in a warm place. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar and milk frosting; recipe found on confectioners sugar box.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Fold in morsels and pecans.

title: one step from starvation meal
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Brown meat; drain off fat.
Place corn, peas, macaroni and meat in a big pot.
Add milk and cheese; mix.

title: turkey tetrazzini (or chicken)
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper, celery in 2 Tbsp. butter.
Stir in soup and broth.
Cook until hot.
Stir in meat, mushrooms, peas and cheese.
Cook 2 minutes.
Season with pepper and add spaghetti. Transfer to casserole.
(Totals 4 quarts)

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Trim excess fat off ribs.
Place in slow cooking pot.
In a bowl, combine tomato soup, vinegar, brown sugar, soy sauce, celery seed and chili powder.
Pour over ribs.
Cover and slow cook at setting number 2 1/2 for 8 to 9 hours, setting number 3 for 6 to 7 hours or setting number 4 for 4 hours.
Reduce to number 2 for serving.

title: microwave hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Mix flour, granulated sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt in an ungreased 3-quart microwavable casserole. Stir in milk, oil and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in nuts. Sprinkle the brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa over all.
Do not stir!!
Bring water to a boil and pour over the batter.
Do not stir!!
Microwave, uncovered, on High until cake is set, but still glossy, approximately 9 to 10 minutes.
Turn casserole every 3 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.
Makes about 8 delicious servings.

title: mama's corn bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add butter, eggs and buttermilk. Mix quickly and pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan. Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: old-fashioned egg custard
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add condensed milk and flour or cornstarch.
Then add beaten egg yolks and mix well.
Add vanilla. Add well beaten egg whites.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake slowly at 325°.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the sugars and shortening.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: reuben ham sandwiches
directions: Spread mayonnaise on six slices and spread mustard on remaining slices. Layer 1 cheese slice, 3 tablespoons of sauerkraut and 1 ham slice on bread and mayonnaise; top with other bread.
Place on a baking sheet and broil four inches from heat (with electric oven door partially opened) two minutes on each side or until cheese melts.
Yield:
6 sandwiches.

title: classic cheese cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, 1/3 cup sugar and melted margarine. Press into bottom and up the sides of a spring-form pan.

title: pickle-pepper relish
directions: Grind together the peppers, onions and cukes.
Let drain overnight.
Heat the remaining ingredients until sugar is dissolved.
Cool, then mix with relish.
Put in jars; leave in refrigerator for 3 to 4 days, then put into freezer.

title: german chocolate cake shortcut
directions: In a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass dish, place a layer of chopped nuts and a layer of coconut.
Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour over first two layers.

title: best cake
directions: Hand mix all ingredients (no shortening in this cake).
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. For a glass pan, bake at 325°.
Frost immediately after removing from oven.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Mix together the broth, soy sauce, sherry and cornstarch; set aside.
Cut chicken into 1-inch cubes.
Heat liquid Butter Buds in a large pan or wok and brown chicken quickly.
Remove from pan and keep warm.
Add garlic, mushrooms and snow peas; stir for 2 minutes until mushrooms are golden brown.
Return chicken to pan. Add water chestnuts and bamboo shoots.
Pour well mixed sauce over all and cook for 2 to 3 minutes until chicken is done and vegetables are crisp and tender.
Serves 4.

title: ann's red rice
directions: Brown sausage in bacon drippings; add onion and green pepper. Saute.
Stir in tomato paste and water; add rice and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer on low for 45 minutes or until rice is done.

title: mike hughes' quick ginger baked beans
directions: Drain the juice from the beans and discard.
Chop onion coarsely and saute in the butter.
Microwave the bacon (not quite crisp).

Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan (if you are in a hurry) or covered baking dish (if you've got more time). Simmer on the stove top for 15 minutes or bake at 350° for 40 minutes (the longer they cook, the better they are).

title: hamburger roll
directions: Mix Bisquick and milk until soft dough forms.
Roll out flat. Brown ground meat and diced onions.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Drain.
Place on dough and roll like a jelly roll.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 11 minutes until golden brown.
Slice and put brown gravy over it.

title: fruit punch - delphi
directions: Blend ingredients in a blender until smooth.
Add 1 cup punch base to 1 quart water.
Serve cold.

title: fresh corn saute
directions: Remove husks and silk from corn; cut corn from cobs.
In large skillet, cook corn and remaining ingredients except ground pepper in oil until tender-crisp.
Serve with ground pepper.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Heat beans to boiling point with 1 tablespoon margarine. Drain and pour into baking dish. Add shredded cheese and soup. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Add onion rings and cook 10 minutes more.

title: "philly" chocolate tunnel cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake according to directions, substituting margarine for oil.
Reserve 1 cup batter.
Pour remaining batter into 12 cup greased and floured fluted tube pan. Combine cream cheese and sugar, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Blend in eggs, one at a time.
Pour over batter in pan.
Spoon reserved batter over cream cheese mixture.
Bake 1 hour or until toothpick inserted near center comes clean.
Cool 30 minutes; remove to wire rack.
Combine 2 tablespoons margarine, chocolate and corn syrup in small saucepan. Cook over low heat until chocolate is melted.
Pour over cooled cake.
Makes 12 servings.

title: mexican pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Prepare potatoes as directed, except decrease water to 1 cup and omit milk.
Stir in egg, green onion and sour cream.
Press potato mixture into pie plate.
Prick bottom and sides with fork.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: andagi(okinawan doughnuts)
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar and baking powder.
Beat eggs in a separate bowl and add milk.
Fold in the milk mixture with the dry ingredients.
Do not mix too much.
With a teaspoon, scoop the dough and drop the ball-shaped dough into hot oil, about 350°.
As dough rises to the top of the oil, turn the dough around to brown the Andagi evenly.

title: banana oatmeal muffins
directions: Sift the flour and mix all dry ingredients together except oats.
Mix in the rest of the ingredients, adding oats and chocolate chips last.
Bake in muffin cups at 350° for 17 to 20 minutes.
Fill muffin cups almost full.
Yields 24.

title: mexican appetizer
directions: Mix cream cheese, green chilies and green onions together. Add black olives.
Spread a thin layer on one whole tortilla.
Cut tortilla in half and place on half of mixture.
Fold other half of whole tortillas over the half tortilla.
This creates a half circle.
Continue until all tortillas and mixture are used.
Chill and slice very thin.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy. Gradually add sugar until stiff. Fold in chocolate chips, nuts and other ingredients. Preheat oven to 400°.
Turn off when put in.
Leave for 4 hours in oven.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into a buttered loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour no. 2
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until becomes syrupy.
Mix cornstarch and water.
Add cornstarch and water mixture to first 4 ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring until thickens.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes, cut in thin round slices.
Place in greased long baking dish, add salt and pepper to taste.
Spread can of cream of chicken soup over the potatoes.
Cut cheese into strips and place on potatoes, cover and bake at 350° until potatoes are done (about 30 to 45 minutes).

title: peppers and steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Place half the steak in a crock-pot.
Arrange green peppers on steak.
Place remaining steak on top.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover and cook on low setting for 8 to 10 hours (high setting for 4 to 5 hours).
Serve with rice.

title: apple dumplings with vanilla sauce
directions: Peel and core the apples.
Roll out small amount of pie dough to make 4 x 4-inch squares.
Place apple in center of square.
Add sugar and cinnamon to taste. Add 1 pat butter.
If you use tart apples, shake a bit of salt on the apples.
Fold corners into center and pinch together, making a bundle.
Bake at 325° in a shallow pan until apples are soft.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter until crumbly.
Save 2 to 3 tablespoons of this for top of meringue.
Place in bottom of baked pie shell.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, flour and salt.
Stir in egg yolks.
Slowly add the milk.
Over medium heat, bring to just below the boiling point.
Cook for 2 minutes.
(Mixture may bubble; don't boil hard.) Pour over peanut butter mixture in pie shell.
Beat the egg whites and cream of tartar until foamy. Gradually beat in sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Place on top; sprinkle with reserved peanut butter mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, until golden.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour into buttered casserole dish. Cover with 3/4 cup crushed saltine crackers that have been mixed with 1 tablespoon melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shelly's chess brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook ziti as usual.
Mix the egg into the Ricotta cheese. Grease 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Begin layering ingredients.
First layer of ziti, second layer meat sauce.
Top that with dollops of Ricotta, then Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top of Mozzarella.
Then start layering again, ending up with the Parmesan.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour, depending on your oven.
Do not overbake.
(Leave uncovered unless top begins browning too much.)

title: 5 minute fudge
directions: Combine margarine, milk, sugar and salt in a heavy pan over medium heat.
Bring to a boil, cook around 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly (start timing when mixture starts to bubble around edges of pan).
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, chocolate pieces, vanilla and nuts.
Stir vigorously for one minute until marshmallows melt and blend.
Pour into 8 inch square buttered pan and cool then cut in squares.

title: turkey manwich
directions: Brown turkey and onion.
Add Manwich.
Let simmer 5 minutes. Serve over rice or potatoes.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion and butter.
Cook broccoli in 1/2 cup water until tender.
Combine ingredients with the soups and Cheez Whiz. Mix in about half of the onion rings.
Pour entire mixture into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle remaining onion rings on top.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: ramen salad
directions: Combine lettuce, onions and oranges in large salad bowl. Chill.
When ready to serve, crush Ramen noodles into small pieces.
Sprinkle noodles and almonds over salad and add dressing. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: mexicana taco bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles as package directs.
Drain. Set aside.

title: monkey bread
directions: Thaw dough in greased container/pan.
Break into pieces into a 9 x 9-inch pan or cake pan (greased).
Mix remaining ingredients and spread mixture over dough bits.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing mix as directed on box.
Layer chicken, stuffing mix, peas and mushrooms.
Pour soup mix over all.
Make 2 layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with cranberry sauce. Enjoy!!

title: chicken divan
directions: Remove chicken meat from bones; cut into bite-size pieces. Cook broccoli according to package directions.
In large bowl, combine soup with salad dressing and lemon juice; mix thoroughly.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Mix jello with 1 1/4 cups boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Congeal until firm.
Beat with mixer until all is broken up.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Break cake into small pieces and put layer of cake and layer of jello mixture into pretty bowl. Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.

title: ultra low-fat barbecue chicken bake
directions: Brown chicken on the charcoal grill or in a skillet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Just sear or seal the meat.
It does not have to be cooked all the way through as it will bake for an hour in the oven.
Use half of the barbecue sauce and cover the bottom of a medium size baking dish.
Place the browned chicken breasts over the bottom of the dish.
Cover the chicken breasts with large slices of onions.
Sprinkle the beans on top of the sliced onions.
Pour remaining barbecue sauce evenly over the entire contents of the casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: "real" beef barbecue
directions: Cook beef and sauce separately.
Simmer sauce at least 45 minutes.
Shred beef in deep bowl.
Pour over beef and let set overnight.

title: broccoli and cheese dressing
directions: Cook box of dressing.
Spread dressing in 9-inch square size pan.
Cook broccoli and lay on top.
Mix soup with milk.
Pour on top.
Slice Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until cheese starts to turn brown.
You can make a larger size pan, just use more of everything.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients together and press into 9 x 13 pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Let cool completely. Mix the next three ingredients together and spread evenly over crust layer. Mix last three ingredients together and spread evenly over cream cheese layer. Chill until ready to serve. Before serving, spread another small Cool Whip on top. This seems to taste better if you make it a day ahead.

title: nut bread
directions: Beat sugar, shortening and eggs until creamy.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt thoroughly. Stir into egg mixture alternately with liquid and vanilla.
Stir nuts into last portion of flour mixture before blending it into batter.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until no batter clings to toothpick inserted in center of loaf. Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: baked rice
directions: In saucepan, melt butter and saute onions and rice about 5 minutes. Add bouillon soup and 3 1/2 ounces of water. Bring to a boil. Add sausage and drained mushrooms. Transfer to a covered baking dish and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli noodle parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut broccoli into bite-sized pieces. Cook in medium saucepan.
Drain and set aside.

title: stuffed meat loaf
directions: In a bowl, combine ground beef, 1 egg, 1/2 can tomato soup, chopped or minced onions and salt and pepper to taste.
Add bread crumbs and/or rolled oats to solidify the mixture.
In another bowl, make the small bread stuffing mixture of broken slices of bread, 1 egg and onions (celery if desired).
In a loaf pan, place half of the meat mixture.
Line the center with 1 to 2 slices of cheese and then your stuffing on top of that.
Top stuffing with 1 to 2 slices of cheese and cover with remaining meat mixture.
Top with a thin layer of ketchup.
Bake for 45 minutes to an hour at 350°.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add apples and eggs.
Spoon into pie shell.
Cover top with chopped pecans.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°. Reduce temperature to 350°; continue baking 50 minutes.

title: easy sticky buns
directions: Grease an angel food pan.
Cut bread dough into 24 pieces or use 24 roll pieces of dough.
Place dough in pan.
Pour pudding mix, brown sugar and cinnamon on top.
Pour melted margarine on top.
Add chopped pecans, if desired.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix well together the 3 (or 4) ingredients and pour into a greased bread pan, approximately 9 5/8 x 5 1/2 x 2 3/4-inch.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: angel food pie
directions: Sift the first 3 ingredients 3 times.
Add boiling water; boil until thick (about 5 minutes), stirring constantly.
Pour over beaten egg whites; beat well.
Add pineapple and vanilla; cool slightly.
Pour into cold pastry shells.
Top with whipping cream and nut halves.
Chill.

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: Fry bacon and save drippings; crumble bacon.
Cook chopped onion in drippings.
Cook spaghetti and while that's going, beat eggs.
Add cream, Parmesan cheese and parsley flakes.
Set aside for later.
Drain pasta and immediately pour egg and cream mixture over top.
Add bacon and onion.
Mix all very well.
Egg will cook on hot pasta.
Add more bacon drippings to taste, Parmesan, too. Makes 6 to 10 servings.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: In a covered 10-inch skillet, combine water, broccoli, spinach, carrots, Italian seasoning and garlic powder. Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low, cover and cook 10 minutes or until vegetables are thawed, stirring occasionally. Drain.

title: almond bark cookies
directions: Melt bark in large bowl in slow oven or in double boiler. Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Mix well, then add marshmallows and cereal.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper to cool.
May add nuts.

title: donut muffins
directions: Cream oil, sugar and egg.
Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk. Turn into greased muffin tin.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in preheated oven.
Immediately remove from pan.
Roll in butter, then in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: applesauce coffee cake
directions: In a bowl combine 3/4 cup flour and the sugar; cut in margarine.
For topping, remove 1/2 cup crumb mixture; stir in nuts and cinnamon.
Set aside.
To remaining crumb mixture add remaining flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add eggs, applesauce or apple butter and vanilla; beat until well blended.
If desired, stir in raisins.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle topping on batter.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Serve warm.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add gradually to shortening mixture.
Chill.
Roll out on floured board and cut into desired shapes.
Bake in 400° oven about 12 minutes.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: oreo cookie ice cream dessert
directions: In an 11 x 13-inch pan put the following:
Spread (all but 1/2 cup) the crushed cookies on bottom of pan; layer the ice cream evenly onto cookies.
Pour fudge sauce on ice cream; spread container of Cool Whip on top of sauce.
Sprinkle nuts and remaining cookies on top.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer 5 minutes before serving.

title: green pepper steak
directions: With sharp knife, cut beef across grain into thin 1/8-inch strips.
Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add beef, toss and set aside while preparing vegetables.
Heat oil in frypan or wok. Add beef and toss over high heat until browned.
Test for tenderness, may need to cook longer over low heat and cover.
Add vegetables, turn up heat and toss until tender.
Mix cornstarch with water.
Add and cook until thickened.
Add tomatoes and heat through.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Mix cheese and sausage first.
Then add Bisquick mix, 1 cup at a time.
Make into snack patties.
Place on brown paper sacks and bake at 325° about 25 to 40 minutes, depending on how brown you like them.

title: squash puffs
directions: Mix well.
Fry in hot oil (like hushpuppies).

title: turkey divan
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine and blend in flour.
Gradually add chicken stock and cook, stirring, until thick and smooth.
Then cook over low heat, stirring frequently 10 minutes.
Fold in whipped evaporated milk (see below) and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Arrange broccoli and turkey slices in a broiler proof pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Cover with sauce and sprinkle with cheese.
Put under preheated broiler until brown and bubbly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: spinach madeline
directions: Cook spinach; drain and save liquid.
Melt butter over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until blended, but not brown.
Add onion and cook until soft, but not brown.
Add liquid slowly, stirring constantly, to avoid lumps.
Cook until smooth and thick; continue stirring.
Add seasoning and cheese which has been cut into small pieces.
Stir until melted.
Combine with cooked spinach.
Put into a casserole topped with buttered bread crumbs. Keep in refrigerator overnight.
(Also may be frozen.)
Warm for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: macho nachos
directions: Place tortilla chips edge to edge in single layer in a shallow, microwave-safe baking dish. Spoon chili over chips. Sprinkle cheese over chili.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve hot.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Soak zucchini squash and onions in salt and cold water to cover.
Soak for 2 hours; drain well.
Make a syrup of vinegar, sugar, celery seed, turmeric and mustard seed.
Heat until hot; pour over squash.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Boil 5 minutes.
Pack in sterile jars.

title: hot & bothered rum
directions: Cream everything together except rum.
Place 1 heaping tsp. batter in mug.
Add 1 1/2 ounces rum, fill with hot water.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Combine margarine and crumbs in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Press mixture with back of spoon to form crust.
Layer on top of one another:
nuts, chocolate chips and coconut.
Pour condensed milk on top.
Bake in 350° oven about 25 minutes.
Cool, cut into bars.

title: chicken breast on rice
directions: Blend soup and milk.
Reserve 1/2 cup of the mix. Stir together remaining soup mixture, rice, mushrooms and 1/2 cup onion soup mix.
Pour into ungreased baking dish.
Arrange chicken breasts on top.
Pour reserved soup mix on top.
Sprinkle remaining onion mix on top.

title: sausage bread
directions: Prepare roll mix as directed.
Brown sausage.
Add onion. Drain.
Roll dough out before it rises and spread with sausage, then sprinkle with garlic, salt and cheese.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Place on long sheet pan and let rise as directed on hot roll mix.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, 30 to 45 minutes. Makes 24 servings.

title: best ever caramels
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, combine all ingredients except vanilla. Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until sugar is dissolved and butter is melted (20 to 25 minutes).
Continue cooking, without stirring, until candy thermometer reaches 248° or small amount of mixture dropped into ice water forms a firm ball. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool completely; cut into 1 x 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Yield:
6 dozen.

title: picante sauce
directions: Grind onions, green peppers, garlic and jalapeno peppers. Add tomatoes, chopped.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Pour into jars and process in cold pack canner for 20 minutes.
If you like thicker sauce, mix 4 teaspoons cornstarch with tomato juice and add to mixture during last 2 or 3 minutes of cooking stage.

title: beef burgundy
directions: *One part wine vinegar, 3 parts water and 1 tablespoon sugar may be substituted for wine.

title: meat loaf
directions: Blend meats, add
eggs,
bread	crumbs,
onions, tomato paste, tomatoes, salt and pepper.	Mix
well.
Put into one or two loaf pans.
Top with strips
of bacon.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until well done.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs until smooth.
Put in spices, pumpkin and water.
Mix flour, baking soda and raisins.
Mix all together. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 2 large loaves.

title: corn relish
directions: Mix all together and cook for 30 minutes. Then seal in hot jars.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° approximately 1 hour. (Use toothpick test after 45 minutes as pans and ovens vary.) This makes a large loaf or two smaller.

title: honeyed chicken teriyaki
directions: Cut chicken in 2-inch squares.
Combine flour, salt and pepper. Dip chicken into eggs, then coat with seasoned flour. Pour 1/2 inch oil in frying pan; place over medium-high heat. When oil is hot, add chicken, 1/2 at a time.
Cook, turning as needed, until golden brown.
Allow total of 6 or 8 minutes.

title: "taco salad"
directions: Just before serving, add 1 bag crushed Doritos tortilla or nacho cheese tortilla chips and mix.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Cook and stir beef, onion and garlic in shortening until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups water and all ingredients except 1/4 cup water and flour.
Cover and simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours. Shake 1/4 cup water and flour in tightly covered container.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Serve over hot noodles.

title: barbecue beef sandwiches
directions: Combine tomato juice, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, mustard, chili powder, garlic powder and red pepper.
Trim fat from meat. Place meat in a 3 1/2 to 4-quart crock-pot, cutting as necessary to fit.
Add juice mixture.
Cover; cook on low for 10 to 12 hours or on high for 5 to 6 hours.
Remove meat.
Slice thinly across grain.
Skim fat from juice.
Spoon some juices on bun.
Place meat on top with barbecue sauce.
Serves 8.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Heat corn and tomatoes together.
Add the ground meat.
Heat through, then serve.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together; pour into casserole dish.
Top with crackers and cheese; dot with butter.
Bake at 300° until it bubbles and is golden brown.
Oven temperatures may vary.

title: chicken almond casserole
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Pour raw rice over, then sprinkle almonds.
Place chicken on this.
Mix 3 cans of soup with 1 can water.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar and butter.
Add dry ingredients. Add zucchini and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoons on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: keene bean casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a bowl, mixing well. Layer green beans, water chestnuts and sauce mixture alternately in a 1-1/2 quart baking dish until all ingredients are used. Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes or until bubbly. Serves 8-10.

title: summer slush
directions: Add water to make 2 gallons in giant canister.
Mix and freeze.

title: dinosaur food
directions: Let fat stand for a while so it's not hard.
Mix fat and crushed bones well.
Add swamp water, dirt, muddy water and grass. Mix well and roll into balls.
Roll balls into powdered rocks and serve.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichokes very fine.
Mix all ingredients together in a small baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese in order given.
Pour half of the mixture into hot, well-greased iron skillet.
Sprinkle half the cheese over batter.
Add remaining batter and top with the rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butternut squash souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Put into greased baking dish and bake 45 minutes at 325° until light brown and firm. Marshmallows may then be put on top and lightly browned.
Serves 6.
Double recipe for 12 and bake in 9 x 13-inch casserole.

title: cheese pie
directions: Mix butter, flour, baking powder and salt.
Them mix in 4 eggs, beaten.
Add grated cheese, cottage cheese and green chilies.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes, then lower oven temperature to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Combine and dissolve jello, sugar and water in a small mixing bowl and pour liquid over rhubarb in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Crumble the white cake mix over ingredients.
Melt oleo and pour over top of the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: toffee dessert(makes 15 servings)
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; mix until coated.
Press 2/3 mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare pudding as package directs, using only 2 cups milk.
Blend softened ice cream into pudding until smooth.
Pour over crumbs in pan.
Refrigerate until somewhat firm.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding.
Crush frozen candy bars.
Mix with remaining crumbs.
Sprinkle on top of dessert. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: breakfast delight
directions: Cut up weenies into small portions.
Fry lightly brown.
Cut up sausages into 1-inch pieces.
Fry.
Remove.
Let drippings remain in pan.
Beat eggs together; put in drippings.
When almost done, put in cooked rice.
Stir, then add weenies and sausages, stirring together.
Lay cheese on top.
Cover with lid.
