Cut off heat. Ready to eat when cheese is completely melted.

title: blond brownies
directions: Sift flour once.
Add baking powder, soda and salt.
Sift again and add nuts.
Mix shortening with sugar and add eggs and vanilla.
Add chocolate chips and flour mixture.
Spread in a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 2 dozen.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; beat in egg.
Stir together flour, baking soda, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in apples, turn into ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cool with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat applesauce.
Add shortening, sugar and raisins.
When cool, add spices, flour and baking soda; mix, then add chopped nuts.
Turn into greased pan and bake at 350° about 1 hour and 15 minutes depending on depth of cake.
Cover with buttercream frosting.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour half of the batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Sprinkle 2 teaspoons brown sugar and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon on top of batter.
Pour other half. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pick 'em ups(body builders)
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg. Add flour and baking soda.
Stir in bran flakes, cheese and raisins.

title: chicken and ham roll
directions: Place chicken, breast down, and top with slice of ham.
Roll and wrap bacon strip around to hold in place.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Spread over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours, uncovered.

title: home ec. cookies
directions: Mix well.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 60 medium size cookies.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Form crescent rolls to greased pizza pan.
Brown sausage or bacon.
Sprinkle on top.
Sprinkle on hash browns and cheese. Beat eggs; drizzle on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: cake-like dessert
directions: Grease 9-inch pie plate with 1 tablespoon oleo.
Set aside. Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a large bowl; beat eggs and vanilla until foamy.
Stir in sugar.
Add flour mixture, stir until well combined (dough will be stiff).
Stir in apples/pears, pecans and raisins.
Spread evenly in greased pie plate.
Bake at 325° for approximately 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: baked - stuffed scrod
directions: Crumble crackers in medium sized bowl.
Add melted butter and spice.
Mix together.
Place fish fillets in baking dish.
Spread cracker mixture evenly over fish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Line tray with vanilla wafers. Pour 1/2 mixture on top of vanilla wafers.
Then put a layer of sliced bananas.
Cover with remaining pudding mixture.
Top with vanilla wafers.

title: japanese fruitcake pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add other ingredients to beaten eggs. Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: fruit salad delight
directions: Mix instant pudding with first 4 ingredients and marshmallows. Pour into serving bowl.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Garnish with nuts.
Chill until set.

title: easy fried potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes well.
Do not peel.
Amount depends on what you desire.
Microwave potatoes until tender.
Cool.
Slice and brown in French dressing.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt stick of butter in a large saucepan over medium heat. Next stir in sugar, cocoa and milk.
Stir constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter. Stir until dissolved.
Stir in 3 cups of oats and drop by spoonfuls onto foil, waxed paper or buttered plates.
Makes approximately 3 to 3 1/2 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare stuffing as directed.
Mix gravy, chicken and vegetables in 2-quart casserole, adding thyme.
Spoon stuffing over chicken mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: overnight clock rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Boil water and sugar for 5 minutes. Let cool until lukewarm.
Put yeast and water mixture in a bowl and add margarine, salt and eggs.
Mix and add enough flour to make a soft dough (about 12 cups).

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot and let cook all afternoon.

title: best ever pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add baking powder with flour and add milk gradually. Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour without opening the door.

title: prune pie
directions: Cut up prunes.
Cook in enough water to cover 1/2 inch above prunes as directed on prune package.
When cooked, add the remainder of the ingredients mixed together.
Cook gently over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Pour into prepared pie crust and cover with second crust.
Make several slits for steam to escape.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 45 minutes or until crust is nicely browned.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Cook sugar, vinegar, salt and egg yolks until thick.
Add cream cheese; stir until melted.
Add pimentos and onion.

title: curried vegetables
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; stir until cornstarch dissolves. Set aside.
Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add vegetables; stir-fry 8 minutes, or until crisp-tender.
Add curry powder; stir-fry 15 seconds.
Stir in cornstarch mixture; stir-fry 1 minute, or until thickened.
Serve immediately.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: butter bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place by teaspoonfuls on a cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Shape into a cookie with back of spoon.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: orange icing
directions: Combine ingredients in	a small bowl and mix well.
Can be served over carrot cake.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute chopped onion in oil.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer until well blended.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese.
Blend Cheddar, cream and Old English thoroughly.
Add Worcestershire, onion salt and garlic salt.
Mix well.
Form ball.
Roll in pecans.
Chill.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook the broccoli and place in casserole, then layer chicken and cheese on top.
Mix the rest of the ingredients, except the onion rings.
Pour over the broccoli, chicken and cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Place the onion rings on the casserole 20 minutes before it is finished.

title: pineapple souffle
directions: Mix eggs, pineapple, sugar and oleo.
Mix with bread cubes. Place 8 to 12 marshmallows in 8-inch square greased casserole. Pour mixture over marshmallows.
Do not stir.
Pour can of milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; add milk, water and egg yolks. Mix and microwave for 3 minutes.
Stir and microwave 2 minutes at a time until filling starts to thicken, stirring after each 2 minutes.
Add coconut and flavoring; microwave 2 minutes.
Add margarine and microwave 2 minutes at a time until thick.
Pour in baked deep pie crust.

title: stern-style garlic chicken
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan and saute chopped garlic.
Dip chicken in garlic mixture, then in a plate of Italian bread crumbs mixed with Parmesan cheese.
Put in an oven-safe baking dish. Pour leftover garlic mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread out dough and cook according to directions.
Cream together cream cheese, powdered sugar and lemon juice.
Spread over cooked cookie crust.
Drain fruits well, place on top.
Put glaze and chill a few hours.

title: sugar-free pineapple pie
directions: Combine pineapple, pudding mix and sour cream.
Pour into crust and chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: cheesy hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes, salt, pepper, onion and shredded cheese.
In another bowl, mix melted oleo, sour cream and cream of chicken soup.
Pour over potatoes and mix.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup oleo and sprinkle over top of potatoes.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Slice potatoes as thin as possible. In 2-quart glass bowl, spoon in a layer of ground beef, then a layer of potatoes, half the green beans, 1 can soup and then 3 slices cheese.
Repeat the layers.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mother's velvet cream
directions: Combine crushed cookies with margarine and press into bottom of pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Combine cream cheese which has been softened, sugar and vanilla, mixing well until blended.
Stir in 2 beaten egg yolks and chocolate pieces.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually beat in 1/4 cup sugar and fold into chocolate mixture.
Fold in cream and chopped pecans.
Pour over crust.
Freeze.
Decorate any way you wish with whipped cream.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water, then add cold water and set aside until cool.
Add corned beef, celery and remaining ingredients.
Mix all together; pour into 8 x 11-inch pan or serving dish.
Spread sour cream on top 1 hour before serving and sprinkle with finely chopped parsley.

title: biscuits on creamy chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Rinse peas under cold water and separate. Heat peas, chicken soup, sour cream, 1/2 cup milk, salt and pepper until boiling in 3-quart pan, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat and keep warm while preparing biscuits.
Stir baking mix (Bisquick and water) to a soft dough; beat 20 strokes and gently smooth dough into a ball on floured surface.
Knead 5 times and roll to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured cookie cutter.

title: chicken-stuffed peppers
directions: About 1 1/4 hours before serving, cut off top third from each pepper. Reserve tops.
Remove seeds from peppers.
Dice zucchini. In a 12-inch skillet, in 1-inch of water, place pepper bottoms. Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until peppers are tender-crisp, turning peppers occasionally.
Remove peppers from skillet; drain. Add pepper tops to water in skillet.
Over high heat, heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 1 to 2 minutes until tender-crisp. Drain.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into an oblong baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water. Cream sugar, salt and Crisco. Add soda in cup of buttermilk. Add yeast to creamed mixture. Add milk and flour; knead and let rise. Knead and make out into rolls. Let rise until double. Bake at 400°.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in food processor, except 1/2 of Colby cheese and crab.
Mix in Colby and crab by hand.
Put all into a roomy casserole and place remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: banana cake
directions: Mash bananas with sour cream.
Mix together all other ingredients and add the bananas and sour cream mixture.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: rotel dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well.
Heat soups and tomatoes until creamy.
Add ground beef.
Mix well.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.
Great with or without ground beef.

title: impossible pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Butter pie plate.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool. Serve warm.

title: sesame seed cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
With a good size teaspoon of dough, roll in hands to form ball.
Then elongate ball a little. Dip in milk, then in sesame seed.
Put on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: miss evie's conch souse
directions: Pound conch until tender.
Soak in lime juice.	Cut into pieces.
Put vegetables and salt into pot with enough water to cover generously.
Simmer until nearly done.
Add spices (to taste) and conch;
cook until all is tender.
Serve with Johnny Cake or fresh, hot Bahamian bread.

title: mocha fudge sundae cake
directions: Heat 1/4 cup skim milk.

Stir in coffee powder to dissolve. Add remaining milk, melted margarine and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Resift cake flour with salt, baking powder, 2 tablespoons cocoa powder and 1/2 cup sugar in mixing bowl.
Add milk mixture to dry ingredients, stirring with fork until blended.
Mix in oats.
Do not overmix.

title: cabbage in cream sauce
directions: Cut head of cabbage into 8 pieces.
Cook until partially tender; cool.
Make Cheese Sauce.

title: hello dolly
directions: Melt butter in a baking dish.
Spread crumbs evenly in a dish. Pour coconut, nuts and chocolate chips over crumbs; pour can of Eagle Brand milk over top.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: christmas anise bell cookies
directions: Beat margarine with 1/4 teaspoon salt for 30 seconds.
Add sugar, egg and anise; beat well.
Add flour and beat until well mixed.
Cover and chill about 30 minutes (until easy to handle). Divide dough in half.
Roll into 2 (6-inch) rolls.
Roll each in colored sugar.
Wrap and freeze 4 to 6 hours.
To bake, let roll stand at room temperature for 15 minutes.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices; let stand 10 minutes to soften.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Place M&M's on bottom half.
Fold into bell overlapping candy slightly.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: grandma's cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix together milk, sugar and salt.
Add yeast softened in water.
Stir in egg and shortening.
Mix in first with a spoon and then by hand the flour.
Let rise until doubled.
Punch down and let rise again.
Roll out dough into a 10 x 15-inch rectangle. Spread with soft butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll as a jelly roll.
Cut into 12 equal slices.

title: california chicken crepes
directions: Combine soup, chilies, onions, green onions, olives, sour cream, chicken and half of cheese.
Place 3 heaping tablespoonfuls of mixture on each tortilla and roll.
Place seam down in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Continue for all 10 tortillas.
Spoon remaining mixture evenly over top and sprinkle remaining cheese.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(Best to bring to room temperature before baking.) Serves 10.

title: breakfast casserole(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Crumble bread in bottom of casserole dish. Next, mix eggs and milk. After browning, add sausage, then cheese on top. Mix night before and refrigerate to cook next morning. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: enchilada's
directions: Cook, peel and mash potatoes.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Scald milk, add sugar, flavorings and salt.
Mix together. Stir slowly into beaten eggs.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Mix sugar, flour, mustard, salt, vinegar and water together, cook until thickened.
Add to beaten eggs and cook until thick.

title: coffee brandy pie
directions: Split ladyfingers.
Arrange over bottom and sides of buttered 9-inch pie plate, flat side down, making a crust.
Soften gelatin in brandy.
Combine milk, coffee, salt, 1/2 cup sugar, vanilla and beaten egg yolks in top of double boiler.
Cook over hot water, stirring until dissolved.
Remove from heat and cool.
When mixture begins to jell, fold in egg whites, beaten to a meringue with remaining 1/4 cup of sugar and cream of tartar, then fold in stiffly beaten cream and 3/4 cup nuts.
Mound into ladyfinger crust.
Garnish top of pie with remaining chopped nuts.
Chill until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Empty biscuit mix into large bowl.
Stir in milk and beat until smooth. Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Spread evenly in prepared pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes. Cut into 3 x 3/4-inch strips.
Makes about 3 dozen cheese sticks.

title: german pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°, then melt butter in a 10-inch skillet in oven.
Mix flour, milk and eggs with electric beater for 45 seconds.
Pour into skillet.
Put back in oven and bake.
Take out when done and sprinkle with powdered sugar and lemon juice.
Cut into sections, then spread with jelly, if desired.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 425°.

title: green tomato pickle
directions: Cut green tomatoes and onions.
Cover with 1/2 cup lime to 1 gallon water.
Let stand overnight.
Next morning, drain water from tomatoes and rinse well.
Tie spices in cheesecloth bag.
Add bag of ingredients to tomatoes and onions.
Cook 1/2 hour stirring occasionally.
Remove spice bag.
Pack into jars, cover with syrup and garnish with slices of pepper.
Seal.
Simmer in hot water bath for 15 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers thoroughly, using a vegetable brush; drain on a rack.
Slice unpeeled cucumbers into 1/8-inch or 1/4-inch slices; discard ends.
Add onions and garlic.
Add salt and mix thoroughly.
Cover with crushed ice or ice cubes, let stand 3 hours; drain thoroughly.
Remove garlic cloves; combine sugar, spices and vinegar, heat just to boiling.
Add drained cucumbers and slices and heat 5 minutes.
(Caution: Do not boil or pickles will be mushy.) Pack hot pickles loosely into clear, hot pint jars to 1/2-inch of top.
Adjust jar lids.
Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.
Have water boiling when jars are placed in water bath, so that pickles are in the boiling water the shortest time possible.
Start counting processing time as soon as water returns to boiling.
Remove jars.
Cool upright on rack away from draft.
Yields 7 pints.

title: sausage puffs
directions: Cook sausage until done, breaking up meat with a fork.
Drain off fat; place sausage in a large bowl.
Cool; add cheese, Bisquick mix, pepper and water.
Mix with fork until blended. Roll in 1/2 to 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Remove from baking sheets and cool completely.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: fruit punch
directions: You will need 2 Ziploc gallon-size freezer bags.

title: cheese niblets
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Gradually add flour.
Sprinkle in red pepper.
Fold in Rice Krispies.
Blend well.
Bake in bite size balls at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chili nuts
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Put margarine in a shallow baking pan. When it is melted, stir in chili powder and garlic, then stir in nuts.
Mix well, making sure the nuts are coated.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.
Immediately after you take them out, sprinkle generously with the salt.
Store in an airtight container.
Will keep for several weeks.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix gently in a large bowl the first 6 ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour combined mayonnaise, lemon juice and chicken soup over chicken mixture and stir gently, but thoroughly. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake one hour at 350°.
Serves 10 generously.
Can be prepared a day ahead and refrigerated.

title: burger bundles
directions: You will need a 12 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch or 2-quart shallow baking dish.

title: grammy's hash browns
directions: Put all in large bowl and mix.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan. Pour mixture into pan and bake covered 40 to 50 minutes.
Sprinkle corn flakes on top and bake another 10 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Mix all and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 50 minutes.

title: banana berry pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Mix in 1 cup of the Cool Whip.
Stir in 3/4 cup of the strawberries.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill until firm, about 15 minutes.
Whisk pudding mix into milk.
Fold in 1 1/2 cups of Cool Whip.
Stir in remaining strawberries.
Spread mixture over gelatin in pie crust.
Chill until set, about 2 hours.
Garnish with additional sliced strawberries.
Makes 8 servings.

title: western baked beans
directions: Brown together ground chuck, celery, pepper and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine all ingredients except cinnamon sticks in saucepan and heat to boiling.
Remove from heat and set aside for 15 minutes to one hour to allow flavors to blend.
When ready to serve, reheat cider.
Pour into mugs and place a cinnamon stick in each mug. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: herbed potatoes
directions: Scrub and slice potatoes.
Peel and slice onion.
Melt margarine.
Mix herb and melted margarine.
Put potatoes in crock-pot.
Layer top with onions.
Pour margarine and herb mixture over potatoes.
Cook on low 5 to 6 hours.

title: cranberry party punch
directions: Combine juices and chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving. Garnish with orange slices.
Yields 1 1/2 gallons.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute garlic and onion in oil until translucent.
Add broth, corn, chiles, chicken, and carrots.
Bring to a low boil; simmer, stirring occasionally.
Add lime juice and chili powder; stir and simmer until heated through.
Salt to taste.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Heat until cheese melts and then add 1 package of cooked spaghetti.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Add crushed potato chips.
Heat until bubbly.

title: do-ahead breakfast casserole
directions: Fry bacon and drain.
In small amount of grease, fry potatoes, onion and green pepper; drain and add bacon.
Mix eggs, cheese, milk, Bisquick and butter.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Spoon potato mixture over top of egg mixture.
At this point, casserole may be refrigerated overnight.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: rolls and cheese
directions: *Or you can use Brown 'N Serve rolls.

title: dessert coffee cake
directions: Mix like pie crust sugar, butter and flour.
Mix baking powder, eggs and milk; add to first mixture.
Spread mixture in cookie sheet.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add persimmons and egg.
Mix with mixer.
Mix dry ingredients, then add to persimmon mixture.
Fold in raisins and nuts.

title: roberta's puffed chicken breasts
directions: Place garlic in oil and allow to stand one hour.
Mix together the cheeses, bread crumbs and salt.
Dip chicken into oil and then into cheese/crumb mixture.
Press breasts into egg shapes, tucking in sides.
Place seam side down, not touching, on cookie sheet. Bake uncovered at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cover squash and onion with water; boil until tender.
Drain and reserve liquid for later use.
Add chicken soup, dressing and oleo.
Add enough reserved liquid to resemble dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: graham crispies
directions: Boil butter, margarine and sugar for two minutes.
Line cookie sheet
with
foil and put as many graham
crackers
as possible on it.
Pour mixture evenly over crackers
and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: 7-up pudding cake
directions: Blend thoroughly the cake mix, oil, nuts, eggs and 7-Up. Add dry pudding mix. Blend again. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: "death by chocolate cake"
directions: Bake 1 oblong dark chocolate Duncan Hines cake.
Cool.
Cut into thirds.
Crush Heath or Skor bars.
Set aside.
Mix chocolate mousse as directed.
Set aside.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt and blend together over hot water the chocolate chips, milk and sugar; cool.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Beat until stiff the 4 egg whites; fold into chocolate mixture.
Pour into cooled, baked pie shell. Chill several hours.

title: hot rice
directions: Cook slowly until rice is tender or liquid is absorbed.
Can add water if needed.
Great with meat.
Jalapeno peppers can be increased or decreased to suit desired hot or taste.

title: scott and alison's cheese cake
directions: In small bowl, combine chocolate wafer crumbs, butter and sugar.
Press firmly into 9-inch pie plate. Chill 15 minutes.

title: crumb cake or squares
directions: Mix flour, margarine and sugar to crumbs.
Save 1 cup for topping.
Mix rest of crumb mixture with remaining ingredients. Sprinkle with topping and bake.

title: old fashioned potato salad
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, salt, dry mustard and flour.
Add the two eggs and stir well.
Mix in vinegar and water.
Heat until thickens just a little.
When cool, add same amount of Hellmann's mayonnaise to cooked mayonnaise.
Mix the potatoes, hard-boiled eggs, celery, cucumber, onion and macaroni.
Add salt, pepper, mayonnaise and celery seed.
Makes a very large bowl.

title: baked crabmeat
directions: Mix crabmeat, beaten egg yolks, crumbs and melted butter and all seasonings.
Blend thoroughly.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and turn into well greased casserole.
Place casserole in pan of water and bake in moderately hot oven, 375 for 25 -30 minutes.
May be served with sauce.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Add vinegar, raisins, coconut and nuts. Pour in melted oleo.
Mix well and bake 40 to 50 minutes in unbaked pie shell in a 300° oven.

title: pink punch
directions: Blend Kool-Aid and juices. Add 7-Up.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Combine hamburger, salt, pepper, garlic salt, onion and flour in a large skillet.
Cook until red is no longer visible in meat. Add soup and stir until hot.
Just before serving stir in mushrooms and sour cream and heat just long enough to warm through.
Serve with noodles.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked chicken and gravy
directions: Cook chicken and cut into small pieces. Combine mushrooms (drain), green chilies, cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup, sour cream and chicken in large bowl. Stir until ingredients are mixed. Spoon about 1 to 2 spoons into tortilla shell roll and place seam side down. Place remaining mixture on top of rolled tortillas. Top with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes (until cheese is well melted).

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and lightly flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Beat together margarine, oil and sugar in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in flavorings.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating well after each.
Stir in zucchini.
Pour into prepared pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake 55 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool on wire rack.
Cut into squares.
Frost with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: lemony cheesecake bars
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, pecans, sugar and melted butter. Reserve 1/3 c. and press remaining mixture into 13X9 pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 325 degrees.
Remove and cool on wire rack.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk.
Add eggs and beat until just combined.
Stir in lemon juice.
Carefully spoon mixture atop crust in pan.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean. Cool 1 hour.
Store in refrigerator.
Cut into bars to serve. Makes 24 bars.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix together and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Grease pan lightly with oil. Refrigerate 1 1/2 hours. Melt 12 ounce package chocolate chips and 4 tablespoons peanut butter; mix together. Spread over crust. Chill. Cut into bars.

title: frankfurter casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in water with salt for 10 minutes; drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until top is brown and veggies are done.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook desired amount of potatoes and a little chopped onion until very tender.
Drain partially, leaving a little potato water in bottom of pot.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add margarine.
In a small bowl, make a mixture of milk and cornstarch.
Pour over potatoes and leave on simmer or low until it begins to thicken. Add regular milk to make as thick or thin as you like it.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In a large soup pot, combine all ingredients except macaroni. Cover and bring to a boil.
Add macaroni.
Simmer until macaroni is tender.
Yield:
5 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Drain broccoli and place in baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour over broccoli.
Melt 1/2 stick butter and add 1 tube crushed Ritz crackers mixed for topping.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes.
I usually watch topping to determine when done.

title: pecan pie
directions: Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then turn to 350° for 35 minutes.

title: meatless chili
directions: Cook beans in crock-pot.
Drain all juice off.
Add the tomatoes, pepper, onion and chili powder.
Cook until pepper and onion are tender.

title: adabelle's enchiladas
directions: In skillet, fry hamburg, onions and chorizo.
Set aside and drain.

title: angel muffins
directions: Mix mayonnaise into flour.
Add milk; pour into 12 greased muffin cups.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Combine jello and boiling water. Cool. Add pineapple and blueberry pie mix. Pour into square pan.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms and remove stems.
Saute chopped stems and onions in 1/4 cup butter.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stuff caps.
Arrange on baking dish.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes.
Broil 2 minutes to brown.

title: cranberry party punch
directions: Boil water
and
sugar	for 3 minutes and cool. Add all other ingredients
and
store
in
refrigerator.	Just before serving, add one 2 liter bottle of 7-Up. Serves 40.

title: jenna's favorite homemade applesauce
directions: Peel apples and cut them into quarters. Remove the cores and seeds. Cut each quarter into half. Place apples into a saucepan and cover halfway with water. Cook on medium heat until tender. Mash them with a fork or use a blender. Put the apples back into the pan and add the sugar. Cover the apples with cinnamon. Cook on low heat for 3 minutes. Allow to cool a little.

title: trifle
directions: In a large glass bowl place a layer of yellow cake (slightly stale), crumbled.
Next, place a layer of vanilla pudding, next a layer of crushed strawberries and a layer of Cool Whip.
Continue layering in the same order until bowl is filled, ending with a layer of Cool Whip.
Decorate with strawberries and mint leaves.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Boil hen with enough water to cover and season with salt and pepper. Cover and cook over medium fire until tender.
Remove from fire; debone. Cover and set aside.
Mix light bread, corn bread, onion and celery together with some boiling hot broth.
Let set until broth is absorbed.
Stir well and add eggs. Add enough broth until medium soupy.
Taste now for seasoning and add salt and pepper as needed.
Place 1/2 of the dressing in a 13 x 9-inch pan and top with the hen.
Top with remaining dressing. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 60 minutes.
Bake only until slightly firm.
Unused broth can be used for giblet gravy, dumplings, soup or frozen for later.

title: chicken vegetable casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts and cut up into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix up all other ingredients in greased casserole dish. Can add some chicken broth, if needed.
Melt butter and mix with bread crumbs for a topping.
Cover with lid or foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Remove cover for the last 10 minutes to brown.

title: deep fried cheese bits
directions: Cut cheese into bite-size cubes.
Dip each cube in flour, cream and then bread crumbs.
Repeat.
(Be sure to have a heavy coat of bread crumbs, otherwise the cheese will leak out during cooking.)
Heat oil (about 2-inches deep) in fondue pot and cook cubes until golden brown.

title: ritz cracker bake
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients together until stiff.
Mix next 3 ingredients together with beaten egg white mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown; cool.
Spread with Cool Whip; top with cherry pie filling.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients together except peanut butter.
Place over low flame and add peanut butter.
Heat until peanut butter melts.
Stir until well blended.
Grease spray a small baking pan. Spoon mixture into pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Slice into at least 15 squares.

title: chicken ball ragout
directions: In a large pot add chicken and all of the above ingredients. Cover chicken with water and boil until chicken falls apart. Remove chicken and let cool.

title: fruit sauce
directions: Put all ingredients into large kettle and simmer until thickened.
Stir often (will burn easily).
Bottle.

title: baked squash casserole with sour cream
directions: Boil squash and onion in small amount of water until tender. Drain.
Add seasonings and sour cream.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 325°
until heated throughout.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put rice in greased baking dish.
Pour boiling water over rice and stir.
Add salt; mix well.
Spread chicken on top of rice mix. In separate bowl, combine soups and 1/2 cup water and blend until smooth.
Pour over chicken.
Add pepper to taste.
Cut stick of butter and dot on top.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours covering the first hour.

title: bacon pecan chive finger sandwiches
directions: Cut the crust off all slices of bread.	Keep bread in bag until sandwich spread is ready.
Put mayonnaise in bowl and add chives, bacon bits and pecan pieces.
Mix well.
Spread onto 2 slices of bread.
Put slices of bread together and cut into 4 triangle finger sandwiches.
Place on serving platter.
Cover sandwiches with cold wet paper towels as they are being made so the bread won't dry out.
When all finger sandwiches are made, keep covered with cold, wet paper towels.
Cover with Saran Wrap over the wet towels.
Chill sandwiches for 1 to 2 hours before serving.
Keep wrapped until you are ready to eat them.
Makes ninety-six 1/4 finger sandwiches.

title: egg nog
directions: Mix together with 6 cups milk (whole or skim) in the order listed.
One half pint brandy or rum can be added if desired.

title: brownies
directions: Mix together and spread on well-greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, until dry on top and almost firm.

title: chicken and spaghetti di napoli
directions: In medium skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove, crumble and set aside.
In same skillet, brown chicken in 2 tablespoons drippings; remove.
Cook carrot and garlic until tender.
Add pasta sauce and chicken.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.

title: berried delight
directions: Mix and press first 3 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Cover casserole dish with dried beef.
Wrap strip bacon around each breast.
Place chicken in casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Do not add salt.
Cook uncovered 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 300°.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: joe froggers
directions: In a large bowl, stir together flour, spices and salt.
In a small bowl, combine rum and water.
In another small bowl, stir together the molasses and soda.
In another large bowl, cream the sugar and butter.
Then beat in 1/2 of the dry ingredients, 1/2 of the rum mixture and then 1/2 of the molasses.
Repeat until all ingredients are thoroughly mixed.
Chill dough several hours or overnight.
Roll out on well floured surface to 1/4-inch thick. Cut with 4-inch cookie cutter or 1 pound coffee can.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes, then remove to cooling rack.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.

Add a layer of cracker crumbs. Dot with butter. Place a layer of asparagus, then a layer of grated cheese, then a layer of sliced hard-cooked eggs and pimento strips, a layer of mushroom soup, then another layer of cracker crumbs.
Alternate as listed until casserole is filled.
Save enough cheese to make top layer.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until topping is brown.

title: oven french toast
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Add sugar and salt to unbeaten egg in shallow dish and stir until well mixed.
Stir in milk and oil.
Dip bread in mixture and place in well-greased large cookie sheet or jelly roll pan.
Bake until brown, about 10 minutes.
This is much easier than frying in deep fat and not nearly as fattening.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apricot gelatin salad
directions: Do not drain pineapple or oranges.
Dissolve gelatin with hot water.
Add fruit.
Chill until slightly firm.
Stir in sour cream.
Oil mold and pour into mold.
Chill overnight.
Serves 12.

title: spanish cream
directions: Soak gelatine in 1/2 cup milk.
Scald remaining milk in double boiler.
Pour slowly on egg yolks, beaten with sugar.
Add salt. Return to double boiler.
Cook until thick.
Remove from stove. Add gelatine mixture and egg whites, beaten stiff.
Refrigerate. Serve with whipped cream.

title: hot 'n' gooey chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9-inch tube or Bundt pan, shaking out excess flour.
Beat oil, eggs and sugar with electric mixer on medium speed until light and lemon colored. Sift flour with cocoa, baking powder and baking soda.
Add to egg mixture, alternately with milk and vanilla.
Beat at low speed until blended.
Pour into prepared pan and bake about 1 hour or until center tests done.
Cool in pan 10 to 20 minutes before inverting on a serving platter.
Serve warm with sauce and whipped cream, if desired.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: italian sausage and peppers on a roll
directions: Saute sausage in 1 tablespoon olive oil prickling sausage to release fat.
After browned, drain off fat from sausage; add sliced onion, green pepper, tomatoes and salt, pepper and garlic powder as desired.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve on hard crust roll.

title: baked scallops
directions: Rinse scallops; put in a glass baking dish.
Crush crackers in a bag.
Add parsley and pepper.
Sprinkle over scallops. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: ricotta cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add lemon and Ricotta and beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and pinch of salt; beat.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: mandarin chicken salad
directions: Drain fruit and mix all ingredients; toss.
May use 1 cup cooked rice instead of macaroni rings.
Serve on lettuce, if desired.

title: eye of round roast
directions: Pat dry soup mix on roast or mix with canned soup before pouring over roast in oven roaster.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours.
If roast is under 3 pounds, check earlier.
May cook in crock-pot for 8 to 10 hours.
Serve sliced with gravy.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Add taco seasoning and refried beans; mix well.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer hamburger mixture on the bottom.
Layer sour cream over mixture.
Add lettuce, tomatoes, onion and cheese.
Chill 1 hour and serve.
Great for parties!

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix sweet potatoes, pineapple, pecans, sugar, cream, vanilla, nutmeg, cinnamon, and butter together thoroughly.
Place in a medium size baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Top with marshmallows immediately.

title: herb butter blend
directions: Crush herbs.
Blend with 1 cup margarine.
Cover and chill 4 hours or more.
Garlic may be added for a different blend.
Serve on potatoes, corn-on-the-cob, hot bread, etc.
Also nice on croutons.
Prepared blend can be frozen.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until the potatoes are soft. Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla.

title: best chocolate fudge
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan, mix the sugar, butter, marshmallow cream and milk.
Bring to a bubbling, quick boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce to medium heat when bubbles appear all over the top; stir 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and add the chocolate pieces.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted and blended into mixture.
Add the vanilla and the nuts.
Pop into greased pan.
Cool thoroughly.
Makes approximately 2 1/4 pounds.

title: easy no-crust coconut pie
directions: Beat milk, eggs and vanilla together.
Add to flour and sugar; mix, then add margarine and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 greased pie pans.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Makes its own crust.
Very good!

title: christmas toffee
directions: Spray a 11 x 13-inch cookie sheet.
Combine margarine and sugar; bring to a boil.
Stir constantly until dark tan, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Pour toffee mixture onto cookie sheet. Immediately place broken pieces of chocolate bars on hot mixture and spread.
Cool or refrigerate.
Break into pieces when hard.

title: lemon bars
directions: Sift flour and sugar.
Cut into butter until mixture is like meal. Press firmly into greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: easy buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix together the dry ingredients.
Mix together the wet ingredients.
Add together and mix with a wire whisk.
Cook as usual.
These taste so much better than the boxed pancake mix.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit on paper towel; cut in half.
Arrange the fruit in two 3-quart casserole dishes, topping with cherries.
Combine melted margarine, brown sugar and curry powder and pour over fruit.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 25.

title: overnight salad
directions: Layer as listed.
Top with mayonnaise.
Refrigerate overnight. Toss and serve.
May also add grated carrots and/or green frozen peas (uncooked).

title: fruit skillet cake
directions: Blend cake mix, fruit liquid and egg.
Preheat an 11-inch iron skillet, then melt shortening in it.
Pour cake batter into the skillet.
Partly cover and cook over low heat for about 15 to 20 minutes until top of cake is dry to the touch.
Uncover; add drained fruit.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Keep warm until serving time.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mushroom appetizers
directions: Saute the first 2 ingredients in butter for 2 minutes. Take off heat. Season with salt and pepper. Add the cream cheese. Stir into mixture until melted and smooth. Add Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and Tabasco. Set aside for 1 hour.

title: marinated tri tip
directions: Liberally sprinkle tri-tip with Pappy's seasoning.
Pierce with fork.
Pour beer over tri-tip.
Place in plastic bag and seal for 1 hour.
Remove and barbecue for approximately 45 minutes at 140°.
Baste often with marinade.
Serves 4.

title: donna's sweet potato balls
directions: Cream together, then roll around marshmallows (large ones). Then roll in coconut. Place on baking sheet and bake in a 375° oven until marshmallows swell.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Make a white cake mix according to package directions, but add 3 tablespoons creme de menthe.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
When cool, top with 1 pound can of Hershey's fudge toping which has been opened and set in a pan of boiling water for 10 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip to which you've added and folded in 3 more tablespoons of creme de menthe.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon bars
directions: Cut butter into 2 cups flour and powdered sugar until mixture clings together.
Press into 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Beat together eggs, sugar, lemon juice and peel.
Add remaining 1/4 cup flour and baking powder.
Pour over baked crust.
Bake at 350° another 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with additional powdered sugar.

title: mexican appetizers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread cream cheese along sides and bottom of a 10-inch pie plate.
Layer chili, onion, green pepper and green chilies in order given on top of cream cheese.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with Doritos or Tostitos.
Can be assembled 1 day ahead.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Add the soda and vanilla; pour over popcorn.
Spread on 2 cookie sheets.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
(I usually make more than 6 quarts of popcorn, making sure the popcorn is nicely covered.)

title: grandma's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in loaf pan; drizzle with ketchup on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: spicy pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add the oil, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until thick and foamy.
With spoon, stir in zucchini and pineapple. Combine flour (unsifted), baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and nuts.
Divide into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
You can add dates.
This bread is not dry.

title: pumpkin ice cream
directions: Combine ingredients in order given, folding in whipped cream carefully.
Pour into freezing tray and freeze in refrigerator until firm.
Serves 6.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Break up pretzels with rolling pin.
Mix with melted butter and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch cake pan for 8 minutes in 400° oven.
Let cool completely.
Cream together cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread onto cooled pretzel crust.
Pour 2 cups boiling water into jellos.
Stir, then add frozen berries, again, stirring.
Let set 15 minutes (outside refrigerator) before pouring over creamed mixture.
Now chill. (May be used as dessert, also.)

title: elephant stew
directions: Wash elephant and cut into bite size pieces. This process will take approximately 2 months.
Place in a very large pot and cover with gravy.
Cook slowly over a kerosene bonfire at 275° until tender.

title: chocolate pound cake glaze
directions: Melt chocolate bar and Crisco over low heat.
Beat sugar into mixture until enough sugar is added for somewhat thin spreading consistency.
Add salt and vanilla.
Spread quickly over cake before glaze hardens.
Hint:
add more sugar to thicken, add hot water to thin mixture.

title: oriental chicken and green beans
directions: In small bowl, combine 2 teaspoons soy sauce with the cornstarch; add chicken and toss to coat.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Set aside.
Beat egg yolks slightly and combine with shortening, corn, sugar, flour, milk and seasonings.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until it sets like a custard (about 45 minutes).
Serves 4 to 6.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream together oil and sugar; add egg and beat well.
Sift together flour, soda, cloves, cinnamon and salt.
Add to shortening mixture.
Then stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand until cool. Remove from pan and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: mexican rice casserole
directions: Cook rice by package directions.
Brown hamburger meat.
Mix all ingredients, but save 1/4 cheese for top.
Put in casserole dish.
Cook at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; add cheese to top.
Put back in oven for about 9 minutes.

title: onion and egg casserole
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Scramble eggs.
Pour into baking dish. Take onions and make them into rings.
Put rings into eggs.
Pour in soup.
Cover with pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: old-fashioned beef stew
directions: Coat beef with flour, shaking off excess.
In a
large nonstick pot, heat oil over medium heat. Add beef.
Saute until brown, about 6 minutes.
Place on a plate.
Add onion and mushrooms to pot.
Saute for 6 minutes. Add garlic and saute, stirring for 1 minute.
Pour off fat. Return beef to pot. Stir in tomato paste, then broth. Add enough water to cover. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low.
Simmer until beef is tender, about 1 1/4 hours. Skim off any foam.
Add carrots, potatoes and green beans.
Cover partially. Simmer 15 minutes.
In a small bowl, mix cornstarch and cold water. Stir into stew. Increase heat and boil, uncovered, 1 minute. Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: garlic corn fritters
directions: In medium-size bowl, stir together flour, cornmeal, baking powder, salt, sugar and red pepper.
Add milk, egg and butter. Stir until combined.
Fold in corn and garlic.

title: orange rice
directions: I prefer brown rice by Uncle Ben's.
In hot oil or butter in saucepan, cook celery and onion until tender, but not brown.
Add water, orange rind, juice, salt and thyme.
Bring to boil slowly. Add rice.
Cook covered over low heat 25 minutes or until tender.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Heat the butter, brown sugar and molasses together over low heat in a medium sized saucepan until the butter is liquid and the sugar has dissolved.
Cool.
Beat in the confectioners sugar and the heavy cream alternately, a little at a time, until the frosting is just smooth and thick enough to spread.
Makes 3 cups.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar well; set aside.
Bring to a boil the next 4 ingredients and boil 1 minute; stir.
Pour this over flour and sugar mixture.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla; mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Grease and flour pan.)

title: gma baker's cookies(molasses cookies)
directions: Melt shortening slowly in large Pyrex bowl (microwave).
Remove from heat and let cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg; beat well. Sift flour, soda, cloves, ginger, cinnamon and salt together.
Add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Chill.
Form into 1-inch balls; roll in granulated sugar and place on greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: quiche new mexico
directions: Sprinkle bacon bits on bottom of each pie shell. Mix together remaining bacon bits with the rest of the ingredients.
Pour half of this mixture into each pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown and knife inserted comes out clean.
Serves 12.

title: pink party dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in boiling water.
Cool; add strawberries and stir until almost thawed.
Chill until quite thick.
Cut cake into 1-inch square cubes.
Mix with Jell-O.
Mix and pour into large Pyrex dish and chill until firm.
Mix 3 ounces strawberry Jell-O according to directions.
Chill until syrupy and pour over cake, Jell-O and strawberries.
This makes a smoother top.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Mix well. Add cocoa, sugar and vanilla.
Mix until lumps are out by kneading with a spatula.
Press in 8-inch square buttered pan. Refrigerate about 20 to 30 minutes or until set.

title: aunt nellie's creme de menthe pie
directions: Crust:
Roll cookies into crumbs.
Add melted butter and mix well.
Pat into greased 8-inch pie dish (save some crumbs to sprinkle over top of pie).
Chill 20 minutes.

title: beef roast
directions: Mix onion soup mix and cream of mushroom soup. Pour over roast and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Put peeled carrots and potatoes in for the last 45 minutes. Cover while cooking.
(For larger roast, add another can of soup.)

title: peaches 'n' cream dessert
directions: Make crust of butter and cracker crumbs, reserving 1/2 cup for top.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: damson preserves
directions: Wash, drain, seed and chop Damsons.
Then measure.
Add water and sugar.	Bring to boil.	Cook to jellying point.
Put into hot jars and seal at once.
I always seed my Damsons.
I test the juice in a saucer and when it gets as thick as I want it, I put into jars.	I like the juice to jell.
My favorite!

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix well the oleo, sugar and powdered sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, then oil, flour, cream of tartar, vanilla and salt.
Mix well, then chill.
Make into balls.
Press with glass dipped in sugar to flatten balls. Bake at 325° to 350° until golden brown. Makes 5 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: mexican black-eyed peas
directions: Crumb and crown sausage.
Add onion and garlic.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 1 hour.

title: lobster stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wipe
mushroom
caps with damp cloth.
In a large bowl, combine
crumbs,
garlic,
parsley, paprika and melted butter. Add coarsely
chopped
lobster meat.
Stuff caps and place in buttered baking dish.
Bake at 425° until heated through for 8 to 10
minutes.
Serve
with lemon wedges and a sprinkling of chopped parsley.

title: homemade pimento cheese
directions: Chop pimentos and mix with cheese, mustard and mayonnaise. Allow to sit at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Then put in refrigerator.
Keeps for a week.

title: fried catfish
directions: You will also need 2 large brown paper grocery bags.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Add onion and cook with sausage.
Add seasonings.
Melt cheese with sausage mixture. Spread on party rye.
Bake at 400° for 9 minutes.
May be frozen and baked layer.

title: sausage-cheese dip
directions: Cook sausage; drain off grease. Add softened cream cheese and tomatoes. Eat with nacho chips.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Separate eggs; set whites aside.
Beat Crisco, margarine and sugar really good; add egg yolks and beat thoroughly.
Add flavoring; beat well.
Add milk and flour alternately until all is beaten in.
Add coconut; beat well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours in a large tube pan.
Do not open oven door while cake is baking.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Lightly brown the meat.
Add the onion and cook until tender. Add seasonings, beans and soup.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mash hot potatoes.
Add the milk and egg and season.
Drop in mounds over the meat mixture.
If desired, sprinkle 1/2 cup shredded process cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pie shell
directions: Combine flour and salt. Cut shortening into dry ingredients until mixture resembles corn meal. Add ice water, one tablespoon at a time.
Stir with fork.
Form into a ball.
Place on lightly floured surface and roll from center to edge until 1/8-inch thick. Makes one 9-inch pie shell.

title: easy swiss steak
directions: Pound steak; cut in small pieces.
Brown steak; pour off fat. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover; simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbage and onion and steam together in a small amount of water about 5 or 6 minutes.
Drain dry.
Fry bacon and set aside. Drain bacon grease and use same skillet to mix soup (undiluted) and Cheez Whiz.
Heat on low flame.
In a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish, put half of cabbage and onion mixture.
Crumble bacon slices on top.
Pour half of cheese mixture over cabbage.
Put the rest of cabbage and pour the balance of cheese mixture over top.
Put in a preheated 375° oven and bake until it starts to bubble.

title: hoe cakes
directions: Beat egg; add remaining ingredients in order and beat until smooth.
Grease griddle.
Pour batter onto griddle.
Turn when puffed and full of bubbles.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with bacon.
Mix sour cream and mushroom soup together.
Spread over breasts.
Bake covered at 275° for about 2 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake another 1/2 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken, vegetables and noodles or rice in layers in baking dish.
Make white sauce with the butter, flour, milk and dry dressing mix.
Pour over ingredients in casserole; bake until heated through well.

title: ricotta fruit dip
directions: In a blender container or food processor bowl, combine the Ricotta cheese, powdered sugar, orange and lemon juices and vanilla.
Cover and blend or process until smooth.
Stir into the yogurt.
If desired, cover and chill up to 24 hours.
Serve with berries, melon and other fruit.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sugar-free banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions, decreasing milk by 1/2 cup per package.
After pudding is cooked, stir in vanilla extract.
(For richer flavor, use 1 cup milk and 1/2 cup canned evaporated milk per package.)
In large casserole dish, layer vanilla wafers, then banana slices, then 1/2 of pudding; repeat layers.
Beat egg whites with 2 to 3 packets Equal sweetener, to taste.
Pile meringue on top of pudding, spread to edge of pan.
Bake in hot (400°) oven very briefly, until meringue browns lightly.
Refrigerate.

title: homemade bread
directions: Mix warm water, sugar and yeast.
Let stand 5 minutes. Add Crisco, milk and 5 cups flour.
If needed, use 1 cup flour to roll out.
Mix all ingredients. Roll out on floured board until smooth. Cut or form with hand and place on greased pan.
Bake at 350° until brown. Do not let rise in oven. Store in plastic bag in refrigerator.

title: the philadelphia experiment
directions: Crumble the biscuits (rub them through a sieve), then make a base by mixing them well with 150 grams melted butter.
Press the base well in a buttered cake form (12-inch).
Keep 2 tablespoons for later.

title: honey bunch's batty cakes
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Add milk to desired consistency, not too thick, not too thin.
Cook in hot skillet or on hot griddle using a little bacon grease.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in boiling water.
Add all remaining ingredients and chill.

title: bryan's peanut butter fudge
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan, combine powdered sugar and milk with wire whip.
Place on medium heat and bring to a hard boil. Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Pour into a buttered dish and let cool. Cut into 1-inch squares.
Enjoy!

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix cake mix, jello, nectar and oil together.
Add salt and vanilla; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: summer frosted salad
directions: Combine fruits and place in a serving bowl or individual servings.
Combine sour cream and marshmallows and spoon over fruit.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: irene's coffee cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix together flour, baking powder and salt to be used later. Using a mixer, cream together shortening and sugar in mixing bowl.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately (flour 4 times, milk 3 times) until thoroughly mixed.
Add vanilla last.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Blend sugars, eggs and butter until creamy. Add pinto beans and blend well. Pour into deep unbaked pie shell. Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes, then at 350° for 25 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean. Delicious; tastes like pecan pie. Serve with Cool Whip. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: retired baked potatoes
directions: Add green onion dip mix to sour cream and spoon onto your baked potatoes.
Easy and good.

title: mexican breakfast
directions: Beat eggs at high speed of mixer until thick, about 10 minutes. Combine flour, baking powder, salt and celery salt. Gradually add flour mixture to eggs, beating at low speed just until dry ingredients are moistened. Add cheese.
Pour 1/2 cup batter into lightly buttered warm skillet.
Turn when brown and bake the other side. Serve 3 puffs for each person and cover with the warm sauce. Serves 4.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in olive oil over medium heat in skillet until tender.
Add rice, stirring, until it turns a whitish gold, about 3 or 5 minutes.
Add chicken broth, tomato sauce, cumin, pepper and salt.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low and simmer uncovered for 20 minutes or until rice is done.

title: banana peanut butter bread
directions: Mash the bananas with a fork.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Pour into a buttered 8 1/4 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour in preheated oven at 325°.
Keeps well in the refrigerator.
Freezes beautifully.

title: icesicles
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add Kool-Aid, cold water and sugar.
Mix and pour into popsicle molds and freeze.

title: calico (cabbage) salad
directions: Shred cabbage and carrots; slice onion thinly or chop.
Mix dressing in jar and mix well (lemon juice, oil and seasonings). Pour dressing over cabbage mixture.

title: candied cranberries
directions: Spread berries in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar. Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger in a large skillet.
Add salt, pepper, chili powder and paprika while your hamburger browns, then add your onion and tomato soup.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 1 hour.

title: southern frankfurter dinner
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Add frankfurters and tomatoes.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Prepare corn muffin batter as directed on package and spoon over frankfurter mixture.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli and corn casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
In a casserole dish, alternate layers of broccoli, corn, cheese, cracker crumbs and a few pats of butter.
Repeat same layer pattern starting with broccoli and ending with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Boil briskly for 5 minutes the raisins and water.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add eggs. Sift flour, cinnamon, baking powder and salt.
Mix all ingredients together and add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: round steak sauerbraten
directions: In a skillet, brown meat and remove.
Put remaining ingredients in skillet and bring to a boil.
Add meat.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over hot buttered noodles.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: cookie bars
directions: Cream butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; gradually beat into creamed mixture.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Spread batter in greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely; cut into bars.

title: summer fruitcake
directions: Roll graham crackers with rolling pin until very fine.
Add cherries, which have been cut in thirds.
Add raisins, nuts and condensed milk.
Mix all well; put in wax paper.
Roll to make one long roll.
Place in icebox.
The next day, cut the size desired.

title: meat ball sub
directions: Form into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet to bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn after 15 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar with eggs.
Stir in bread cubes and pineapple.
Pour into greased casserole dish (8 x 8-inch).
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes until lightly brown.

title: million dollar cookies
directions: Cream butter and both sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
(You will probably have to use your hands because the mixture will be thick and dry.
Very small portions of water may be dribbled into the mixture to help with the blending.)
Roll into balls and place 2-inches apart on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Makes approximately 100 cookies.

title: baked cruschiki
directions: Beat eggs; add sour cream and mix well.
Put butter in flour; mix until crumbly.
Put beaten eggs and sour cream.
Add vanilla; stir all together.
If sticky, add flour.
Refrigerate 3 hours. Roll out 1/4-inch.
Cut into strips 1 1/2-inches wide and 2 inches long.
Bake at 375° or 400° approximately 7 minutes or until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar; store in tins.

title: busy day chicken
directions: Scatter rice on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay chicken on top of rice, skin side up.
Combine soup, water and onion soup mix.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: sue's mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients as listed.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: party hors d'oeuvres
directions: Early in day or day before, blend deviled ham, pretzels, Worcestershire sauce and pepper. Form into 25 balls using a rounded half teaspoonful.
Arrange on cookie sheet and freeze for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, work cream cheese with fork until soft. Roll each ball first in 1 tablespoon soft cream cheese to cover, then in snipped chives.
Refrigerate until served.
Serve on colored picks.

title: basic cake recipe
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add vanilla.
Add flour and milk alternately until all is used.
Bake in 3 greased and floured cake pans.
(I use 8-inch pans.)
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until done.
Frost with your favorite icing.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix together the crushed pretzels and margarine.
Press in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Cool completely.

title: orange salad
directions: Place jello in 2-quart bowl.
Add drained crushed pineapple and cut up, drained mandarin oranges.
Stir well, coating pineapple and oranges.
Stir in cottage cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add marshmallows and stir until mixed.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, bacon, onion and cheese.
Mix together the mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over broccoli mixture and toss.

title: chinese stir-fry
directions: Brown up the meat in frying pan.
Add the vegetables and everything except the stock and starch.
Cover and simmer until the vegetables are done.

title: jalapeno pepper relish
directions: Put peppers in blender with vinegar.
Use about a 7-quart pan; put sugar and pepper mixture in and bring to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes and take off stove.
Add Certo.
Boil 1 minute longer. Let stand 2 to 4 minutes, then pour into jars.
Makes approximately 6 to 7 jars.

title: larry's chop suey
directions: Cut meat in small cubes.
Braise until brown.
Cover and simmer until done.
Slice a small onion and braise until transparent.
Cut 1 medium stalk of celery and fry until brown. Put in kettle.
Add 2 cans bean sprouts and juice and 1 tablespoon brown sugar with 1/2 bottle soy sauce.
Bring to boil and thicken with cornstarch.
Cook until transparent.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Mix soups, broth and all but a small amount of stuffing.
Place half of mixture over chicken, then add another layer of chicken, topped with soup and stuffing mix.
Sprinkle with remaining stuffing. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: layered bean dip
directions: In a medium bowl, mix refried beans, green chilies and taco seasoning mix.
Spread on 12-inch platter.

title: ridpath roof salad
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in a small bowl.
Mix oil and olive oil in blender.
Slowly add vinegar, then add dressing from small bowl.
Chill.

title: banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, mix instant pudding with 2 cups cold milk until pudding gets stiff.
Fold in Eagle Brand milk.
Fold in Cool Whip which has been defrosted (don't add frozen) until well blended.

title: layered oreo delight
directions: Butter a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex pan.
Crush Oreos in blender until powdery.
Remove 1/2 cup crumbs and set aside.
Mix remaining crumbs with butter.
Press onto bottom and up sides of the glass pan.

title: apple salad
directions: Use apple slicer to core apples; cut into 1/2 inch chunks. Add pineapple, grapes, marshmallows.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Chop or grind apples and put the tomatoes through grinder. Add the rest of ingredients; cook slowly for 3 hours.
Put in cans and seal.
Makes 15 pints.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture. Stir in nuts and chips. Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, until light brown. Makes 6 dozen.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Mix the corn and soup with the rice. Put into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Put in oven only until hot.

title: wes' chili with beans
directions: In large pot or Dutch oven, lightly brown hamburger, sausage and turkey over medium heat.
Drain and add onions, onion soup mix, celery and tomato items.
Bring to a slow boil; add remainder of spices and bring back to boil.
Cook for about 45 minutes at a slow boil.
Add 1 quart water and all beans.
Bring back to boil, cover and continue to cook slowly for 4 to 6 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot with crackers and fresh corn bread.
Makes about 2 gallons.

title: "janice's" baked chicken
directions: Mix 1/2 can soup, broth and eggs.
Toss with stuffing.
Spread in baking dish.
Sprinkle chicken on top.
Mix remaining soup and milk.
Pour on top of chicken.
Sprinkle pimentos on top of this. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove cover the last 10 minutes.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix and bake in greased pan for 45 to 50 minutes at 300°.
Do not open oven door for 30 minutes.

title: cube steak and mushroom gravy
directions: Flour cube steak.
Brown on both sides.
Remove steak.	Pour soup into steak drippings.	Add water and stir until well blended. Put steak back into pan.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes. This is also delicious when cooked in a crock-pot on low for several hours.

title: vegetable casserole(great low-fat recipe)
directions: Combine all ingredients except breadcrumbs, butter, 1/4 c. cheese and 1 tsp.
Italian seasoning.
Transfer to a casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with remaining cheese.
Combine breadcrumbs and remaining Italian seasoning and sprinkle on top.
Drizzle butter over top.
Cover dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in 4-quart saucepan, saute onions until tender (about 15 minutes).
Stir in flour and salt, add water and beef stock base, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir in milk.
Heat to serving temperature.
(Do not boil.)

title: lasagne
directions: Cook beef until crumbly and lightly browned.
Blend in mushrooms and liquid, tomato sauce and paste, oregano and water. Simmer 15 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Arrange one layer of graham crackers in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine next three ingredients in bowl. Mix well. Spread 1/2 mixture over graham crackers. Add a second layer of crackers and remaining pudding mixture. Top with third layer of crackers.
Spread with a chocolate icing.
Chill for 6 hours or longer. Serves 12.

title: tomato bisque with croutons and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place bread slices on heavy large cookie sheet.
Brush both sides of bread with oil.
Bake until golden brown, about 10 minutes; cool.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Heat oil, garlic and onions; cook to tender, then add pork and beans, kidney beans, lima beans, brown sugar, white sugar, vinegar, ketchup, mustard, salt and pepper.
Mix all together.
Cook or bake at 350° covered 30 minutes.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Put chips in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes and chicken together.
Pour on top of chips and grate cheese on top.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: baked pork chops
directions: You will need a plate and a pan.

title: robert redford cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, pecans and butter and press into baking pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Rinse mushrooms quickly and wipe with a damp towel.
Combine the above ingredients and pour over the mushrooms.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 12 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar together and set aside. Mix all other ingredients together. Add mayonnaise mixture. Mix well. Refrigerate overnight. Toss before serving.

title: cinnamon peanut cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Have cookie sheets ready.
Mix flour, salt and cinnamon.
Put remaining ingredients into a large bowl.
Beat with electric mixer until well blended.
Gradually add flour mixture, beating just until blended.
Drop heaping teaspoon 1 1/2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350° until lightly golden.
Do not overbake.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Can be pressed with a fork dipped in sugar for a crisper cookie.

title: ham and cheese crescent sandwiches
directions: Beat eggs and grated cheese together (add a little salt and pepper). Pat one pack of rolls on bottom of cookie sheet. Put in layers: ham, Genoa salami, Swiss cheese and Provolone cheese. Pour egg mixture on top of Provolone cheese, leaving some to brush on top. Then place 2nd pack of rolls on top. Pinch edges together. Brush remaining egg mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until rolls are lightly browned. Cut into sandwiches.

title: corn dog bites
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine oil, egg and buttermilk; stir into flour mixture, mixing well.
Cut each hot dog into 5 pieces.
Dip each piece into batter, coating completely (use toothpicks to aid in dipping).
Pour oil 3 to 4 inches in Dutch oven.
Heat to medium to medium-high heat.
Fry pieces until golden, turning once; drain on paper towels.
Serve with mustard and/or catsup.

title: tuna salad
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Mix tuna, celery, eggs and pimento with noodles.
Mix salad dressing mix with mayonnaise and buttermilk according to directions on package.
Mix salad dressing with other mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: easy macaroons
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing well.
Drop from teaspoon 1 inch apart on well-greased baking sheet.
Decorate with sprinkles or sugar crystals.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove at once using a moistened spatula.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: barbecue roast
directions: Sprinkle roast with salt and pepper and rub with 2 tablespoons brown sugar. Place in a Dutch oven and add 2 cups water. Cook, partially covered, over low heat 2 hours or until tender. Remove roast and shred. Bring remaining 2 tablespoons brown sugar, ketchup and next 8 ingredients to a boil in a heavy saucepan. Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until thickened. Stir in shredded roast. Serve on hamburger buns. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: veggie bars
directions: For Crust:
Pat crescent rolls into jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk, following the directions on the box. In your serving dish, place a large spoonful of pudding; spread thinly.
Place a layer of Nilla wafers, then a layer of banana slices and cover with 1/2 of the pudding.
Repeat cookies, bananas and pudding.
Just before serving, top with Cool Whip.

title: overnight breakfast casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole in the following order: bread cubes, cooked sausage, green pepper, mushrooms and cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk and salt and pepper and pour over layers.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Mix boned chicken, Ro-Tel tomatoes, soups and 1/2 bag of the Doritos in a large bowl.
Add broth of chicken, if needed.
Put the other half bag Doritos in bottom of a large baking dish.
Pour chicken mixture on top of Doritos in dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for approximately 50 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Put in oven until cheese melts and serve.

title: welsh cookies
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients.
Add shortening (like pie crust); crumble, then add remaining ingredients.
Roll 1/8-inch thick (mix sugar and flour to roll).
Cut out and bake on griddle on low.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Using a 2-quart baking dish, make a crust of biscuits.
Brown and drain ground beef.
Mix together ground beef, onion, mushrooms, parsley, salt, pepper and oregano.
Cook over medium heat.
When done, stir in egg and layer on top of biscuits.
Then mix cheeses, eggs, sour cream and half and half.
Layer on top of beef mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until brown. Serve hot.

title: banana freeze
directions: Thaw bananas slightly at room temperature 5 to 10 minutes, cut into pieces.
Place milk, milk powder, brown sugar and vanilla in blender.
With blender on low speed; add frozen banana pieces processing until fruit begins to blend into mixture.
Increase speed to high and process until smooth.
Garnish, if desired, and serve immediately.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: In a bowl, combine egg and 1/4 cup soup.
Stir in uncooked rice, onion, parsley flakes, salt and pepper.
Add beef; mix well. Shape meat mixture into approximately 20 small balls.

title: pumpkin pecan roll
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon color.
Add sugar, pumpkin and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and cinnamon.
Line 9 x 13 pan with wax paper.
Pour in pan and sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add cheese and flour and mix well.
In a greased 9 x 9-inch or 7 x 11-inch baking pan, layer the apples and the cheese mixture.
Cover top with cheese mixture. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until topping is lightly browned. Makes about 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat all ingredients vigorously with spoon. Pour batter in pan. Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean. Makes 1 loaf.

title: chestnut dressing
directions: Crisp chestnuts in hot oven, turning frequently with a spoon. Chop or grind.
Crumb the bread and add chopped chestnuts, celery, parsley, minced onion, seasonings, melted butter and hot water. Mix until well blended, adding the baking powder when about half mixed.
Fill fowl.

title: hilda's chicken
directions: Melt oleo in metal baking dish or 9 x 11-inch pan.
Brush chicken with mayonnaise and roll in dry dressing.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour 1 1/2 cups white wine over chicken.
Return to oven and bake 20 minutes more.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix the jello in the boiling water.
Mix until jello is dissolved.
Chill until it is the consistency of egg white.
Mix well the tuna, celery, relish, onion, cottage cheese and Miracle Whip.
When well mixed add to the jello and put in a salad mold.

title: old fashioned teacake
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift together flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Add to mixture. Add enough more flour to make dough you can handle.
Roll out and cut as you choose.
Bake at 375°.

title: tuna melts
directions: Combine 1/2 cup Cheez Whiz and mayonnaise.
Stir in tuna, water chestnuts and spread onto English muffin halves.
Place muffins on the unheated rack of a broiler pan.
Broil 4 inches from the heat until heated through.
Top each with a dollop of the remaining Cheez Whiz and broil for 30 to 60 seconds more or until Cheez Whiz melts.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Cook vegetables until very soft.
Drain.
Puree in blender with chicken stock.
Add sour cream.
Serve hot or cold.

title: fudgy toffee bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar and cocoa. Cut in cold butter until it resembles coarse crumbs. Press into 13 x 9-inch greased pan. Bake 10 minutes in 350° oven. Meanwhile, heat milk with chocolate chips and vanilla. Stir until smooth. Pour over the baked crust. Combine coconut, toffee bits and walnuts. Sprinkle over the top. Press firmly. Bake for 15 to 18 minutes or until light brown.

title: quick chicken tarragon
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
Brown chicken breast in large skillet on high heat in olive oil and butter.
