(When the oil and butter begins to turn brown, add the chicken.) Cook for 4 minutes on each side.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Serve over rice and steamed broccoli.

title: raisin sauce for ham
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together; slowly add vinegar, then add next 3 ingredients.
Use medium saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add 1/2 cup raisins and butter.

title: layered delight
directions: First Layer:
With hands thoroughly mix flour, margarine and pecans; spread on bottom of 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Press firmly for dough to only cover bottom of dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes and let cool.

title: lemon angel bars
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together
by
hand;
don't use a mixer. Coat
a
9 x 13-inch pan with a shortening spray.	Add mixture. Bake
in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.	Cool and frost.

title: tostada casserole
directions: Preheat oven at 375°.
Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain off fat.
Add 1 1/2 cups tomato sauce and the taco seasonings; mix well.
Line bottom of 2-quart flat casserole with 2 cups corn chips.
Crush remaining corn chips; set aside.
Spoon meat mixture over corn chips in baking dish.

title: oatmeal-chocolate cookies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together.
Add milk and butter.
Slowly cook to a thick boil (until ball forms in cold water).
Add oatmeal, vanilla and peanut butter; drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Let harden.

title: ginger chicken
directions: Cook chicken in vegetable oil with ginger (cut ginger into small pieces) and garlic salt.
Add onion and mushrooms and cook until done.
Add water chestnuts and pea pods and heat through. Add water and flour combined to make a thick sauce.
Add soy sauce. Serve with rice.

title: fish casserole
directions: Place fish in greased or Pam-sprayed casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
While baking, saute onion and garlic in butter.
Remove from heat and add Worcestershire sauce.
Blend with crumbs.
Drain the fish when cooked or put in another dish.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over fish; bake 10 or 15 minutes or until turning brown.

title: old fashioned oatmeal pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Combine the honey, eggs, oatmeal, coconut, brown sugar, butter or margarine, raisins and walnuts; mix well.
Pour into the pie shell and bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until the filling browns and a knife blade inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool before serving (with optional whipped cream).

title: chicken and vegetables(microwave)
directions: Combine celery, carrots, green pepper and zucchini.
Spread evenly over bottom of greased shallow microwave-safe baking dish. Arrange chicken pieces toward outside of dish.

title: aunt lucy's chicken sandwiches(serves 6)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat and serve.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: In skillet, melt butter and stir in garlic powder, lemon juice, salt and pepper, sherry and teriyaki sauce.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes, stirring frequently to blend ingredients.

title: quick cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat over to 450°.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a medium bowl.

Stir in Cheddar. Cut butter using a pastry blender, 2 knives, or a fork until coarse crumbs form. Using a fork, stir milk into flour mixture until a soft dough forms. Do not overmix or overwork the dough. Drop dough in heaping tablespoons 1 inch apart, onto an ungreased baking sheet. Bake about 15 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers thoroughly; pack into hot sterilized jars.
Put one pepper, 1 teaspoon dill seed and one piece garlic in each quart.
Place jars in pan of 1 to 2-inches of boiling water.
Mix water, vinegar and salt; bring to a boil.
Pour over cucumbers. Adjust lids and remove from boiling water.

title: cynthia's turkey enchiladas
directions: Add all ingredients to a saucepan.
Rinse each can with 1/2 can of water each and pour into pan.
Mix all ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Spoon mixture onto flour tortillas and serve with the following toppings:
shredded Cheddar cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, olives, sour cream and so on.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumbers; slice thin and put into a glass bowl.
Gently stir in all other ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: fudge pie
directions: Prick pie shell and cook 5 minutes.
Mix all ingredients; beat with mixer for 3
minutes and pour into prepared pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin crunch cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and mix with milk, sugar, pumpkin and spices.
Beat well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix and nuts over top of mixture.
Drizzle melted margarine over top.
Bake 1 hour until brown.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: bill's date nut bread
directions: Grease an 8 x 4 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake about 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: easy shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef.
In an 8 or 9-inch square baking dish, layer meat, corn (drained) and mashed potatoes.
Bake at 350° until heated through, about 45 minutes.
Also good with Velveeta melted over.

title: fruit and nut nibbles
directions: In medium mixing bowl mix granola, dried fruit, peanuts and chocolate pieces.
Store in container.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: chicken hawaiian
directions: In a saucepan cook green pepper with garlic in oil until tender.
Blend in soup and pineapple juice.
Add chicken, pineapple tidbits and soy sauce.
Heat, stirring now and then. Serve over rice.
Top with almonds. Serves 6.

title: apple muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in muffin pans at 350°. Makes 24 muffins.

title: peach cake
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup milk which has cooled to lukewarm. Add remaining milk, shortening, salt, sugar and egg.
Gradually add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Beat thoroughly.
Turn out on lightly floured board and knead until dough becomes elastic and does not stick to board.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk.
Take 1/2 dough.
Knead and roll into round piece about 1/2-inch thick.
Grease a round 9-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle bottom of pan lightly with brown sugar and line with sliced peaches, fresh or canned.
Over peaches, sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon.
Dot with butter.
Fit dough into pan on top of peach mixture and let rise
again until double in bulk.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil and cut chicken into small pieces.
Heat soup, broth and vegetables until boiling.
Place cooked chicken into an 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan.
Pour hot mixture over chicken.

title: chalapus
directions: Boil roast in water.
Cool and take fat off roast.
Cut into small pieces.
Add roast and dry beans to broth.
Add other ingredients and cook until tender.
Add more water as needed. Serve over corn chips.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and taco sauce.

title: bite size herb biscuits
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour, sugar and cream of tartar. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Make a well in center.
Add milk, onions and parsley.
Stir until dough clings together.
On a lightly floured surface, knead dough gently 10 to 12 times.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut dough with 1 1/2-inch cutter.
Cook on ungreased pan at 450° for 6 to 8 minutes. Half biscuits, then split halves.
Put filling in biscuits.
Makes 24 to 28 appetizers.

title: caramel apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs, add oil and vanilla.
Add apples. Combine flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add nuts, if desired. Pour batter into 13 x 9-inch pan or two 8-inch round pans, which have been sprayed with "Pam."
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: spaghetti sauce(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Finely dice onions, bell pepper and celery.
Saute in a small amount of oil until clear.
Drain well.
Brown ground beef, breaking up large chunks of meat.
Drain well.
Mix all ingredients in a large Dutch oven.
Simmer on low heat for as close to 10 hours as possible.
Before serving, remove garlic bulbs and bay leaves.
Serve over spaghetti noodles.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix the dry ingredients together in a large bowl. Add the eggs, buttermilk and oil and mix well. Store in covered container in refrigerator until ready to bake. Will keep up to six weeks or baked muffins will keep frozen up to six months.

title: peach sherbet
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in electric mixer to freeze ice cream sherbet.

title: quickie chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa and baking soda.
Add mayonnaise, cold water and vanilla.
Flour and grease a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Pour mixture into pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: homemade doughnuts
directions: Heat the oil in a large skillet.
Open the biscuit container and separate the biscuits.
Tear a hole in the center of each one. Place the biscuits in the hot oil for 2 minutes.
When the underside is browned, turn them over with a slotted spoon.
Brown the other side for 2 minutes.
Remove the doughnuts from the skillet and drain them on a paper towel.

(Oil that remains may be recycled by pouring back into the original container once it has cooled off.) Put the sugar and cinnamon in a large plastic bag. Add 2 cooked doughnuts into the bag and shake until they are coated.
Repeat until all doughnuts have been covered.

title: black bean soup
directions: Saute in pressure cooker the oil, onions, celery, garlic and rice.
Add everything but milk and pressure cook for 10 minutes. Cool under cold running water.
Blend milk powder with 1/2 cup of stock, then add to soup.

title: holiday boil(to give a holiday aroma to your house)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a stainless steel pan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for several hours.
Cover and leave on stove.
Reheat and simmer each day during the holidays.

title: miniature meat turnovers
directions: In medium skillet, combine soup, ground beef, sprouts, water chestnuts and onion; brown well.
Separate rolls as package directs.
Cut in half.
Place a spoonful of cooked mixture in the center of each triangle, fold over and seal edges.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes or until golden brown in 375° oven.
Makes 32 turnovers.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Add all the other ingredients.
Cover with crushed potato chips.
Cook at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cream cheese chive sauce
directions: Stir cream cheese and milk in saucepan over low heat until smooth.
Stir in chives, juice and garlic salt.
Serve over baked potatoes or vegetables.
Takes 5 minutes to make 1 1/3 cup serving.
Serve over potatoes.

title: easy cherry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix together flour, sugar and milk until smooth.
Pour batter evenly into pan.
Do not stir with butter.
Spoon pie filling over batter.
Bake 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients altogether.
Add bread crumbs.
Mix together and bake 45 minutes at 350° in greased casserole dish. Serve with ham.

title: little red beef loaves
directions: Mix ground beef, oatmeal, onion, parsley, 2 tablespoons mustard, salt, pepper, eggs and milk.
Mix well.
Form into small loaves, 1/2 to 3/4 cup size.
Place meat loaves in baking pan. Make finger length indentations on each and spoon piquant sauce over each.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hungry-jack casserole
directions: Cook hamburger meat.
Drain excess grease.
Add all other ingredients, except cheese and biscuits into a 2-quart dish.
Stir together.
Bake at 375° until hot.
Bake without biscuits.
When done, place cheese on casserole and add biscuits.

title: orange caf au lait slush
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 10 x 7-inch baking dish. Freeze 3 to 4 hours or until firm, stirring after every 30 minutes. Scoop slush into tall serving glasses. If desired, top with additional grated orange peel. Makes 6 servings.

title: 125 year old walnut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flavoring and beat.
Mix 1/4 cup flour with nuts.
Add remaining flour (with baking powder mixed in) alternately with milk, starting and ending with flour.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in large, greased and floured tube pan (Bundt pan preferred) for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.
Do not open oven during the first hour of baking.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well. Boil until soft ball stage. Remove from heat and add the peanut butter. Beat until thick and pour onto 2 buttered plates.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Mix ingredients.
Marinate meat 8 hours to overnight in refrigerator.
Cook over low heat on charcoal grill.
Makes about 3/4 cup.

title: apple cake squares
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; set aside.
Cream shortening; add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Fold in apples, nuts and raisins.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Cut into squares.
If desired, drizzle top of cooled cake with lemon glaze.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Marinate all ingredients except spaghetti overnight.
Add cooled pasta and refrigerate.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar.
Set aside.
Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add cold water, lemon juice, cinnamon and cloves.

title: pickled beets
directions: Mix together and seal in jars with hot lids.

title: nut cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually and beat until fluffy. Add egg yolks and beat until well blended.
Sift flour; measure and add salt and baking powder and sift again.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and flavoring.
Beat thoroughly after each addition.
Fold in chopped nuts and stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased loaf or layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes for layer cake and
1 hour for loaf cake.
Makes two 9-inch layers or 1 loaf, 4 x 8 x 3 1/2-inches.

title: teriyaki steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Make a sauce from ginger, garlic, onion, sugar, soy sauce and water.
Pour over meat and let stand 1 to 2 hours.
Spread out on shallow pan and broil 3 to 5 minutes on each side.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: 1-2-3 cup coconut pie
directions: Cook pie crust as directed.
Combine flour, sugar, milk and egg yolks in large microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave for 1 to 2 minutes at a time, stirring after each cycle, until thick.
(It may take as long as 10 minutes.)
After filling starts to thicken, add vanilla, butter and salt; stir well.
Continue to microwave until done.
Add coconut and mix until well combined.
(Save enough coconut to sprinkle on meringue.)
Pour into pie crusts.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients twice.
Add coffee, mayonnaise and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with frosting of your choice.

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling salted water; drain.
While spaghetti is cooking, cook bacon in frying pan until crisp; drain on paper towels, saving 2 tablespoons pan drippings.
Beat eggs, Parmesan cheese, parsley, salt, pepper and reserved pan drippings together.
Place hot spaghetti in heated serving bowl.
Add egg mixture, tossing well.
Add bacon; toss again and serve PRONTO!

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Heat oven at 350°.
Place foil on cookie sheet for easy removal.
Beat egg whites until almost stiff.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet 2 inches apart. Place in heated oven.
Turn oven off and leave overnight.

title: lazy man's peach pie
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Make batter of sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour batter over butter, then add fruit and juice.
Bake at 325° until dough is brown, about 60 minutes.

title: apricot cheese ball
directions: Chop apricots very fine.
Mix cream cheese, apricots, ginger and cinnamon.
Shape the mixture into a ball and chill until firm. Roll ball in chopped nuts, then coat with apricot preserves.
Serve with gingersnaps.

title: easy congealed salad
directions: Mix jello according to directions.
Add other ingredients and congeal.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift flour.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make paste from red food coloring and some flour.
Add to creamed mixture.
Sift and measure cocoa.
Sift again with remaining flour.
Add salt, vanilla and buttermilk.
Add alternately with flour mixture. Beat well.

title: rusty's salsa
directions: Mix tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Add salt, pepper, garlic and vinegar.
Cut up or blend tomatoes, onion and jalapenos. Bring to a boil; simmer to desired thickness (approximately 1 hour).
Yields about 2 quarts.

title: burrito casserole
directions: Place burritos in large baking dish.
Cover with chili and cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and cheese is melted well.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: knorr's spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain the spinach (I squeeze out the moisture).
Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Brown bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan.
Add 1/4 cup water and spinach.
Cover and simmer until done.
Sprinkle flour over the spinach.
Stir until well blended and thick.
Add salt and pepper to taste and enough milk to loosen and cream.
Let simmer for about 5 minutes.
Add bacon chunks.
Stir and serve.

title: ginger crinkles
directions: Mix oil and sugar thoroughly.
Add egg, then molasses.
Mix dry ingredients together and add.
Form into balls and roll in cinnamon-sugar.
Bake on ungreased sheet 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: I use chicken breast tenders.

title: peanut pattie
directions: Combine 3 cups sugar, 1 cup syrup and 1 cup water in large saucepan.
Bring to boil; add peanuts and food coloring.
Boil to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, salt and butter. Stir until thick; spread out onto buttered tin foil.

title: easy clam chowder
directions: Saute onion and celery (with leaves) in margarine.
Mix with soups, clams and milk to desired consistency.
Add parsley, white pepper, paprika and nutmeg.
This makes a nice Sunday night meal with salad, bread and fruit.
We used to have this on Christmas Eve.

title: magnificent macaroni salad
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients until well blended. Refrigerate mixture for at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: catfish stew
directions: Cook catfish in boiler; remove bones.
Cook potatoes and onions until they are mush.
Add fish and small can of milk to boiler; let cook until all is done.
Add large cans of milk, water, margarine, corn, salt and pepper.
Stir over low heat until it comes to a boil; set off.
Stir good, or it will stick.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: bishop's bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease 10 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan; line bottom with wax paper.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt in medium bowl.
Stir in chocolate pieces, nuts, dates and cherries until well coated with flour.
Beat eggs well in large bowl at medium speed of mixer.
Fold in flour mixture.
Turn into loaf pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Cool in pan on wire rack. When cool, remove from pan; wrap in foil and store.
Serve in slices.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: whole wheat butter rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add rest of ingredients, except whole wheat flour, and beat.
Stir in whole wheat flour.
Cover and let rise 30 minutes.
Spoon batter into greased muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: any time punch
directions: Just follow ingredients. Better if mixture is almost frozen before using. Just add ginger ale.

title: magic beef casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni, then put in casserole dish.
Stir in soup and add sour cream.
Pour beef mixture over macaroni.
Mix well and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Grate Cheddar cheese over the top as soon as removed from the oven.

title: extra-tender pancakes
directions: Mix milk, egg and butter.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir milk mixture into flour mixture just until moistened.
Heat lightly oiled griddle until hot.

title: shoestring salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except shoestring potatoes.
Chill.
Add potatoes before serving.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix and blend well; bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hamburger cookies
directions: Put 1 peppermint patty between 2 vanilla wafers.
Mix small amount of green food coloring on coconut to make it look like lettuce.
Place on top of patty.
Add sesame seed to top vanilla wafer.
Put in microwave for 30 second to 1 minute to warm (optional).
Fun for parties.

title: baked brisket
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Add water 1 inch from bottom of pan. Add brisket and ingredients.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 4 to 5 hours.
One hour before it's done, add potatoes and carrots. Re-cover with foil.
Cook 1 more hour.
Add water if needed.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: baked seafood casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1/4 cup bread crumbs; pour into buttered shallow baking dish.
Top with remaining bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt
in saucepan.
Gradually stir in
milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until it comes to
a boil
and
thickens.
Continue to cook 1 minute;
stir. Remove from heat;
stir 1/2 mixture into egg yolks, then stir egg mixture
into
saucepan.
Cook and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add butter, vanilla and coconut.
Cool 20 minutes. Beat 30 seconds.
Pour in shell.
Top with meringue.

title: date balls
directions: Melt margarine with sugar and chopped dates.
Cook between 5 and 10 minutes on medium.
Put in Rice Krispies, chopped pecans and vanilla.
Stir while hot; pinch off while hot and roll into balls, then roll in powdered sugar.

title: angel yeast biscuits
directions: Sift flour, sugar and soda together.
Cut in shortening. Dissolve yeast into water and add to flour.
Stir in buttermilk. Knead with enough flour to make a workable dough.
Roll out and cut.
It does not have to rise.
Bake at 375° until brown.
This dough will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks.
You can cut out and put back in refrigerator before baking.

title: indiana baked beans
directions: Soak beans in a large kettle overnight.
Simmer about 1 hour in water in which
they were soaked.
Mix together sugar, salt, ketchup, molasses and mustard.
Add to beans.
Lay onion on top. Bake, covered, at
for
hours.
Add
boiling water if necessary to keep beans
from
becoming
dry.
Remove the onion before serving.

title: 14 day pickles
directions: First Day:
Wash cucumbers and pack tightly in gallon jar. Cover with boiling water to which salt has been added.
Let stand for 24 hours.

title: cathy's apple cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread apple pie filling on top. Bake as directed on box. Drizzle with glaze.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Mix all in the bacon and when it has boiled, pour over lettuce.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: In large saucepan, cook onion, green pepper and 2 tablespoons butter until tender.
Combine cubed chicken and green chilies with onion and pepper.
Remove from pan and set aside.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Put zucchini, onions, peppers and garlic in large crock.
Add 2 tablespoons salt and cover with ice.
Let stand 3 hours.
Then drain.
Combine sugar, spices and vinegar with zucchini mixture and heat to boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Seal in hot jars.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Put in a greased casserole dish. Top with a mixture of butter and crumbled cornflakes.

title: pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast, stir in oil, add flour and salt.
Knead until smooth and not sticky.
Grease bowl and flip dough.
Let rise 2 hours.
Roll on floured board and put in pizza pan.
Top with favorites and bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until crisp.
Makes 2 round pizzas.

title: green pea-cauliflower salad
directions: Stir together and chill overnight.

title: ham and cheese potato salad
directions: In a saucepan, cook potatoes in boiling, salted water until tender, drain and cool.
Meanwhile, in a large salad bowl combine mayonnaise, sour cream, mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper; mix well.
Cut potatoes into cubes, add to mayonnaise mixture and toss to coat.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for at least two hours.
Yield:
16-20 servings.

title: coconut pie(makes its own crust)
directions: Mix well and pour into 2 Pyrex pie dishes.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal-fudge bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan. Mix sugar, 3/4 cup butter, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in Bisquick and oatmeal until uniform consistency.
Heat chocolate chips, milk, 2 tablespoons butter and salt in 2-quart pan over low heat (or in microwave), stirring constantly until smooth.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Press 2/3 of the oatmeal mixture into pan.
Spread chocolate mixture over oatmeal and top with remaining oatmeal by drops.
Bake until light brown.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter and chocolate chips together.
Set confectioners sugar aside.
Mix remaining ingredients together in a bowl.
Mix well.
Place confectioners sugar in a bag with mixture and shake well.

title: lynn's chicken
directions: Fry chicken until brown.
Put in baking dish. Cover with tomatoes and A.1. sauce. Cover and bake 1 hour.
Uncover.
Add cheese and bake 1/2 hour longer.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown onion and garlic flakes and add tomato sauce, tomato soup, tomato juice, water, bay leaves, basil, oregano and thyme in saucepan. Simmer at least 10 minutes. Brown hamburger, green pepper and mushrooms. Add to other mixture and simmer for at least 30 minutes.

title: famous fruitcake cookies
directions: Soak cherries, pineapple, citron and white raisins overnight in sherry or fruit juice.
Cover with foil.

title: autumn salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients. Chill for
1 hour. Fold in whipped topping and coconut. Sprinkle with nuts and cherry bits.

title: nutmeg buttered carrots
directions: Bring 1-inch of water to a boil.
Add all ingredients. Simmer, covered, 15 minutes or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter, sugar, flour, 2 eggs and vanilla together.
Mix contents of brownie mix as directed, using 2 eggs. Pour brownie mix in oblong pan sprayed with Pam.
Pour cream cheese mixture over it and run a knife through the mixtures but don't mix completely.
Bake at 350° until firm, about 30 minutes. Cut and cover with Saran Wrap.

title: rosemary pound cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Cut in shortening. Combine wet ingredients in a separate bowl.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Batter will be somewhat stiff.
Place in Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.

title: microwave mashed potato favorite
directions: Combine potatoes and water in 2-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Cover with lid.
Microwave on High for 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring 2 to 3 times. Drain.
Mash until smooth.
Beat in milk until desired consistency.
Mix in butter until melted.
Stir in cottage cheese, onion and salt.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole or serving bowl.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with casserole lid or overturned plate.
Microwave on High for 7 to 8 minutes or until heated through (160°).

title: beau monde dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in large bowl and refrigerate a couple of days for best flavor.

title: mexican lasagna rollups
directions: Boil noodles as directed on package and drain.
Run cold water over noodles to stop cooking process.
Brown hamburger and onions in skillet, drain.
Add 1/2 c. salsa, taco seasoning mix and water. Boil down to water evaporates.
Remove from heat and set aside to cool slightly.
In 13 x 9 casserole dish, spread approx. 2 Tbsp. of salsa on bottom of dish.
Cut each lasagna noodle in half the short way.
Take one half of the noodle and place 1 Tbsp. of the beef mixture on the noodle.
Do Not Overfill!!!

title: japanese fruit pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Melt oleo and chips.
Add all other ingredients; mix well. Divide into two pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cookie pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugars, margarine, vanilla and egg. Stir in flour (dough will be stiff).
Stir in chocolate chips. Spread or pat dough in ungreased 12-inch pizza pan or on cookie sheet.
Bake about 15 minutes or until golden brown; cool.
Just before serving, spread cookie with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with walnuts, coconut and M&M's. Cut into wedges.
Refrigerate any remaining cookie.
Serves 16.

title: franklin nut cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar; add beaten eggs and add 3 cups of flour.
Mix remaining flour with fruits and nuts.
Stir into batter.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Cool in pan.

title: lasagne
directions: Fry hamburger with onion until brown.
Add spaghetti sauce, salt and pepper; simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook lasagne noodles according to package directions; drain.
Place a layer of noodles in bottom of 14 x 10-inch square pan.
Add a layer of sauce, then cheese.
Continue layering until everything is used, except enough cheese for top.
Finish with cheese on top and bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain squash.
Scald milk and butter.
Beat eggs slightly. Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crescent chicken
directions: Cook chicken and remove bones.
Mix chicken soup, 1 cup chicken broth and cheese.
Heat until warm.
Roll chicken in crescent rolls and place in baking dish.
Pour liquid over this and add remaining chicken.
Bake until rolls are golden brown.

title: the best margaritas
directions: Blend tequila, Triple Sec and lime juice.
Add ice cubes and blend until slush.
Pour into 4 salt-rimmed glasses.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream together in a large mixing bowl the margarine, peanut butter, sugar and eggs.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook chicken breasts, reserve broth.
Cover vegetables with water and cook until tender.
The last 5 minutes, add the broccoli. Drain and reserve the broth.
Take chicken broth, vegetable broth and enough more water to make 3-quarts.
Bring to boil.
Add bouillon cubes.
Melt margarine.
Mix flour in well. Add to liquids.
Heat until thick.
Add Velveeta cheese.
Stir until melted.
Then add vegetables, chopped up chicken and 1 package frozen peas.
Heat thoroughly.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: matchless meat loaf
directions: Blend molasses and mustard in large bowl. Stir in vinegar, ketchup, milk, eggs, onion soup mix and bread crumbs. Stir to mash crumbs. Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Pack into greased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inches). Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Slice to serve.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt Milky Ways in one stick of oleo.
Cream sugar and one stick of oleo.
Add eggs, then flour and soda alternately with buttermilk.
Add melted candy mixture and nuts.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) greased pans at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done. (Use Milky Way Icing.)

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon.
Set aside 2 tablespoons of the juice.
Mix salmon, egg and onion.
Stir in flour.
Add baking powder to salmon juice.
Stir into salmon mixture.
Form patties.
Brown on both sides.
Cooking time is approximately 5 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour.
Melt butter; add to sugar mixture. Mix eggs and add.
Mix well; do not beat.
Add vanilla and milk. Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce to 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mama's banana bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat at medium speed, shortening, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Add bananas; mix in dry ingredients.
Stir until just smooth.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool overnight before slicing.

title: cherry, pineapple salad
directions: Mix together Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Add pie filling, pineapple and pecans to milk mixture; mix gently.
Fold Cool Whip into salad.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except crab.
Shape on a large dish.
Pat over top, then add crab meat.
Pat again.
Pour Crossman Blackwell cocktail sauce over all.
Serve with crackers.
Best chilled.

title: honey popcorn balls
directions: Combine ingredients in pan over low heat.
Cook until mixture bubbles around edges.
Pour over popcorn, press into balls.
Be careful!
It will be hot.

title: creamed onions
directions: Put onions in 1 inch of boiling salted water.
Bring again to boil.
Cover; cook for 10 to 15 minutes, or until tender.
Drain; place in serving dish.
While onions are cooking, melt butter over medium heat.
Add flour; stir until smooth.
Gradually add milk and salt to pan; stir constantly over medium heat until thick (just starts to boil).
Pour over onions; sprinkle with paprika and serve.

title: white chocolate wonders
directions: Take small Ritz crackers; spread smooth peanut butter between 2 and make a sandwich.
Melt almond bark; dip cracker sandwiches in almond bark.
Set on wax paper and allow to harden.
Enjoy!

title: lynn's italian zucchini pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 10-inch skillet, cook zucchini and onion in butter until tender.
Stir in parsley and seasonings.
In a large bowl, blend eggs and cheese.
Stir in vegetable mixture. Spread dough into an ungreased 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Press over bottom and up sides to form a crust.
Spread mustard over crust with a spoon.
Pour vegetable mixture over crust evenly.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.
(If crust becomes too brown during baking, cover with foil.) Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: sugar-free strawberry banana pie
directions: Combine jello, pudding, Sweet 'N Low and water in saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Cool mixture and add strawberries (berries may be sweetened if you wish).
Pour into pie shell and refrigerate for several hours.
Serve with whipped cream.
Makes 6 generous servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well; shape into ball.
Roll in finely chopped pecans.
Chill 24 hours and serve.

title: peanut butter delight
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, margarine and milk in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add oats and peanut butter.
Stir well.
Drop 1 tablespoon of mixture onto waxed paper until firm.

title: breakfast egg dish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat; drain.
Butter both sides of bread; use to line a 10 x 15-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Beat eggs; add milk and cream.
Mix well; pour over bread and cheese.
Sprinkle with 3/4 teaspoon salt and a little pepper. Top with meat.
Thyme or parsley may be sprinkled over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cheddar muffins
directions: Prepare Cheddar Muffins, substituting 3/4 cup yellow corn flour for 3/4 cup of the flour and omitting the Cheddar cheese and chives.

Fold in 1 small red jalapeno pepper (stem, ribs, and seeds removed and discarded), finely chopped, 1 cup fresh or frozen yellow whole kernel corn and 1 tablespoon chopped cilantro before spooning into cups.
Makes 24 (1 1/2-inch).

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Wash zucchini; do not pare.
Cut on diagonal into 1/2-inch slices.
Saute onion in butter in a large skillet.
Add zucchini, salt, pepper and oregano; mix well.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes and cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Add corn and cook until corn is heated.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Cover with crumbs and brown in oven until golden.

title: creamy cheese potatoes
directions: In medium saucepan, over low heat, blend milk into cream cheese.
If necessary, beat smooth with rotary beater.
Stir in chives, onion and salt.
Add cubed potato; stir carefully to coat. Turn potato-cheese mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Or, cook in saucepan over low heat until heated through.

title: oreo cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and oil together until moistened.
Roll cookie-size dough in hand.
Press slightly on cookie sheet, about 1 inch apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until cookie is done.
Do not overbake. When cookies cool, make sandwich, using frosting.

title: corn pudding by aunt sallie brooks
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until brown.

title: fudge
directions: Mix
chocolate	chips,	nuts,
butter
and vanilla in a large bowl.
Set aside.
Mix sugar, milk and marshmallows in a saucepan. Bring
to
a boil and boil for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour
over
mixture
in bowl and stir until chocolate chips are dissolved.
Pour into a buttered dish. Cut into squares when cool.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix jello pudding and milk until smooth.
Add Cool Whip to pudding mixture. Layer 9 x 13-inch dish with crackers.
Add pudding mixture, alternating with crackers, pudding mixture and top with crackers. Chill for a few hours or overnight and top with frosting.
Frosting will spread easier if put in microwave for 20 seconds.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Beat cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, about 4 hours. Before serving, arrange fruit on filling.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Then add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in layer cake pans in a 350° oven until done (toothpick comes out clean).
Ice with favorite frosting.
If you want a loaf cake, use only 1/2 cup milk.

title: popovers
directions: Beat 2 eggs until foamy.
Stir in 1 cup milk and 1 teaspoon melted butter.
Sift into this egg mixture the flour and salt.

title: baked bean salad
directions: Brown together first 3 ingredients and drain on a paper towel. In a separate bowl, combine the rest of the ingredients.
Mix all together in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pink punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Serve over ice cubes. Serves 8.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Dust chicken with flour and sprinkle each piece with the garlic and pepper.
Set aside.
Saute mushrooms in butter until semi-soft.
Set aside and reserve liquid.
In frypan, brown chicken until fully cooked, adding oil as necessary.

title: apple oatmeal crisp
directions: Place apples in greased 2-quart casserole.
Combine brown sugar, butter, oats, flour and cinnamon.
Mix until crumbly and then press firmly over the apples.
Bake in 350° oven for one hour.
Serve with cream, plain or whipped.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all together well.
May be used with potato chips, Fritos, etc.

title: refrigerator slaw(this will last for weeks)
directions: Mix all ingredients except sugar.
Stir in sugar.

title: rhonda's taco dip
directions: Cook and drain ground beef.
Add taco mix.
Layer beef, 1 jar taco sauce, sour cream, 1 jar taco sauce and Cheddar cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: t's impossible fruit pie
directions: Blend all ingredients and pour into a greased and floured pie pan.
Will be thick and pasty.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 45 minutes or until firm and golden brown.

title: granny's sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add other ingredients until mixed well. Spoon dough on a lightly greased pan. Bake in the oven 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 3 dozen

title: the cake that never lasts
directions: Make cake according to directions on package.
Pour cake into a 9 x 13-inch pan and cook.
Leave cake in pan.
When done, poke a few holes in top with pencil.
Put pineapple (undrained) and sugar in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Stir so it won't burn.
Let boil 5 minutes; pour onto cake and let cool.
Mix pudding according to directions; spread on cake, then top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with shredded coconut and nuts.
